module Network.AWS.ElasticBeanstalk.Types.BuildConfiguration

-- | Settings for an AWS CodeBuild build.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newBuildConfiguration</a> smart constructor.
data BuildConfiguration
BuildConfiguration' :: Maybe Text -> Maybe Int -> Maybe ComputeType -> Text -> Text -> BuildConfiguration

-- | The name of the artifact of the CodeBuild build. If provided, Elastic
--   Beanstalk stores the build artifact in the S3 location
--   <i>S3-bucket</i>/resources/<i>application-name</i>/codebuild/codebuild-<i>version-label</i>-<i>artifact-name</i>.zip.
--   If not provided, Elastic Beanstalk stores the build artifact in the S3
--   location
--   <i>S3-bucket</i>/resources/<i>application-name</i>/codebuild/codebuild-<i>version-label</i>.zip.
[$sel:artifactName:BuildConfiguration'] :: BuildConfiguration -> Maybe Text

-- | How long in minutes, from 5 to 480 (8 hours), for AWS CodeBuild to
--   wait until timing out any related build that does not get marked as
--   completed. The default is 60 minutes.
[$sel:timeoutInMinutes:BuildConfiguration'] :: BuildConfiguration -> Maybe Int

-- | Information about the compute resources the build project will use.
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li><pre>BUILD_GENERAL1_SMALL: Use up to 3 GB memory and 2 vCPUs for
--   builds</pre></li>
--   <li><pre>BUILD_GENERAL1_MEDIUM: Use up to 7 GB memory and 4 vCPUs for
--   builds</pre></li>
--   <li><pre>BUILD_GENERAL1_LARGE: Use up to 15 GB memory and 8 vCPUs for
--   builds</pre></li>
--   </ul>
[$sel:computeType:BuildConfiguration'] :: BuildConfiguration -> Maybe ComputeType

-- | The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the AWS Identity and Access
--   Management (IAM) role that enables AWS CodeBuild to interact with
--   dependent AWS services on behalf of the AWS account.
[$sel:codeBuildServiceRole:BuildConfiguration'] :: BuildConfiguration -> Text

-- | The ID of the Docker image to use for this build project.
[$sel:image:BuildConfiguration'] :: BuildConfiguration -> Text

-- | Create a value of <a>BuildConfiguration</a> with all optional fields
--   omitted.
--

--   <li><pre>BUILD_GENERAL1_MEDIUM: Use up to 7 GB memory and 4 vCPUs for
--   builds</pre></li>
--   <li><pre>BUILD_GENERAL1_LARGE: Use up to 15 GB memory and 8 vCPUs for
--   builds</pre></li>
--   </ul>
buildConfiguration_computeType :: Lens' BuildConfiguration (Maybe ComputeType)

-- | The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the AWS Identity and Access
--   Management (IAM) role that enables AWS CodeBuild to interact with
--   dependent AWS services on behalf of the AWS account.
buildConfiguration_codeBuildServiceRole :: Lens' BuildConfiguration Text

-- | The ID of the Docker image to use for this build project.
buildConfiguration_image :: Lens' BuildConfiguration Text
instance GHC.Generics.Generic Network.AWS.ElasticBeanstalk.Types.BuildConfiguration.BuildConfiguration
instance GHC.Show.Show Network.AWS.ElasticBeanstalk.Types.BuildConfiguration.BuildConfiguration
instance GHC.Read.Read Network.AWS.ElasticBeanstalk.Types.BuildConfiguration.BuildConfiguration
instance GHC.Classes.Eq Network.AWS.ElasticBeanstalk.Types.BuildConfiguration.BuildConfiguration
instance Data.Hashable.Class.Hashable Network.AWS.ElasticBeanstalk.Types.BuildConfiguration.BuildConfiguration
instance Control.DeepSeq.NFData Network.AWS.ElasticBeanstalk.Types.BuildConfiguration.BuildConfiguration

module Network.AWS.ElasticBeanstalk.Types.ConfigurationOptionSetting

-- | A specification identifying an individual configuration option along
--   with its current value. For a list of possible namespaces and option
--   values, see <a>Option Values</a> in the <i>AWS Elastic Beanstalk
--   Developer Guide</i>.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newConfigurationOptionSetting</a> smart constructor.
data ConfigurationOptionSetting
ConfigurationOptionSetting' :: Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> ConfigurationOptionSetting

-- | The name of the configuration option.
[$sel:optionName:ConfigurationOptionSetting'] :: ConfigurationOptionSetting -> Maybe Text

-- | The current value for the configuration option.
[$sel:value:ConfigurationOptionSetting'] :: ConfigurationOptionSetting -> Maybe Text

-- | A unique namespace that identifies the option's associated AWS
--   resource.
[$sel:namespace:ConfigurationOptionSetting'] :: ConfigurationOptionSetting -> Maybe Text

-- | A unique resource name for the option setting. Use it for a time–based
--   scaling configuration option.
[$sel:resourceName:ConfigurationOptionSetting'] :: ConfigurationOptionSetting -> Maybe Text

-- | Create a value of <a>ConfigurationOptionSetting</a> with all optional
--   fields omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:optionName:ConfigurationOptionSetting'</a>,
--   <a>configurationOptionSetting_optionName</a> - The name of the
--   configuration option.
--   
--   <a>$sel:value:ConfigurationOptionSetting'</a>,
--   <a>configurationOptionSetting_value</a> - The current value for the
--   configuration option.
--   
--   <a>$sel:namespace:ConfigurationOptionSetting'</a>,
--   <a>configurationOptionSetting_namespace</a> - A unique namespace that
--   identifies the option's associated AWS resource.
--   
--   <a>$sel:resourceName:ConfigurationOptionSetting'</a>,
--   <a>configurationOptionSetting_resourceName</a> - A unique resource
--   name for the option setting. Use it for a time–based scaling
--   configuration option.
newConfigurationOptionSetting :: ConfigurationOptionSetting

-- | The name of the configuration option.
configurationOptionSetting_optionName :: Lens' ConfigurationOptionSetting (Maybe Text)

-- | The current value for the configuration option.
configurationOptionSetting_value :: Lens' ConfigurationOptionSetting (Maybe Text)

-- | A unique namespace that identifies the option's associated AWS
--   resource.
configurationOptionSetting_namespace :: Lens' ConfigurationOptionSetting (Maybe Text)

-- | A unique resource name for the option setting. Use it for a time–based
--   scaling configuration option.
configurationOptionSetting_resourceName :: Lens' ConfigurationOptionSetting (Maybe Text)
instance GHC.Generics.Generic Network.AWS.ElasticBeanstalk.Types.ConfigurationOptionSetting.ConfigurationOptionSetting
instance GHC.Show.Show Network.AWS.ElasticBeanstalk.Types.ConfigurationOptionSetting.ConfigurationOptionSetting
instance GHC.Read.Read Network.AWS.ElasticBeanstalk.Types.ConfigurationOptionSetting.ConfigurationOptionSetting
instance GHC.Classes.Eq Network.AWS.ElasticBeanstalk.Types.ConfigurationOptionSetting.ConfigurationOptionSetting

module Network.AWS.ElasticBeanstalk.Types.ConfigurationSettingsDescription

-- | Describes the settings for a configuration set.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newConfigurationSettingsDescription</a> smart
--   constructor.
data ConfigurationSettingsDescription
ConfigurationSettingsDescription' :: Maybe Text -> Maybe ISO8601 -> Maybe Text -> Maybe ConfigurationDeploymentStatus -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe ISO8601 -> Maybe [ConfigurationOptionSetting] -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> ConfigurationSettingsDescription

-- | If not <tt>null</tt>, the name of the configuration template for this
--   configuration set.
[$sel:templateName:ConfigurationSettingsDescription'] :: ConfigurationSettingsDescription -> Maybe Text

-- | The date (in UTC time) when this configuration set was created.
[$sel:dateCreated:ConfigurationSettingsDescription'] :: ConfigurationSettingsDescription -> Maybe ISO8601

-- | The name of the solution stack this configuration set uses.
[$sel:solutionStackName:ConfigurationSettingsDescription'] :: ConfigurationSettingsDescription -> Maybe Text

-- | If this configuration set is associated with an environment, the
--   <tt>DeploymentStatus</tt> parameter indicates the deployment status of
--   this configuration set:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li><tt>null</tt>: This configuration is not associated with a running
--   environment.</li>
--   <li><tt>pending</tt>: This is a draft configuration that is not
--   deployed to the associated environment but is in the process of
--   deploying.</li>
--   <li><tt>deployed</tt>: This is the configuration that is currently
--   deployed to the associated running environment.</li>
--   <li><tt>failed</tt>: This is a draft configuration that failed to
--   successfully deploy.</li>
--   </ul>
[$sel:deploymentStatus:ConfigurationSettingsDescription'] :: ConfigurationSettingsDescription -> Maybe ConfigurationDeploymentStatus

-- | The ARN of the platform version.
[$sel:platformArn:ConfigurationSettingsDescription'] :: ConfigurationSettingsDescription -> Maybe Text

-- | If not <tt>null</tt>, the name of the environment for this
--   configuration set.
[$sel:environmentName:ConfigurationSettingsDescription'] :: ConfigurationSettingsDescription -> Maybe Text

-- | The date (in UTC time) when this configuration set was last modified.
[$sel:dateUpdated:ConfigurationSettingsDescription'] :: ConfigurationSettingsDescription -> Maybe ISO8601

-- | A list of the configuration options and their values in this
--   configuration set.
[$sel:optionSettings:ConfigurationSettingsDescription'] :: ConfigurationSettingsDescription -> Maybe [ConfigurationOptionSetting]

-- | Describes this configuration set.
[$sel:description:ConfigurationSettingsDescription'] :: ConfigurationSettingsDescription -> Maybe Text

-- | The name of the application associated with this configuration set.
[$sel:applicationName:ConfigurationSettingsDescription'] :: ConfigurationSettingsDescription -> Maybe Text

-- | Create a value of <a>ConfigurationSettingsDescription</a> with all
--   optional fields omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:templateName:ConfigurationSettingsDescription'</a>,
--   <a>configurationSettingsDescription_templateName</a> - If not
--   <tt>null</tt>, the name of the configuration template for this
--   configuration set.
--   
--   <a>$sel:dateCreated:ConfigurationSettingsDescription'</a>,
--   <a>configurationSettingsDescription_dateCreated</a> - The date (in UTC
--   time) when this configuration set was created.
--   
--   <a>$sel:solutionStackName:ConfigurationSettingsDescription'</a>,
--   <a>configurationSettingsDescription_solutionStackName</a> - The name
--   of the solution stack this configuration set uses.
--   
--   <a>$sel:deploymentStatus:ConfigurationSettingsDescription'</a>,
--   <a>configurationSettingsDescription_deploymentStatus</a> - If this
--   configuration set is associated with an environment, the
--   <tt>DeploymentStatus</tt> parameter indicates the deployment status of
--   this configuration set:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li><tt>null</tt>: This configuration is not associated with a running
--   environment.</li>
--   <li><tt>pending</tt>: This is a draft configuration that is not
--   deployed to the associated environment but is in the process of
--   deploying.</li>
--   <li><tt>deployed</tt>: This is the configuration that is currently
--   deployed to the associated running environment.</li>
--   <li><tt>failed</tt>: This is a draft configuration that failed to
--   successfully deploy.</li>
--   </ul>
--   
--   <a>$sel:platformArn:ConfigurationSettingsDescription'</a>,
--   <a>configurationSettingsDescription_platformArn</a> - The ARN of the
--   platform version.
--   
--   <a>$sel:environmentName:ConfigurationSettingsDescription'</a>,
--   <a>configurationSettingsDescription_environmentName</a> - If not
--   <tt>null</tt>, the name of the environment for this configuration set.
--   
--   <a>$sel:dateUpdated:ConfigurationSettingsDescription'</a>,
--   <a>configurationSettingsDescription_dateUpdated</a> - The date (in UTC
--   time) when this configuration set was last modified.
--   
--   <a>$sel:optionSettings:ConfigurationSettingsDescription'</a>,
--   <a>configurationSettingsDescription_optionSettings</a> - A list of the
--   configuration options and their values in this configuration set.
--   
--   <a>$sel:description:ConfigurationSettingsDescription'</a>,
--   <a>configurationSettingsDescription_description</a> - Describes this
--   configuration set.
--   
--   <a>$sel:applicationName:ConfigurationSettingsDescription'</a>,
--   <a>configurationSettingsDescription_applicationName</a> - The name of
--   the application associated with this configuration set.
newConfigurationSettingsDescription :: ConfigurationSettingsDescription

-- | If not <tt>null</tt>, the name of the configuration template for this
--   configuration set.
configurationSettingsDescription_templateName :: Lens' ConfigurationSettingsDescription (Maybe Text)

-- | The date (in UTC time) when this configuration set was created.
configurationSettingsDescription_dateCreated :: Lens' ConfigurationSettingsDescription (Maybe UTCTime)

-- | The name of the solution stack this configuration set uses.
configurationSettingsDescription_solutionStackName :: Lens' ConfigurationSettingsDescription (Maybe Text)

-- | If this configuration set is associated with an environment, the
--   <tt>DeploymentStatus</tt> parameter indicates the deployment status of
--   this configuration set:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li><tt>null</tt>: This configuration is not associated with a running
--   environment.</li>
--   <li><tt>pending</tt>: This is a draft configuration that is not
--   deployed to the associated environment but is in the process of
--   deploying.</li>
--   <li><tt>deployed</tt>: This is the configuration that is currently
--   deployed to the associated running environment.</li>
--   <li><tt>failed</tt>: This is a draft configuration that failed to
--   successfully deploy.</li>
--   </ul>
configurationSettingsDescription_deploymentStatus :: Lens' ConfigurationSettingsDescription (Maybe ConfigurationDeploymentStatus)

-- | The ARN of the platform version.
configurationSettingsDescription_platformArn :: Lens' ConfigurationSettingsDescription (Maybe Text)

-- | If not <tt>null</tt>, the name of the environment for this
--   configuration set.
configurationSettingsDescription_environmentName :: Lens' ConfigurationSettingsDescription (Maybe Text)

-- | The date (in UTC time) when this configuration set was last modified.
configurationSettingsDescription_dateUpdated :: Lens' ConfigurationSettingsDescription (Maybe UTCTime)

-- | A list of the configuration options and their values in this
--   configuration set.
configurationSettingsDescription_optionSettings :: Lens' ConfigurationSettingsDescription (Maybe [ConfigurationOptionSetting])

-- | Describes this configuration set.
configurationSettingsDescription_description :: Lens' ConfigurationSettingsDescription (Maybe Text)

-- | The name of the application associated with this configuration set.
configurationSettingsDescription_applicationName :: Lens' ConfigurationSettingsDescription (Maybe Text)
instance GHC.Generics.Generic Network.AWS.ElasticBeanstalk.Types.ConfigurationSettingsDescription.ConfigurationSettingsDescription
instance GHC.Show.Show Network.AWS.ElasticBeanstalk.Types.ConfigurationSettingsDescription.ConfigurationSettingsDescription
instance GHC.Read.Read Network.AWS.ElasticBeanstalk.Types.ConfigurationSettingsDescription.ConfigurationSettingsDescription
instance GHC.Classes.Eq Network.AWS.ElasticBeanstalk.Types.ConfigurationSettingsDescription.ConfigurationSettingsDescription

module Network.AWS.ElasticBeanstalk.Types.Deployment

-- | Information about an application version deployment.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newDeployment</a> smart constructor.
data Deployment
Deployment' :: Maybe Text -> Maybe Integer -> Maybe Text -> Maybe ISO8601 -> Deployment

-- | The status of the deployment:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li><tt>In Progress</tt> : The deployment is in progress.</li>
--   <li><tt>Deployed</tt> : The deployment succeeded.</li>
--   <li><tt>Failed</tt> : The deployment failed.</li>
--   </ul>
[$sel:status:Deployment'] :: Deployment -> Maybe Text

-- | The ID of the deployment. This number increases by one each time that
--   you deploy source code or change instance configuration settings.
[$sel:deploymentId:Deployment'] :: Deployment -> Maybe Integer

-- | The version label of the application version in the deployment.
[$sel:versionLabel:Deployment'] :: Deployment -> Maybe Text

-- | For in-progress deployments, the time that the deployment started.
--   
--   For completed deployments, the time that the deployment ended.
[$sel:deploymentTime:Deployment'] :: Deployment -> Maybe ISO8601

-- | Create a value of <a>Deployment</a> with all optional fields omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:status:Deployment'</a>, <a>deployment_status</a> - The status
--   of the deployment:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li><tt>In Progress</tt> : The deployment is in progress.</li>
--   <li><tt>Deployed</tt> : The deployment succeeded.</li>
--   <li><tt>Failed</tt> : The deployment failed.</li>
--   </ul>
--   
--   <a>$sel:deploymentId:Deployment'</a>, <a>deployment_deploymentId</a> -
--   The ID of the deployment. This number increases by one each time that
--   you deploy source code or change instance configuration settings.
--   
--   <a>$sel:versionLabel:Deployment'</a>, <a>deployment_versionLabel</a> -
--   The version label of the application version in the deployment.
--   
--   <a>$sel:deploymentTime:Deployment'</a>,
--   <a>deployment_deploymentTime</a> - For in-progress deployments, the
--   time that the deployment started.
--   
--   For completed deployments, the time that the deployment ended.
newDeployment :: Deployment

-- | The status of the deployment:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li><tt>In Progress</tt> : The deployment is in progress.</li>
--   <li><tt>Deployed</tt> : The deployment succeeded.</li>
--   <li><tt>Failed</tt> : The deployment failed.</li>
--   </ul>
deployment_status :: Lens' Deployment (Maybe Text)

-- | The ID of the deployment. This number increases by one each time that
--   you deploy source code or change instance configuration settings.
deployment_deploymentId :: Lens' Deployment (Maybe Integer)

-- | The version label of the application version in the deployment.
deployment_versionLabel :: Lens' Deployment (Maybe Text)

-- | For in-progress deployments, the time that the deployment started.
--   
--   For completed deployments, the time that the deployment ended.
deployment_deploymentTime :: Lens' Deployment (Maybe UTCTime)
instance GHC.Generics.Generic Network.AWS.ElasticBeanstalk.Types.Deployment.Deployment
instance GHC.Show.Show Network.AWS.ElasticBeanstalk.Types.Deployment.Deployment
instance GHC.Read.Read Network.AWS.ElasticBeanstalk.Types.Deployment.Deployment
instance GHC.Classes.Eq Network.AWS.ElasticBeanstalk.Types.Deployment.Deployment
instance Network.AWS.Data.XML.FromXML Network.AWS.ElasticBeanstalk.Types.Deployment.Deployment
instance Data.Hashable.Class.Hashable Network.AWS.ElasticBeanstalk.Types.Deployment.Deployment
instance Control.DeepSeq.NFData Network.AWS.ElasticBeanstalk.Types.Deployment.Deployment

module Network.AWS.ElasticBeanstalk.Types.EnvironmentInfoDescription

-- | The information retrieved from the Amazon EC2 instances.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newEnvironmentInfoDescription</a> smart constructor.
data EnvironmentInfoDescription
EnvironmentInfoDescription' :: Maybe Text -> Maybe EnvironmentInfoType -> Maybe ISO8601 -> Maybe Text -> EnvironmentInfoDescription

-- | The retrieved information. Currently contains a presigned Amazon S3
--   URL. The files are deleted after 15 minutes.
--   
--   Anyone in possession of this URL can access the files before they are
--   deleted. Make the URL available only to trusted parties.
[$sel:message:EnvironmentInfoDescription'] :: EnvironmentInfoDescription -> Maybe Text

-- | The type of information retrieved.
[$sel:infoType:EnvironmentInfoDescription'] :: EnvironmentInfoDescription -> Maybe EnvironmentInfoType

-- | The time stamp when this information was retrieved.
[$sel:sampleTimestamp:EnvironmentInfoDescription'] :: EnvironmentInfoDescription -> Maybe ISO8601

-- | The Amazon EC2 Instance ID for this information.
[$sel:ec2InstanceId:EnvironmentInfoDescription'] :: EnvironmentInfoDescription -> Maybe Text

-- | Create a value of <a>EnvironmentInfoDescription</a> with all optional
--   fields omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:message:EnvironmentInfoDescription'</a>,
--   <a>environmentInfoDescription_message</a> - The retrieved information.
--   Currently contains a presigned Amazon S3 URL. The files are deleted
--   after 15 minutes.
--   
--   Anyone in possession of this URL can access the files before they are
--   deleted. Make the URL available only to trusted parties.
--   
--   <a>$sel:infoType:EnvironmentInfoDescription'</a>,
--   <a>environmentInfoDescription_infoType</a> - The type of information
--   retrieved.
--   
--   <a>$sel:sampleTimestamp:EnvironmentInfoDescription'</a>,
--   <a>environmentInfoDescription_sampleTimestamp</a> - The time stamp
--   when this information was retrieved.
--   
--   <a>$sel:ec2InstanceId:EnvironmentInfoDescription'</a>,
--   <a>environmentInfoDescription_ec2InstanceId</a> - The Amazon EC2
--   Instance ID for this information.
newEnvironmentInfoDescription :: EnvironmentInfoDescription

-- | The retrieved information. Currently contains a presigned Amazon S3
--   URL. The files are deleted after 15 minutes.
--   
--   Anyone in possession of this URL can access the files before they are
--   deleted. Make the URL available only to trusted parties.
environmentInfoDescription_message :: Lens' EnvironmentInfoDescription (Maybe Text)

-- | The type of information retrieved.
environmentInfoDescription_infoType :: Lens' EnvironmentInfoDescription (Maybe EnvironmentInfoType)

-- | The time stamp when this information was retrieved.
environmentInfoDescription_sampleTimestamp :: Lens' EnvironmentInfoDescription (Maybe UTCTime)

-- | The Amazon EC2 Instance ID for this information.
environmentInfoDescription_ec2InstanceId :: Lens' EnvironmentInfoDescription (Maybe Text)
instance GHC.Generics.Generic Network.AWS.ElasticBeanstalk.Types.EnvironmentInfoDescription.EnvironmentInfoDescription
instance GHC.Show.Show Network.AWS.ElasticBeanstalk.Types.EnvironmentInfoDescription.EnvironmentInfoDescription
instance GHC.Read.Read Network.AWS.ElasticBeanstalk.Types.EnvironmentInfoDescription.EnvironmentInfoDescription
instance GHC.Classes.Eq Network.AWS.ElasticBeanstalk.Types.EnvironmentInfoDescription.EnvironmentInfoDescription
instance Network.AWS.Data.XML.FromXML Network.AWS.ElasticBeanstalk.Types.EnvironmentInfoDescription.EnvironmentInfoDescription
instance Data.Hashable.Class.Hashable Network.AWS.ElasticBeanstalk.Types.EnvironmentInfoDescription.EnvironmentInfoDescription
instance Control.DeepSeq.NFData Network.AWS.ElasticBeanstalk.Types.EnvironmentInfoDescription.EnvironmentInfoDescription


module Network.AWS.ElasticBeanstalk.Types.EnvironmentLink

-- | A link to another environment, defined in the environment's manifest.
--   Links provide connection information in system properties that can be
--   used to connect to another environment in the same group. See
--   <a>Environment Manifest (env.yaml)</a> for details.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newEnvironmentLink</a> smart constructor.
data EnvironmentLink
EnvironmentLink' :: Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> EnvironmentLink

-- | The name of the linked environment (the dependency).
[$sel:environmentName:EnvironmentLink'] :: EnvironmentLink -> Maybe Text

-- | The name of the link.
[$sel:linkName:EnvironmentLink'] :: EnvironmentLink -> Maybe Text

-- | Create a value of <a>EnvironmentLink</a> with all optional fields
--   omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:environmentName:EnvironmentLink'</a>,
--   <a>environmentLink_environmentName</a> - The name of the linked
--   environment (the dependency).
--   
--   <a>$sel:linkName:EnvironmentLink'</a>, <a>environmentLink_linkName</a>
--   - The name of the link.
newEnvironmentLink :: EnvironmentLink

-- | The name of the linked environment (the dependency).
environmentLink_environmentName :: Lens' EnvironmentLink (Maybe Text)

-- | The name of the link.
environmentLink_linkName :: Lens' EnvironmentLink (Maybe Text)
instance GHC.Generics.Generic Network.AWS.ElasticBeanstalk.Types.EnvironmentLink.EnvironmentLink

module Network.AWS.ElasticBeanstalk.Types.EnvironmentTier

-- | Describes the properties of an environment tier
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newEnvironmentTier</a> smart constructor.
data EnvironmentTier
EnvironmentTier' :: Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> EnvironmentTier

-- | The version of this environment tier. When you don't set a value to
--   it, Elastic Beanstalk uses the latest compatible worker tier version.
--   
--   This member is deprecated. Any specific version that you set may
--   become out of date. We recommend leaving it unspecified.
[$sel:version:EnvironmentTier'] :: EnvironmentTier -> Maybe Text

-- | The name of this environment tier.
--   
--   Valid values:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li>For <i>Web server tier</i> – <tt>WebServer</tt></li>
--   <li>For <i>Worker tier</i> – <tt>Worker</tt></li>
--   </ul>
[$sel:name:EnvironmentTier'] :: EnvironmentTier -> Maybe Text

-- | The type of this environment tier.
--   
--   Valid values:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li>For <i>Web server tier</i> – <tt>Standard</tt></li>
--   <li>For <i>Worker tier</i> – <tt>SQS/HTTP</tt></li>
--   </ul>
[$sel:type':EnvironmentTier'] :: EnvironmentTier -> Maybe Text

-- | Create a value of <a>EnvironmentTier</a> with all optional fields
--   omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:version:EnvironmentTier'</a>, <a>environmentTier_version</a> -
--   The version of this environment tier. When you don't set a value to
--   it, Elastic Beanstalk uses the latest compatible worker tier version.
--   
--   This member is deprecated. Any specific version that you set may
--   become out of date. We recommend leaving it unspecified.
--   
--   <a>$sel:name:EnvironmentTier'</a>, <a>environmentTier_name</a> - The
--   name of this environment tier.
--   
--   Valid values:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li>For <i>Web server tier</i> – <tt>WebServer</tt></li>
--   <li>For <i>Worker tier</i> – <tt>Worker</tt></li>
--   </ul>
--   
--   <a>$sel:type':EnvironmentTier'</a>, <a>environmentTier_type</a> - The
--   type of this environment tier.
--   
--   Valid values:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li>For <i>Web server tier</i> – <tt>Standard</tt></li>
--   <li>For <i>Worker tier</i> – <tt>SQS/HTTP</tt></li>
--   </ul>
newEnvironmentTier :: EnvironmentTier

--   it, Elastic Beanstalk uses the latest compatible worker tier version.
--   
--   This member is deprecated. Any specific version that you set may
--   become out of date. We recommend leaving it unspecified.
environmentTier_version :: Lens' EnvironmentTier (Maybe Text)

-- | The name of this environment tier.
--   
--   Valid values:

--   <li>For <i>Web server tier</i> – <tt>WebServer</tt></li>

module Network.AWS.ElasticBeanstalk.Types.EventDescription

-- | Describes an event.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newEventDescription</a> smart constructor.
data EventDescription
EventDescription' :: Maybe Text -> Maybe EventSeverity -> Maybe Text -> Maybe ISO8601 -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> EventDescription

-- | The name of the configuration associated with this event.
[$sel:templateName:EventDescription'] :: EventDescription -> Maybe Text

-- | The severity level of this event.
[$sel:severity:EventDescription'] :: EventDescription -> Maybe EventSeverity

-- | The event message.
[$sel:message:EventDescription'] :: EventDescription -> Maybe Text

-- | The date when the event occurred.
[$sel:eventDate:EventDescription'] :: EventDescription -> Maybe ISO8601

-- | The ARN of the platform version.
[$sel:platformArn:EventDescription'] :: EventDescription -> Maybe Text

-- | The name of the environment associated with this event.
[$sel:environmentName:EventDescription'] :: EventDescription -> Maybe Text

-- | The release label for the application version associated with this
--   event.
[$sel:versionLabel:EventDescription'] :: EventDescription -> Maybe Text

-- | The web service request ID for the activity of this event.
[$sel:requestId:EventDescription'] :: EventDescription -> Maybe Text

-- | The application associated with the event.
[$sel:applicationName:EventDescription'] :: EventDescription -> Maybe Text

-- | Create a value of <a>EventDescription</a> with all optional fields
--   omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:templateName:EventDescription'</a>,
--   <a>eventDescription_templateName</a> - The name of the configuration
--   associated with this event.
--   
--   <a>$sel:severity:EventDescription'</a>,
--   <a>eventDescription_severity</a> - The severity level of this event.
--   
--   <a>$sel:message:EventDescription'</a>, <a>eventDescription_message</a>
--   - The event message.
--   
--   <a>$sel:eventDate:EventDescription'</a>,
--   <a>eventDescription_eventDate</a> - The date when the event occurred.
--   
--   <a>$sel:platformArn:EventDescription'</a>,
--   <a>eventDescription_platformArn</a> - The ARN of the platform version.
--   
--   <a>$sel:environmentName:EventDescription'</a>,
--   <a>eventDescription_environmentName</a> - The name of the environment
--   associated with this event.
--   
--   <a>$sel:versionLabel:EventDescription'</a>,
--   <a>eventDescription_versionLabel</a> - The release label for the
--   application version associated with this event.
--   
--   <a>$sel:requestId:EventDescription'</a>,
--   <a>eventDescription_requestId</a> - The web service request ID for the
--   activity of this event.
--   
--   <a>$sel:applicationName:EventDescription'</a>,
--   <a>eventDescription_applicationName</a> - The application associated
--   with the event.
newEventDescription :: EventDescription

-- | The name of the configuration associated with this event.
eventDescription_templateName :: Lens' EventDescription (Maybe Text)

-- | The severity level of this event.
eventDescription_severity :: Lens' EventDescription (Maybe EventSeverity)

-- | The event message.
eventDescription_message :: Lens' EventDescription (Maybe Text)

-- | The date when the event occurred.
eventDescription_eventDate :: Lens' EventDescription (Maybe UTCTime)

-- | The ARN of the platform version.
eventDescription_platformArn :: Lens' EventDescription (Maybe Text)

-- | The name of the environment associated with this event.
eventDescription_environmentName :: Lens' EventDescription (Maybe Text)

-- | The release label for the application version associated with this
--   event.
eventDescription_versionLabel :: Lens' EventDescription (Maybe Text)

-- | The web service request ID for the activity of this event.

eventDescription_applicationName :: Lens' EventDescription (Maybe Text)

module Network.AWS.ElasticBeanstalk.Types.InstanceHealthSummary

-- | Represents summary information about the health of an instance. For
--   more information, see <a>Health Colors and Statuses</a>.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newInstanceHealthSummary</a> smart constructor.
data InstanceHealthSummary
InstanceHealthSummary' :: Maybe Int -> Maybe Int -> Maybe Int -> Maybe Int -> Maybe Int -> Maybe Int -> Maybe Int -> Maybe Int -> InstanceHealthSummary

-- | <b>Green.</b> An instance is passing health checks and the health
--   agent is not reporting any problems.
[$sel:ok:InstanceHealthSummary'] :: InstanceHealthSummary -> Maybe Int

-- | <b>Grey.</b> AWS Elastic Beanstalk and the health agent are reporting
--   no data on an instance.
[$sel:noData:InstanceHealthSummary'] :: InstanceHealthSummary -> Maybe Int

-- | <b>Green.</b> An operation is in progress on an instance.
[$sel:info:InstanceHealthSummary'] :: InstanceHealthSummary -> Maybe Int

-- | <b>Red.</b> The health agent is reporting a very high number of
--   request failures or other issues for an instance or environment.
[$sel:severe:InstanceHealthSummary'] :: InstanceHealthSummary -> Maybe Int

-- | <b>Yellow.</b> The health agent is reporting a moderate number of
--   request failures or other issues for an instance or environment.
[$sel:warning:InstanceHealthSummary'] :: InstanceHealthSummary -> Maybe Int

-- | <b>Grey.</b> An operation is in progress on an instance within the
--   command timeout.
[$sel:pending:InstanceHealthSummary'] :: InstanceHealthSummary -> Maybe Int

-- | <b>Grey.</b> AWS Elastic Beanstalk and the health agent are reporting
--   an insufficient amount of data on an instance.
[$sel:unknown:InstanceHealthSummary'] :: InstanceHealthSummary -> Maybe Int

-- | <b>Red.</b> The health agent is reporting a high number of request
--   failures or other issues for an instance or environment.
[$sel:degraded:InstanceHealthSummary'] :: InstanceHealthSummary -> Maybe Int

-- | Create a value of <a>InstanceHealthSummary</a> with all optional
--   fields omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:ok:InstanceHealthSummary'</a>, <a>instanceHealthSummary_ok</a>
--   - <b>Green.</b> An instance is passing health checks and the health
--   agent is not reporting any problems.
--   
--   <a>$sel:noData:InstanceHealthSummary'</a>,
--   <a>instanceHealthSummary_noData</a> - <b>Grey.</b> AWS Elastic
--   Beanstalk and the health agent are reporting no data on an instance.
--   
--   <a>$sel:info:InstanceHealthSummary'</a>,
--   <a>instanceHealthSummary_info</a> - <b>Green.</b> An operation is in
--   progress on an instance.
--   
--   <a>$sel:severe:InstanceHealthSummary'</a>,
--   <a>instanceHealthSummary_severe</a> - <b>Red.</b> The health agent is
--   reporting a very high number of request failures or other issues for
--   an instance or environment.
--   
--   <a>$sel:warning:InstanceHealthSummary'</a>,
--   <a>instanceHealthSummary_warning</a> - <b>Yellow.</b> The health agent
--   is reporting a moderate number of request failures or other issues for
--   an instance or environment.
--   
--   <a>$sel:pending:InstanceHealthSummary'</a>,
--   <a>instanceHealthSummary_pending</a> - <b>Grey.</b> An operation is in
--   progress on an instance within the command timeout.
--   
--   <a>$sel:unknown:InstanceHealthSummary'</a>,
--   <a>instanceHealthSummary_unknown</a> - <b>Grey.</b> AWS Elastic
--   Beanstalk and the health agent are reporting an insufficient amount of
--   data on an instance.
--   
--   <a>$sel:degraded:InstanceHealthSummary'</a>,
--   <a>instanceHealthSummary_degraded</a> - <b>Red.</b> The health agent
--   is reporting a high number of request failures or other issues for an
--   instance or environment.
newInstanceHealthSummary :: InstanceHealthSummary

-- | <b>Green.</b> An instance is passing health checks and the health
--   agent is not reporting any problems.
instanceHealthSummary_ok :: Lens' InstanceHealthSummary (Maybe Int)

-- | <b>Grey.</b> AWS Elastic Beanstalk and the health agent are reporting
--   no data on an instance.
instanceHealthSummary_noData :: Lens' InstanceHealthSummary (Maybe Int)

-- | <b>Green.</b> An operation is in progress on an instance.
instanceHealthSummary_info :: Lens' InstanceHealthSummary (Maybe Int)

-- | <b>Red.</b> The health agent is reporting a very high number of
--   request failures or other issues for an instance or environment.
instanceHealthSummary_severe :: Lens' InstanceHealthSummary (Maybe Int)

-- | <b>Yellow.</b> The health agent is reporting a moderate number of
--   request failures or other issues for an instance or environment.
instanceHealthSummary_warning :: Lens' InstanceHealthSummary (Maybe Int)

-- | <b>Grey.</b> An operation is in progress on an instance within the
--   command timeout.
instanceHealthSummary_pending :: Lens' InstanceHealthSummary (Maybe Int)

-- | <b>Grey.</b> AWS Elastic Beanstalk and the health agent are reporting
--   an insufficient amount of data on an instance.
instanceHealthSummary_unknown :: Lens' InstanceHealthSummary (Maybe Int)

-- | <b>Red.</b> The health agent is reporting a high number of request
--   failures or other issues for an instance or environment.
instanceHealthSummary_degraded :: Lens' InstanceHealthSummary (Maybe Int)
instance GHC.Generics.Generic Network.AWS.ElasticBeanstalk.Types.InstanceHealthSummary.InstanceHealthSummary
instance GHC.Show.Show Network.AWS.ElasticBeanstalk.Types.InstanceHealthSummary.InstanceHealthSummary
instance GHC.Read.Read Network.AWS.ElasticBeanstalk.Types.InstanceHealthSummary.InstanceHealthSummary
instance GHC.Classes.Eq Network.AWS.ElasticBeanstalk.Types.InstanceHealthSummary.InstanceHealthSummary
instance Network.AWS.Data.XML.FromXML Network.AWS.ElasticBeanstalk.Types.InstanceHealthSummary.InstanceHealthSummary
instance Data.Hashable.Class.Hashable Network.AWS.ElasticBeanstalk.Types.InstanceHealthSummary.InstanceHealthSummary
instance Control.DeepSeq.NFData Network.AWS.ElasticBeanstalk.Types.InstanceHealthSummary.InstanceHealthSummary

module Network.AWS.ElasticBeanstalk.Types.Latency

-- | Represents the average latency for the slowest X percent of requests
--   over the last 10 seconds.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newLatency</a> smart constructor.
data Latency
Latency' :: Maybe Double -> Maybe Double -> Maybe Double -> Maybe Double -> Maybe Double -> Maybe Double -> Maybe Double -> Maybe Double -> Latency

-- | The average latency for the slowest 5 percent of requests over the
--   last 10 seconds.
[$sel:p95:Latency'] :: Latency -> Maybe Double

-- | The average latency for the slowest 0.1 percent of requests over the
--   last 10 seconds.
[$sel:p999:Latency'] :: Latency -> Maybe Double

-- | The average latency for the slowest 90 percent of requests over the
--   last 10 seconds.
[$sel:p10:Latency'] :: Latency -> Maybe Double

-- | The average latency for the slowest 1 percent of requests over the
--   last 10 seconds.
[$sel:p99:Latency'] :: Latency -> Maybe Double

-- | The average latency for the slowest 50 percent of requests over the
--   last 10 seconds.
[$sel:p50:Latency'] :: Latency -> Maybe Double

-- | The average latency for the slowest 15 percent of requests over the
--   last 10 seconds.
[$sel:p85:Latency'] :: Latency -> Maybe Double

-- | The average latency for the slowest 10 percent of requests over the
--   last 10 seconds.
[$sel:p90:Latency'] :: Latency -> Maybe Double

-- | The average latency for the slowest 25 percent of requests over the
--   last 10 seconds.
[$sel:p75:Latency'] :: Latency -> Maybe Double

-- | Create a value of <a>Latency</a> with all optional fields omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:p95:Latency'</a>, <a>latency_p95</a> - The average latency for
--   the slowest 5 percent of requests over the last 10 seconds.
--   
--   <a>$sel:p999:Latency'</a>, <a>latency_p999</a> - The average latency
--   for the slowest 0.1 percent of requests over the last 10 seconds.
--   
--   <a>$sel:p10:Latency'</a>, <a>latency_p10</a> - The average latency for
--   the slowest 90 percent of requests over the last 10 seconds.
--   
--   <a>$sel:p99:Latency'</a>, <a>latency_p99</a> - The average latency for
--   the slowest 1 percent of requests over the last 10 seconds.
--   
--   <a>$sel:p50:Latency'</a>, <a>latency_p50</a> - The average latency for
--   the slowest 50 percent of requests over the last 10 seconds.
--   
--   <a>$sel:p85:Latency'</a>, <a>latency_p85</a> - The average latency for
--   the slowest 15 percent of requests over the last 10 seconds.
--   
--   <a>$sel:p90:Latency'</a>, <a>latency_p90</a> - The average latency for
--   the slowest 10 percent of requests over the last 10 seconds.
--   
--   <a>$sel:p75:Latency'</a>, <a>latency_p75</a> - The average latency for
--   the slowest 25 percent of requests over the last 10 seconds.
newLatency :: Latency

--   last 10 seconds.

--   last 10 seconds.

--   last 10 seconds.

instance Network.AWS.Data.XML.FromXML Network.AWS.ElasticBeanstalk.Types.EnvironmentResourcesDescription.EnvironmentResourcesDescription
instance Data.Hashable.Class.Hashable Network.AWS.ElasticBeanstalk.Types.EnvironmentResourcesDescription.EnvironmentResourcesDescription
instance Control.DeepSeq.NFData Network.AWS.ElasticBeanstalk.Types.EnvironmentResourcesDescription.EnvironmentResourcesDescription


module Network.AWS.ElasticBeanstalk.Types.EnvironmentDescription

-- | Describes the properties of an environment.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newEnvironmentDescription</a> smart constructor.
data EnvironmentDescription
EnvironmentDescription' :: Maybe Bool -> Maybe Text -> Maybe EnvironmentStatus -> Maybe ISO8601 -> Maybe [EnvironmentLink] -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe EnvironmentHealth -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe ISO8601 -> Maybe EnvironmentResourcesDescription -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe EnvironmentHealthStatus -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe EnvironmentTier -> Maybe Text -> EnvironmentDescription

-- | Indicates if there is an in-progress environment configuration update
--   or application version deployment that you can cancel.
--   
--   <tt>true:</tt> There is an update in progress.
--   
--   <tt>false:</tt> There are no updates currently in progress.
[$sel:abortableOperationInProgress:EnvironmentDescription'] :: EnvironmentDescription -> Maybe Bool

-- | The name of the configuration template used to originally launch this
--   environment.
[$sel:templateName:EnvironmentDescription'] :: EnvironmentDescription -> Maybe Text

-- | The current operational status of the environment:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li><tt>Launching</tt>: Environment is in the process of initial
--   deployment.</li>
--   <li><tt>Updating</tt>: Environment is in the process of updating its
--   configuration settings or application version.</li>
--   <li><tt>Ready</tt>: Environment is available to have an action
--   performed on it, such as update or terminate.</li>
--   <li><tt>Terminating</tt>: Environment is in the shut-down
--   process.</li>
--   <li><tt>Terminated</tt>: Environment is not running.</li>
--   </ul>
[$sel:status:EnvironmentDescription'] :: EnvironmentDescription -> Maybe EnvironmentStatus

-- | The creation date for this environment.
[$sel:dateCreated:EnvironmentDescription'] :: EnvironmentDescription -> Maybe ISO8601

-- | A list of links to other environments in the same group.
[$sel:environmentLinks:EnvironmentDescription'] :: EnvironmentDescription -> Maybe [EnvironmentLink]

-- | The ID of this environment.
[$sel:environmentId:EnvironmentDescription'] :: EnvironmentDescription -> Maybe Text

-- | The name of the <tt>SolutionStack</tt> deployed with this environment.
[$sel:solutionStackName:EnvironmentDescription'] :: EnvironmentDescription -> Maybe Text

-- | The ARN of the platform version.
[$sel:platformArn:EnvironmentDescription'] :: EnvironmentDescription -> Maybe Text

-- | The name of this environment.
[$sel:environmentName:EnvironmentDescription'] :: EnvironmentDescription -> Maybe Text

-- | Describes the health status of the environment. AWS Elastic Beanstalk
--   indicates the failure levels for a running environment:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li><tt>Red</tt>: Indicates the environment is not responsive. Occurs
--   when three or more consecutive failures occur for an environment.</li>
--   <li><tt>Yellow</tt>: Indicates that something is wrong. Occurs when
--   two consecutive failures occur for an environment.</li>
--   <li><tt>Green</tt>: Indicates the environment is healthy and fully
--   functional.</li>
--   <li><tt>Grey</tt>: Default health for a new environment. The
--   environment is not fully launched and health checks have not started
--   or health checks are suspended during an <tt>UpdateEnvironment</tt> or
--   <tt>RestartEnvironment</tt> request.</li>
--   </ul>
--   
--   Default: <tt>Grey</tt>
[$sel:health:EnvironmentDescription'] :: EnvironmentDescription -> Maybe EnvironmentHealth

-- | The application version deployed in this environment.
[$sel:versionLabel:EnvironmentDescription'] :: EnvironmentDescription -> Maybe Text

-- | The URL to the CNAME for this environment.
[$sel:cname:EnvironmentDescription'] :: EnvironmentDescription -> Maybe Text

-- | The last modified date for this environment.
[$sel:dateUpdated:EnvironmentDescription'] :: EnvironmentDescription -> Maybe ISO8601

-- | The description of the AWS resources used by this environment.
[$sel:resources:EnvironmentDescription'] :: EnvironmentDescription -> Maybe EnvironmentResourcesDescription

-- | Describes this environment.
[$sel:description:EnvironmentDescription'] :: EnvironmentDescription -> Maybe Text

-- | For load-balanced, autoscaling environments, the URL to the
--   LoadBalancer. For single-instance environments, the IP address of the
--   instance.
[$sel:endpointURL:EnvironmentDescription'] :: EnvironmentDescription -> Maybe Text

-- | Returns the health status of the application running in your
--   environment. For more information, see <a>Health Colors and
--   Statuses</a>.
[$sel:healthStatus:EnvironmentDescription'] :: EnvironmentDescription -> Maybe EnvironmentHealthStatus

-- | The environment's Amazon Resource Name (ARN), which can be used in
--   other API requests that require an ARN.
[$sel:environmentArn:EnvironmentDescription'] :: EnvironmentDescription -> Maybe Text

-- | The name of the application associated with this environment.
[$sel:applicationName:EnvironmentDescription'] :: EnvironmentDescription -> Maybe Text

-- | Describes the current tier of this environment.
[$sel:tier:EnvironmentDescription'] :: EnvironmentDescription -> Maybe EnvironmentTier

-- | The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the environment's operations role.
--   For more information, see <a>Operations roles</a> in the <i>AWS
--   Elastic Beanstalk Developer Guide</i>.
[$sel:operationsRole:EnvironmentDescription'] :: EnvironmentDescription -> Maybe Text

-- | Create a value of <a>EnvironmentDescription</a> with all optional
--   fields omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:

module Network.AWS.ElasticBeanstalk.Types.ManagedAction

-- | The record of an upcoming or in-progress managed action.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newManagedAction</a> smart constructor.
data ManagedAction
ManagedAction' :: Maybe ActionStatus -> Maybe ActionType -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe ISO8601 -> ManagedAction

-- | The status of the managed action. If the action is <tt>Scheduled</tt>,
--   you can apply it immediately with ApplyEnvironmentManagedAction.
[$sel:status:ManagedAction'] :: ManagedAction -> Maybe ActionStatus

-- | The type of managed action.
[$sel:actionType:ManagedAction'] :: ManagedAction -> Maybe ActionType

-- | A unique identifier for the managed action.
[$sel:actionId:ManagedAction'] :: ManagedAction -> Maybe Text

-- | A description of the managed action.
[$sel:actionDescription:ManagedAction'] :: ManagedAction -> Maybe Text

-- | The start time of the maintenance window in which the managed action
--   will execute.
[$sel:windowStartTime:ManagedAction'] :: ManagedAction -> Maybe ISO8601

-- | Create a value of <a>ManagedAction</a> with all optional fields
--   omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:status:ManagedAction'</a>, <a>managedAction_status</a> - The
--   status of the managed action. If the action is <tt>Scheduled</tt>, you
--   can apply it immediately with ApplyEnvironmentManagedAction.
--   
--   <a>$sel:actionType:ManagedAction'</a>, <a>managedAction_actionType</a>
--   - The type of managed action.
--   
--   <a>$sel:actionId:ManagedAction'</a>, <a>managedAction_actionId</a> - A
--   unique identifier for the managed action.
--   
--   <a>$sel:actionDescription:ManagedAction'</a>,
--   <a>managedAction_actionDescription</a> - A description of the managed
--   action.
--   
--   <a>$sel:windowStartTime:ManagedAction'</a>,
--   <a>managedAction_windowStartTime</a> - The start time of the
--   maintenance window in which the managed action will execute.
newManagedAction :: ManagedAction

-- | The status of the managed action. If the action is <tt>Scheduled</tt>,
--   you can apply it immediately with ApplyEnvironmentManagedAction.
managedAction_status :: Lens' ManagedAction (Maybe ActionStatus)

-- | The type of managed action.
managedAction_actionType :: Lens' ManagedAction (Maybe ActionType)

-- | A unique identifier for the managed action.
managedAction_actionId :: Lens' ManagedAction (Maybe Text)

-- | A description of the managed action.
managedAction_actionDescription :: Lens' ManagedAction (Maybe Text)

-- | The start time of the maintenance window in which the managed action
--   will execute.
managedAction_windowStartTime :: Lens' ManagedAction (Maybe UTCTime)
instance GHC.Generics.Generic Network.AWS.ElasticBeanstalk.Types.ManagedAction.ManagedAction
instance GHC.Show.Show Network.AWS.ElasticBeanstalk.Types.ManagedAction.ManagedAction

module Network.AWS.ElasticBeanstalk.Types.ManagedActionHistoryItem

-- | The record of a completed or failed managed action.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newManagedActionHistoryItem</a> smart constructor.
data ManagedActionHistoryItem
ManagedActionHistoryItem' :: Maybe ActionHistoryStatus -> Maybe ActionType -> Maybe ISO8601 -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe ISO8601 -> Maybe Text -> Maybe FailureType -> ManagedActionHistoryItem

-- | The status of the action.
[$sel:status:ManagedActionHistoryItem'] :: ManagedActionHistoryItem -> Maybe ActionHistoryStatus

-- | The type of the managed action.
[$sel:actionType:ManagedActionHistoryItem'] :: ManagedActionHistoryItem -> Maybe ActionType

-- | The date and time that the action started executing.
[$sel:executedTime:ManagedActionHistoryItem'] :: ManagedActionHistoryItem -> Maybe ISO8601

-- | A unique identifier for the managed action.
[$sel:actionId:ManagedActionHistoryItem'] :: ManagedActionHistoryItem -> Maybe Text

-- | A description of the managed action.
[$sel:actionDescription:ManagedActionHistoryItem'] :: ManagedActionHistoryItem -> Maybe Text

-- | The date and time that the action finished executing.
[$sel:finishedTime:ManagedActionHistoryItem'] :: ManagedActionHistoryItem -> Maybe ISO8601

-- | If the action failed, a description of the failure.
[$sel:failureDescription:ManagedActionHistoryItem'] :: ManagedActionHistoryItem -> Maybe Text

-- | If the action failed, the type of failure.
[$sel:failureType:ManagedActionHistoryItem'] :: ManagedActionHistoryItem -> Maybe FailureType

-- | Create a value of <a>ManagedActionHistoryItem</a> with all optional
--   fields omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:status:ManagedActionHistoryItem'</a>,
--   <a>managedActionHistoryItem_status</a> - The status of the action.
--   
--   <a>$sel:actionType:ManagedActionHistoryItem'</a>,
--   <a>managedActionHistoryItem_actionType</a> - The type of the managed
--   action.
--   
--   <a>$sel:executedTime:ManagedActionHistoryItem'</a>,
--   <a>managedActionHistoryItem_executedTime</a> - The date and time that
--   the action started executing.
--   
--   <a>$sel:actionId:ManagedActionHistoryItem'</a>,
--   <a>managedActionHistoryItem_actionId</a> - A unique identifier for the
--   managed action.
--   
--   <a>$sel:actionDescription:ManagedActionHistoryItem'</a>,
--   <a>managedActionHistoryItem_actionDescription</a> - A description of
--   the managed action.
--   
--   <a>$sel:finishedTime:ManagedActionHistoryItem'</a>,
--   <a>managedActionHistoryItem_finishedTime</a> - The date and time that
--   the action finished executing.
--   
--   <a>$sel:failureDescription:ManagedActionHistoryItem'</a>,
--   <a>managedActionHistoryItem_failureDescription</a> - If the action
--   failed, a description of the failure.
--   
--   <a>$sel:failureType:ManagedActionHistoryItem'</a>,
--   <a>managedActionHistoryItem_failureType</a> - If the action failed,
--   the type of failure.
newManagedActionHistoryItem :: ManagedActionHistoryItem

-- | The date and time that the action started executing.
managedActionHistoryItem_executedTime :: Lens' ManagedActionHistoryItem (Maybe UTCTime)

-- | A unique identifier for the managed action.
managedActionHistoryItem_actionId :: Lens' ManagedActionHistoryItem (Maybe Text)

-- | A description of the managed action.

module Network.AWS.ElasticBeanstalk.Types.MaxAgeRule

-- | A lifecycle rule that deletes application versions after the specified
--   number of days.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newMaxAgeRule</a> smart constructor.
data MaxAgeRule
MaxAgeRule' :: Maybe Bool -> Maybe Int -> Bool -> MaxAgeRule

-- | Set to <tt>true</tt> to delete a version's source bundle from Amazon
--   S3 when Elastic Beanstalk deletes the application version.
[$sel:deleteSourceFromS3:MaxAgeRule'] :: MaxAgeRule -> Maybe Bool

-- | Specify the number of days to retain an application versions.
[$sel:maxAgeInDays:MaxAgeRule'] :: MaxAgeRule -> Maybe Int

-- | Specify <tt>true</tt> to apply the rule, or <tt>false</tt> to disable
--   it.
[$sel:enabled:MaxAgeRule'] :: MaxAgeRule -> Bool

-- | Create a value of <a>MaxAgeRule</a> with all optional fields omitted.
--

--   
--   <a>$sel:enabled:MaxAgeRule'</a>, <a>maxAgeRule_enabled</a> - Specify
--   <tt>true</tt> to apply the rule, or <tt>false</tt> to disable it.
newMaxAgeRule :: Bool -> MaxAgeRule

--   S3 when Elastic Beanstalk deletes the application version.

module Network.AWS.ElasticBeanstalk.Types.MaxCountRule

-- | A lifecycle rule that deletes the oldest application version when the
--   maximum count is exceeded.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newMaxCountRule</a> smart constructor.
data MaxCountRule
MaxCountRule' :: Maybe Int -> Maybe Bool -> Bool -> MaxCountRule

-- | Specify the maximum number of application versions to retain.
[$sel:maxCount:MaxCountRule'] :: MaxCountRule -> Maybe Int

-- | Set to <tt>true</tt> to delete a version's source bundle from Amazon
--   S3 when Elastic Beanstalk deletes the application version.
[$sel:deleteSourceFromS3:MaxCountRule'] :: MaxCountRule -> Maybe Bool

-- | Specify <tt>true</tt> to apply the rule, or <tt>false</tt> to disable
--   it.
[$sel:enabled:MaxCountRule'] :: MaxCountRule -> Bool

-- | Create a value of <a>MaxCountRule</a> with all optional fields
--   omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.

--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:

--   Specify the maximum number of application versions to retain.
--   
--   <a>$sel:deleteSourceFromS3:MaxCountRule'</a>,
--   <a>maxCountRule_deleteSourceFromS3</a> - Set to <tt>true</tt> to
--   delete a version's source bundle from Amazon S3 when Elastic Beanstalk
--   deletes the application version.
--   
--   <a>$sel:enabled:MaxCountRule'</a>, <a>maxCountRule_enabled</a> -
--   Specify <tt>true</tt> to apply the rule, or <tt>false</tt> to disable
--   it.
newMaxCountRule :: Bool -> MaxCountRule

maxCountRule_maxCount :: Lens' MaxCountRule (Maybe Int)

-- | Set to <tt>true</tt> to delete a version's source bundle from Amazon
--   S3 when Elastic Beanstalk deletes the application version.

module Network.AWS.ElasticBeanstalk.Types.ApplicationVersionLifecycleConfig

-- | The application version lifecycle settings for an application. Defines
--   the rules that Elastic Beanstalk applies to an application's versions
--   in order to avoid hitting the per-region limit for application
--   versions.
--   
--   When Elastic Beanstalk deletes an application version from its
--   database, you can no longer deploy that version to an environment. The
--   source bundle remains in S3 unless you configure the rule to delete
--   it.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newApplicationVersionLifecycleConfig</a> smart
--   constructor.
data ApplicationVersionLifecycleConfig
ApplicationVersionLifecycleConfig' :: Maybe MaxCountRule -> Maybe MaxAgeRule -> ApplicationVersionLifecycleConfig

-- | Specify a max count rule to restrict the number of application
--   versions that are retained for an application.
[$sel:maxCountRule:ApplicationVersionLifecycleConfig'] :: ApplicationVersionLifecycleConfig -> Maybe MaxCountRule

-- | Specify a max age rule to restrict the length of time that application
--   versions are retained for an application.
[$sel:maxAgeRule:ApplicationVersionLifecycleConfig'] :: ApplicationVersionLifecycleConfig -> Maybe MaxAgeRule

-- | Create a value of <a>ApplicationVersionLifecycleConfig</a> with all
--   optional fields omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:maxCountRule:ApplicationVersionLifecycleConfig'</a>,
--   <a>applicationVersionLifecycleConfig_maxCountRule</a> - Specify a max
--   count rule to restrict the number of application versions that are
--   retained for an application.
--   
--   <a>$sel:maxAgeRule:ApplicationVersionLifecycleConfig'</a>,
--   <a>applicationVersionLifecycleConfig_maxAgeRule</a> - Specify a max
--   age rule to restrict the length of time that application versions are
--   retained for an application.
newApplicationVersionLifecycleConfig :: ApplicationVersionLifecycleConfig

-- | Specify a max count rule to restrict the number of application
--   versions that are retained for an application.
applicationVersionLifecycleConfig_maxCountRule :: Lens' ApplicationVersionLifecycleConfig (Maybe MaxCountRule)

-- | Specify a max age rule to restrict the length of time that application
--   versions are retained for an application.
applicationVersionLifecycleConfig_maxAgeRule :: Lens' ApplicationVersionLifecycleConfig (Maybe MaxAgeRule)
instance GHC.Generics.Generic Network.AWS.ElasticBeanstalk.Types.ApplicationVersionLifecycleConfig.ApplicationVersionLifecycleConfig
instance GHC.Show.Show Network.AWS.ElasticBeanstalk.Types.ApplicationVersionLifecycleConfig.ApplicationVersionLifecycleConfig
instance GHC.Read.Read Network.AWS.ElasticBeanstalk.Types.ApplicationVersionLifecycleConfig.ApplicationVersionLifecycleConfig
instance GHC.Classes.Eq Network.AWS.ElasticBeanstalk.Types.ApplicationVersionLifecycleConfig.ApplicationVersionLifecycleConfig
instance Network.AWS.Data.XML.FromXML Network.AWS.ElasticBeanstalk.Types.ApplicationVersionLifecycleConfig.ApplicationVersionLifecycleConfig
instance Data.Hashable.Class.Hashable Network.AWS.ElasticBeanstalk.Types.ApplicationVersionLifecycleConfig.ApplicationVersionLifecycleConfig
instance Control.DeepSeq.NFData Network.AWS.ElasticBeanstalk.Types.ApplicationVersionLifecycleConfig.ApplicationVersionLifecycleConfig
instance Network.AWS.Data.Query.ToQuery Network.AWS.ElasticBeanstalk.Types.ApplicationVersionLifecycleConfig.ApplicationVersionLifecycleConfig


module Network.AWS.ElasticBeanstalk.Types.ApplicationResourceLifecycleConfig

-- | The resource lifecycle configuration for an application. Defines
--   lifecycle settings for resources that belong to the application, and
--   the service role that AWS Elastic Beanstalk assumes in order to apply
--   lifecycle settings. The version lifecycle configuration defines
--   lifecycle settings for application versions.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newApplicationResourceLifecycleConfig</a> smart
--   constructor.
data ApplicationResourceLifecycleConfig
ApplicationResourceLifecycleConfig' :: Maybe Text -> Maybe ApplicationVersionLifecycleConfig -> ApplicationResourceLifecycleConfig

-- | The ARN of an IAM service role that Elastic Beanstalk has permission
--   to assume.
--   
--   The <tt>ServiceRole</tt> property is required the first time that you
--   provide a <tt>VersionLifecycleConfig</tt> for the application in one
--   of the supporting calls (<tt>CreateApplication</tt> or
--   <tt>UpdateApplicationResourceLifecycle</tt>). After you provide it
--   once, in either one of the calls, Elastic Beanstalk persists the
--   Service Role with the application, and you don't need to specify it
--   again in subsequent <tt>UpdateApplicationResourceLifecycle</tt> calls.
--   You can, however, specify it in subsequent calls to change the Service
--   Role to another value.
[$sel:serviceRole:ApplicationResourceLifecycleConfig'] :: ApplicationResourceLifecycleConfig -> Maybe Text

-- | Defines lifecycle settings for application versions.
[$sel:versionLifecycleConfig:ApplicationResourceLifecycleConfig'] :: ApplicationResourceLifecycleConfig -> Maybe ApplicationVersionLifecycleConfig

-- | Create a value of <a>ApplicationResourceLifecycleConfig</a> with all
--   optional fields omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:serviceRole:ApplicationResourceLifecycleConfig'</a>,
--   <a>applicationResourceLifecycleConfig_serviceRole</a> - The ARN of an
--   IAM service role that Elastic Beanstalk has permission to assume.
--   
--   The <tt>ServiceRole</tt> property is required the first time that you
--   provide a <tt>VersionLifecycleConfig</tt> for the application in one
--   of the supporting calls (<tt>CreateApplication</tt> or
--   <tt>UpdateApplicationResourceLifecycle</tt>). After you provide it
--   once, in either one of the calls, Elastic Beanstalk persists the
--   Service Role with the application, and you don't need to specify it
--   again in subsequent <tt>UpdateApplicationResourceLifecycle</tt> calls.
--   You can, however, specify it in subsequent calls to change the Service
--   Role to another value.
--   
--   
--   <a>$sel:versionLifecycleConfig:ApplicationResourceLifecycleConfig'</a>,
--   <a>applicationResourceLifecycleConfig_versionLifecycleConfig</a> -
--   Defines lifecycle settings for application versions.
newApplicationResourceLifecycleConfig :: ApplicationResourceLifecycleConfig

-- | The ARN of an IAM service role that Elastic Beanstalk has permission
--   to assume.
--   
--   The <tt>ServiceRole</tt> property is required the first time that you
--   provide a <tt>VersionLifecycleConfig</tt> for the application in one
--   of the supporting calls (<tt>CreateApplication</tt> or
--   <tt>UpdateApplicationResourceLifecycle</tt>). After you provide it
--   once, in either one of the calls, Elastic Beanstalk persists the
--   Service Role with the application, and you don't need to specify it
--   again in subsequent <tt>UpdateApplicationResourceLifecycle</tt> calls.
--   You can, however, specify it in subsequent calls to change the Service
--   Role to another value.
applicationResourceLifecycleConfig_serviceRole :: Lens' ApplicationResourceLifecycleConfig (Maybe Text)

-- | Defines lifecycle settings for application versions.
applicationResourceLifecycleConfig_versionLifecycleConfig :: Lens' ApplicationResourceLifecycleConfig (Maybe ApplicationVersionLifecycleConfig)
instance GHC.Generics.Generic Network.AWS.ElasticBeanstalk.Types.ApplicationResourceLifecycleConfig.ApplicationResourceLifecycleConfig
instance GHC.Show.Show Network.AWS.ElasticBeanstalk.Types.ApplicationResourceLifecycleConfig.ApplicationResourceLifecycleConfig
instance GHC.Read.Read Network.AWS.ElasticBeanstalk.Types.ApplicationResourceLifecycleConfig.ApplicationResourceLifecycleConfig
instance GHC.Classes.Eq Network.AWS.ElasticBeanstalk.Types.ApplicationResourceLifecycleConfig.ApplicationResourceLifecycleConfig
instance Network.AWS.Data.XML.FromXML Network.AWS.ElasticBeanstalk.Types.ApplicationResourceLifecycleConfig.ApplicationResourceLifecycleConfig
instance Data.Hashable.Class.Hashable Network.AWS.ElasticBeanstalk.Types.ApplicationResourceLifecycleConfig.ApplicationResourceLifecycleConfig
instance Control.DeepSeq.NFData Network.AWS.ElasticBeanstalk.Types.ApplicationResourceLifecycleConfig.ApplicationResourceLifecycleConfig
instance Network.AWS.Data.Query.ToQuery Network.AWS.ElasticBeanstalk.Types.ApplicationResourceLifecycleConfig.ApplicationResourceLifecycleConfig

module Network.AWS.ElasticBeanstalk.Types.ConfigurationOptionDescription

-- | Describes the possible values for a configuration option.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newConfigurationOptionDescription</a> smart
--   constructor.
data ConfigurationOptionDescription
ConfigurationOptionDescription' :: Maybe Int -> Maybe [Text] -> Maybe ConfigurationOptionValueType -> Maybe Text -> Maybe OptionRestrictionRegex -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Int -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Int -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Bool -> ConfigurationOptionDescription

-- | If specified, the configuration option must be a numeric value less
--   than this value.
[$sel:maxValue:ConfigurationOptionDescription'] :: ConfigurationOptionDescription -> Maybe Int

-- | If specified, values for the configuration option are selected from
--   this list.
[$sel:valueOptions:ConfigurationOptionDescription'] :: ConfigurationOptionDescription -> Maybe [Text]

-- | An indication of which type of values this option has and whether it
--   is allowable to select one or more than one of the possible values:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li><tt>Scalar</tt> : Values for this option are a single selection
--   from the possible values, or an unformatted string, or numeric value
--   governed by the <tt>MIN/MAX/Regex</tt> constraints.</li>
--   <li><tt>List</tt> : Values for this option are multiple selections
--   from the possible values.</li>
--   <li><tt>Boolean</tt> : Values for this option are either <tt>true</tt>
--   or <tt>false</tt> .</li>
--   <li><tt>Json</tt> : Values for this option are a JSON representation
--   of a <tt>ConfigDocument</tt>.</li>
--   </ul>
[$sel:valueType:ConfigurationOptionDescription'] :: ConfigurationOptionDescription -> Maybe ConfigurationOptionValueType

-- | An indication of which action is required if the value for this
--   configuration option changes:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li><tt>NoInterruption</tt> : There is no interruption to the
--   environment or application availability.</li>
--   <li><tt>RestartEnvironment</tt> : The environment is entirely
--   restarted, all AWS resources are deleted and recreated, and the
--   environment is unavailable during the process.</li>
--   <li><tt>RestartApplicationServer</tt> : The environment is available
--   the entire time. However, a short application outage occurs when the
--   application servers on the running Amazon EC2 instances are
--   restarted.</li>
--   </ul>
[$sel:changeSeverity:ConfigurationOptionDescription'] :: ConfigurationOptionDescription -> Maybe Text

-- | If specified, the configuration option must be a string value that
--   satisfies this regular expression.
[$sel:regex:ConfigurationOptionDescription'] :: ConfigurationOptionDescription -> Maybe OptionRestrictionRegex

-- | The name of the configuration option.
[$sel:name:ConfigurationOptionDescription'] :: ConfigurationOptionDescription -> Maybe Text

-- | If specified, the configuration option must be a numeric value greater
--   than this value.
[$sel:minValue:ConfigurationOptionDescription'] :: ConfigurationOptionDescription -> Maybe Int

-- | A unique namespace identifying the option's associated AWS resource.
[$sel:namespace:ConfigurationOptionDescription'] :: ConfigurationOptionDescription -> Maybe Text

-- | If specified, the configuration option must be a string value no
--   longer than this value.
[$sel:maxLength:ConfigurationOptionDescription'] :: ConfigurationOptionDescription -> Maybe Int

-- | The default value for this configuration option.
[$sel:defaultValue:ConfigurationOptionDescription'] :: ConfigurationOptionDescription -> Maybe Text

-- | An indication of whether the user defined this configuration option:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li><tt>true</tt> : This configuration option was defined by the user.
--   It is a valid choice for specifying if this as an <tt>Option to
--   Remove</tt> when updating configuration settings.</li>
--   <li><tt>false</tt> : This configuration was not defined by the
--   user.</li>
--   </ul>
--   
--   Constraint: You can remove only <tt>UserDefined</tt> options from a
--   configuration.
--   
--   Valid Values: <tt>true</tt> | <tt>false</tt>
[$sel:userDefined:ConfigurationOptionDescription'] :: ConfigurationOptionDescription -> Maybe Bool

-- | Create a value of <a>ConfigurationOptionDescription</a> with all
--   optional fields omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:maxValue:ConfigurationOptionDescription'</a>,
--   <a>configurationOptionDescription_maxValue</a> - If specified, the
--   configuration option must be a numeric value less than this value.
--   
--   <a>$sel:valueOptions:ConfigurationOptionDescription'</a>,
--   <a>configurationOptionDescription_valueOptions</a> - If specified,
--   values for the configuration option are selected from this list.
--   
--   <a>$sel:valueType:ConfigurationOptionDescription'</a>,
--   <a>configurationOptionDescription_valueType</a> - An indication of
--   which type of values this option has and whether it is allowable to
--   select one or more than one of the possible values:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li><tt>Scalar</tt> : Values for this option are a single selection
--   from the possible values, or an unformatted string, or numeric value
--   governed by the <tt>MIN/MAX/Regex</tt> constraints.</li>
--   <li><tt>List</tt> : Values for this option are multiple selections
--   from the possible values.</li>
--   <li><tt>Boolean</tt> : Values for this option are either <tt>true</tt>
--   or <tt>false</tt> .</li>
--   <li><tt>Json</tt> : Values for this option are a JSON representation
--   of a <tt>ConfigDocument</tt>.</li>
--   </ul>
--   
--   <a>$sel:changeSeverity:ConfigurationOptionDescription'</a>,
--   <a>configurationOptionDescription_changeSeverity</a> - An indication
--   of which action is required if the value for this configuration option
--   changes:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li><tt>NoInterruption</tt> : There is no interruption to the
--   environment or application availability.</li>
--   <li><tt>RestartEnvironment</tt> : The environment is entirely
--   restarted, all AWS resources are deleted and recreated, and the
--   environment is unavailable during the process.</li>
--   <li><tt>RestartApplicationServer</tt> : The environment is available
--   the entire time. However, a short application outage occurs when the
--   application servers on the running Amazon EC2 instances are
--   restarted.</li>
--   </ul>
--   
--   <a>$sel:regex:ConfigurationOptionDescription'</a>,
--   <a>configurationOptionDescription_regex</a> - If specified, the
--   configuration option must be a string value that satisfies this
--   regular expression.
--   
--   <a>$sel:name:ConfigurationOptionDescription'</a>,
--   <a>configurationOptionDescription_name</a> - The name of the
--   configuration option.
--   
--   <a>$sel:minValue:ConfigurationOptionDescription'</a>,
--   <a>configurationOptionDescription_minValue</a> - If specified, the
--   configuration option must be a numeric value greater than this value.
--   
--   <a>$sel:namespace:ConfigurationOptionDescription'</a>,
--   <a>configurationOptionDescription_namespace</a> - A unique namespace
--   identifying the option's associated AWS resource.
--   
--   <a>$sel:maxLength:ConfigurationOptionDescription'</a>,
--   <a>configurationOptionDescription_maxLength</a> - If specified, the
--   configuration option must be a string value no longer than this value.
--   
--   <a>$sel:defaultValue:ConfigurationOptionDescription'</a>,
--   <a>configurationOptionDescription_defaultValue</a> - The default value
--   for this configuration option.
--   
--   <a>$sel:userDefined:ConfigurationOptionDescription'</a>,
--   <a>configurationOptionDescription_userDefined</a> - An indication of
--   whether the user defined this configuration option:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li><tt>true</tt> : This configuration option was defined by the user.
--   It is a valid choice for specifying if this as an <tt>Option to
--   Remove</tt> when updating configuration settings.</li>
--   <li><tt>false</tt> : This configuration was not defined by the
--   user.</li>
--   </ul>
--   
--   Constraint: You can remove only <tt>UserDefined</tt> options from a
--   configuration.
--   
--   Valid Values: <tt>true</tt> | <tt>false</tt>
newConfigurationOptionDescription :: ConfigurationOptionDescription

-- | If specified, the configuration option must be a numeric value less
--   than this value.
configurationOptionDescription_maxValue :: Lens' ConfigurationOptionDescription (Maybe Int)

-- | If specified, values for the configuration option are selected from
--   this list.
configurationOptionDescription_valueOptions :: Lens' ConfigurationOptionDescription (Maybe [Text])

-- | An indication of which type of values this option has and whether it
--   is allowable to select one or more than one of the possible values:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li><tt>Scalar</tt> : Values for this option are a single selection
--   from the possible values, or an unformatted string, or numeric value
--   governed by the <tt>MIN/MAX/Regex</tt> constraints.</li>
--   <li><tt>List</tt> : Values for this option are multiple selections
--   from the possible values.</li>
--   <li><tt>Boolean</tt> : Values for this option are either <tt>true</tt>
--   or <tt>false</tt> .</li>
--   <li><tt>Json</tt> : Values for this option are a JSON representation
--   of a <tt>ConfigDocument</tt>.</li>
--   </ul>
configurationOptionDescription_valueType :: Lens' ConfigurationOptionDescription (Maybe ConfigurationOptionValueType)

-- | An indication of which action is required if the value for this
--   configuration option changes:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li><tt>NoInterruption</tt> : There is no interruption to the
--   environment or application availability.</li>
--   <li><tt>RestartEnvironment</tt> : The environment is entirely
--   restarted, all AWS resources are deleted and recreated, and the
--   environment is unavailable during the process.</li>
--   <li><tt>RestartApplicationServer</tt> : The environment is available
--   the entire time. However, a short application outage occurs when the
--   application servers on the running Amazon EC2 instances are
--   restarted.</li>
--   </ul>
configurationOptionDescription_changeSeverity :: Lens' ConfigurationOptionDescription (Maybe Text)

-- | If specified, the configuration option must be a string value that
--   satisfies this regular expression.
configurationOptionDescription_regex :: Lens' ConfigurationOptionDescription (Maybe OptionRestrictionRegex)

-- | The name of the configuration option.
configurationOptionDescription_name :: Lens' ConfigurationOptionDescription (Maybe Text)

-- | If specified, the configuration option must be a numeric value greater
--   than this value.
configurationOptionDescription_minValue :: Lens' ConfigurationOptionDescription (Maybe Int)

-- | A unique namespace identifying the option's associated AWS resource.
configurationOptionDescription_namespace :: Lens' ConfigurationOptionDescription (Maybe Text)

-- | If specified, the configuration option must be a string value no
--   longer than this value.
configurationOptionDescription_maxLength :: Lens' ConfigurationOptionDescription (Maybe Int)

-- | The default value for this configuration option.
configurationOptionDescription_defaultValue :: Lens' ConfigurationOptionDescription (Maybe Text)

-- | An indication of whether the user defined this configuration option:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li><tt>true</tt> : This configuration option was defined by the user.
--   It is a valid choice for specifying if this as an <tt>Option to
--   Remove</tt> when updating configuration settings.</li>
--   <li><tt>false</tt> : This configuration was not defined by the
--   user.</li>
--   </ul>
--   
--   Constraint: You can remove only <tt>UserDefined</tt> options from a
--   configuration.
--   
--   Valid Values: <tt>true</tt> | <tt>false</tt>
configurationOptionDescription_userDefined :: Lens' ConfigurationOptionDescription (Maybe Bool)
instance GHC.Generics.Generic Network.AWS.ElasticBeanstalk.Types.ConfigurationOptionDescription.ConfigurationOptionDescription
instance GHC.Show.Show Network.AWS.ElasticBeanstalk.Types.ConfigurationOptionDescription.ConfigurationOptionDescription
instance GHC.Read.Read Network.AWS.ElasticBeanstalk.Types.ConfigurationOptionDescription.ConfigurationOptionDescription
instance GHC.Classes.Eq Network.AWS.ElasticBeanstalk.Types.ConfigurationOptionDescription.ConfigurationOptionDescription
instance Network.AWS.Data.XML.FromXML Network.AWS.ElasticBeanstalk.Types.ConfigurationOptionDescription.ConfigurationOptionDescription
instance Data.Hashable.Class.Hashable Network.AWS.ElasticBeanstalk.Types.ConfigurationOptionDescription.ConfigurationOptionDescription
instance Control.DeepSeq.NFData Network.AWS.ElasticBeanstalk.Types.ConfigurationOptionDescription.ConfigurationOptionDescription
