module Network.AWS.ElasticBeanstalk.Types.PlatformBranchSummary

-- | Summary information about a platform branch.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newPlatformBranchSummary</a> smart constructor.
data PlatformBranchSummary
PlatformBranchSummary' :: Maybe Text -> Maybe Int -> Maybe Text -> Maybe [Text] -> Maybe Text -> PlatformBranchSummary

-- | The name of the platform branch.
[$sel:branchName:PlatformBranchSummary'] :: PlatformBranchSummary -> Maybe Text

-- | An ordinal number that designates the order in which platform branches
--   have been added to a platform. This can be helpful, for example, if
--   your code calls the <tt>ListPlatformBranches</tt> action and then
--   displays a list of platform branches.
--   
--   A larger <tt>BranchOrder</tt> value designates a newer platform branch
--   within the platform.
[$sel:branchOrder:PlatformBranchSummary'] :: PlatformBranchSummary -> Maybe Int

-- | The support life cycle state of the platform branch.
--   
--   Possible values: <tt>beta</tt> | <tt>supported</tt> |
--   <tt>deprecated</tt> | <tt>retired</tt>
[$sel:lifecycleState:PlatformBranchSummary'] :: PlatformBranchSummary -> Maybe Text

-- | The environment tiers that platform versions in this branch support.
--   
--   Possible values: <tt>WebServer/Standard</tt> |
--   <tt>Worker/SQS/HTTP</tt>
[$sel:supportedTierList:PlatformBranchSummary'] :: PlatformBranchSummary -> Maybe [Text]

-- | The name of the platform to which this platform branch belongs.
[$sel:platformName:PlatformBranchSummary'] :: PlatformBranchSummary -> Maybe Text

-- | Create a value of <a>PlatformBranchSummary</a> with all optional
--   fields omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:branchName:PlatformBranchSummary'</a>,
--   <a>platformBranchSummary_branchName</a> - The name of the platform
--   branch.
--   
--   <a>$sel:branchOrder:PlatformBranchSummary'</a>,
--   <a>platformBranchSummary_branchOrder</a> - An ordinal number that
--   designates the order in which platform branches have been added to a
--   platform. This can be helpful, for example, if your code calls the
--   <tt>ListPlatformBranches</tt> action and then displays a list of
--   platform branches.
--   
--   A larger <tt>BranchOrder</tt> value designates a newer platform branch
--   within the platform.
--   
--   <a>$sel:lifecycleState:PlatformBranchSummary'</a>,
--   <a>platformBranchSummary_lifecycleState</a> - The support life cycle
--   state of the platform branch.
--   
--   Possible values: <tt>beta</tt> | <tt>supported</tt> |
--   <tt>deprecated</tt> | <tt>retired</tt>
--   
--   <a>$sel:supportedTierList:PlatformBranchSummary'</a>,
--   <a>platformBranchSummary_supportedTierList</a> - The environment tiers
--   that platform versions in this branch support.
--   
--   Possible values: <tt>WebServer/Standard</tt> |
--   <tt>Worker/SQS/HTTP</tt>
--   
--   <a>$sel:platformName:PlatformBranchSummary'</a>,
--   <a>platformBranchSummary_platformName</a> - The name of the platform
--   to which this platform branch belongs.
newPlatformBranchSummary :: PlatformBranchSummary

-- | The name of the platform branch.
platformBranchSummary_branchName :: Lens' PlatformBranchSummary (Maybe Text)

-- | An ordinal number that designates the order in which platform branches
--   have been added to a platform. This can be helpful, for example, if
--   your code calls the <tt>ListPlatformBranches</tt> action and then
--   displays a list of platform branches.
--   
--   A larger <tt>BranchOrder</tt> value designates a newer platform branch
--   within the platform.
platformBranchSummary_branchOrder :: Lens' PlatformBranchSummary (Maybe Int)

-- | The support life cycle state of the platform branch.
--   
--   Possible values: <tt>beta</tt> | <tt>supported</tt> |
--   <tt>deprecated</tt> | <tt>retired</tt>
platformBranchSummary_lifecycleState :: Lens' PlatformBranchSummary (Maybe Text)

-- | The environment tiers that platform versions in this branch support.
--   
--   Possible values: <tt>WebServer/Standard</tt> |
--   <tt>Worker/SQS/HTTP</tt>
platformBranchSummary_supportedTierList :: Lens' PlatformBranchSummary (Maybe [Text])

-- | The name of the platform to which this platform branch belongs.
platformBranchSummary_platformName :: Lens' PlatformBranchSummary (Maybe Text)
instance GHC.Generics.Generic Network.AWS.ElasticBeanstalk.Types.PlatformBranchSummary.PlatformBranchSummary
instance GHC.Show.Show Network.AWS.ElasticBeanstalk.Types.PlatformBranchSummary.PlatformBranchSummary
instance GHC.Read.Read Network.AWS.ElasticBeanstalk.Types.PlatformBranchSummary.PlatformBranchSummary
instance GHC.Classes.Eq Network.AWS.ElasticBeanstalk.Types.PlatformBranchSummary.PlatformBranchSummary

instance Control.DeepSeq.NFData Network.AWS.ElasticBeanstalk.Types.PlatformBranchSummary.PlatformBranchSummary


module Network.AWS.ElasticBeanstalk.Types.PlatformFilter

-- | Describes criteria to restrict the results when listing platform
--   versions.
--   
--   The filter is evaluated as follows: <tt>Type Operator Values[1]</tt>
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newPlatformFilter</a> smart constructor.
data PlatformFilter
PlatformFilter' :: Maybe [Text] -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> PlatformFilter

-- | The list of values applied to the filtering platform version
--   attribute. Only one value is supported for all current operators.
--   
--   The following list shows valid filter values for some filter
--   attributes.
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li><tt>PlatformStatus</tt>: <tt>Creating</tt> | <tt>Failed</tt> |
--   <tt>Ready</tt> | <tt>Deleting</tt> | <tt>Deleted</tt></li>
--   <li><tt>PlatformLifecycleState</tt>: <tt>recommended</tt></li>
--   <li><tt>SupportedTier</tt>: <tt>WebServer/Standard</tt> |
--   <tt>Worker/SQS/HTTP</tt></li>
--   <li><tt>SupportedAddon</tt>: <tt>Log/S3</tt> |
--   <tt>Monitoring/Healthd</tt> | <tt>WorkerDaemon/SQSD</tt></li>
--   </ul>
[$sel:values:PlatformFilter'] :: PlatformFilter -> Maybe [Text]

-- | The operator to apply to the <tt>Type</tt> with each of the
--   <tt>Values</tt>.
--   
--   Valid values: <tt>=</tt> | <tt>!=</tt> | <tt>&lt;</tt> |
--   <tt>&lt;=</tt> | <tt>&gt;</tt> | <tt>&gt;=</tt> | <tt>contains</tt> |
--   <tt>begins_with</tt> | <tt>ends_with</tt>
[$sel:operator:PlatformFilter'] :: PlatformFilter -> Maybe Text

-- | The platform version attribute to which the filter values are applied.
--   
--   Valid values: <tt>PlatformName</tt> | <tt>PlatformVersion</tt> |
--   <tt>PlatformStatus</tt> | <tt>PlatformBranchName</tt> |
--   <tt>PlatformLifecycleState</tt> | <tt>PlatformOwner</tt> |
--   <tt>SupportedTier</tt> | <tt>SupportedAddon</tt> |
--   <tt>ProgrammingLanguageName</tt> | <tt>OperatingSystemName</tt>
[$sel:type':PlatformFilter'] :: PlatformFilter -> Maybe Text

-- | Create a value of <a>PlatformFilter</a> with all optional fields
--   omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:values:PlatformFilter'</a>, <a>platformFilter_values</a> - The
--   list of values applied to the filtering platform version attribute.
--   Only one value is supported for all current operators.
--   
--   The following list shows valid filter values for some filter
--   attributes.
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li><tt>PlatformStatus</tt>: <tt>Creating</tt> | <tt>Failed</tt> |
--   <tt>Ready</tt> | <tt>Deleting</tt> | <tt>Deleted</tt></li>
--   <li><tt>PlatformLifecycleState</tt>: <tt>recommended</tt></li>
--   <li><tt>SupportedTier</tt>: <tt>WebServer/Standard</tt> |
--   <tt>Worker/SQS/HTTP</tt></li>
--   <li><tt>SupportedAddon</tt>: <tt>Log/S3</tt> |
--   <tt>Monitoring/Healthd</tt> | <tt>WorkerDaemon/SQSD</tt></li>
--   </ul>
--   
--   <a>$sel:operator:PlatformFilter'</a>, <a>platformFilter_operator</a> -
--   The operator to apply to the <tt>Type</tt> with each of the
--   <tt>Values</tt>.
--   
--   Valid values: <tt>=</tt> | <tt>!=</tt> | <tt>&lt;</tt> |
--   <tt>&lt;=</tt> | <tt>&gt;</tt> | <tt>&gt;=</tt> | <tt>contains</tt> |
--   <tt>begins_with</tt> | <tt>ends_with</tt>
--   
--   <a>$sel:type':PlatformFilter'</a>, <a>platformFilter_type</a> - The
--   platform version attribute to which the filter values are applied.
--   
--   Valid values: <tt>PlatformName</tt> | <tt>PlatformVersion</tt> |
--   <tt>PlatformStatus</tt> | <tt>PlatformBranchName</tt> |
--   <tt>PlatformLifecycleState</tt> | <tt>PlatformOwner</tt> |
--   <tt>SupportedTier</tt> | <tt>SupportedAddon</tt> |
--   <tt>ProgrammingLanguageName</tt> | <tt>OperatingSystemName</tt>
newPlatformFilter :: PlatformFilter

-- | The list of values applied to the filtering platform version
--   attribute. Only one value is supported for all current operators.
--   
--   The following list shows valid filter values for some filter
--   attributes.
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li><tt>PlatformStatus</tt>: <tt>Creating</tt> | <tt>Failed</tt> |
--   <tt>Ready</tt> | <tt>Deleting</tt> | <tt>Deleted</tt></li>
--   <li><tt>PlatformLifecycleState</tt>: <tt>recommended</tt></li>
--   <li><tt>SupportedTier</tt>: <tt>WebServer/Standard</tt> |
--   <tt>Worker/SQS/HTTP</tt></li>
--   <li><tt>SupportedAddon</tt>: <tt>Log/S3</tt> |
--   <tt>Monitoring/Healthd</tt> | <tt>WorkerDaemon/SQSD</tt></li>
--   </ul>
platformFilter_values :: Lens' PlatformFilter (Maybe [Text])

-- | The operator to apply to the <tt>Type</tt> with each of the
--   <tt>Values</tt>.
--   
--   Valid values: <tt>=</tt> | <tt>!=</tt> | <tt>&lt;</tt> |
--   <tt>&lt;=</tt> | <tt>&gt;</tt> | <tt>&gt;=</tt> | <tt>contains</tt> |
--   <tt>begins_with</tt> | <tt>ends_with</tt>
platformFilter_operator :: Lens' PlatformFilter (Maybe Text)

-- | The platform version attribute to which the filter values are applied.
--   
--   Valid values: <tt>PlatformName</tt> | <tt>PlatformVersion</tt> |
--   <tt>PlatformStatus</tt> | <tt>PlatformBranchName</tt> |
--   <tt>PlatformLifecycleState</tt> | <tt>PlatformOwner</tt> |
--   <tt>SupportedTier</tt> | <tt>SupportedAddon</tt> |
--   <tt>ProgrammingLanguageName</tt> | <tt>OperatingSystemName</tt>
platformFilter_type :: Lens' PlatformFilter (Maybe Text)
instance GHC.Generics.Generic Network.AWS.ElasticBeanstalk.Types.PlatformFilter.PlatformFilter
instance GHC.Show.Show Network.AWS.ElasticBeanstalk.Types.PlatformFilter.PlatformFilter
instance GHC.Read.Read Network.AWS.ElasticBeanstalk.Types.PlatformFilter.PlatformFilter
instance GHC.Classes.Eq Network.AWS.ElasticBeanstalk.Types.PlatformFilter.PlatformFilter
instance Data.Hashable.Class.Hashable Network.AWS.ElasticBeanstalk.Types.PlatformFilter.PlatformFilter
instance Control.DeepSeq.NFData Network.AWS.ElasticBeanstalk.Types.PlatformFilter.PlatformFilter
instance Network.AWS.Data.Query.ToQuery Network.AWS.ElasticBeanstalk.Types.PlatformFilter.PlatformFilter

module Network.AWS.ElasticBeanstalk.Types.PlatformDescription

-- | Detailed information about a platform version.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newPlatformDescription</a> smart constructor.
data PlatformDescription
PlatformDescription' :: Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe [CustomAmi] -> Maybe [Text] -> Maybe ISO8601 -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe PlatformStatus -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe [PlatformFramework] -> Maybe ISO8601 -> Maybe [Text] -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe [PlatformProgrammingLanguage] -> Maybe Text -> PlatformDescription

-- | The operating system used by the platform version.
[$sel:operatingSystemName:PlatformDescription'] :: PlatformDescription -> Maybe Text

-- | The category of the platform version.
[$sel:platformCategory:PlatformDescription'] :: PlatformDescription -> Maybe Text

-- | The custom AMIs supported by the platform version.
[$sel:customAmiList:PlatformDescription'] :: PlatformDescription -> Maybe [CustomAmi]

-- | The additions supported by the platform version.
[$sel:supportedAddonList:PlatformDescription'] :: PlatformDescription -> Maybe [Text]

-- | The date when the platform version was created.
[$sel:dateCreated:PlatformDescription'] :: PlatformDescription -> Maybe ISO8601

-- | The platform branch to which the platform version belongs.
[$sel:platformBranchName:PlatformDescription'] :: PlatformDescription -> Maybe Text

-- | The AWS account ID of the person who created the platform version.
[$sel:platformOwner:PlatformDescription'] :: PlatformDescription -> Maybe Text

-- | The status of the platform version.
[$sel:platformStatus:PlatformDescription'] :: PlatformDescription -> Maybe PlatformStatus

-- | The name of the solution stack used by the platform version.
[$sel:solutionStackName:PlatformDescription'] :: PlatformDescription -> Maybe Text

-- | The version of the platform version.
[$sel:platformVersion:PlatformDescription'] :: PlatformDescription -> Maybe Text

-- | The ARN of the platform version.
[$sel:platformArn:PlatformDescription'] :: PlatformDescription -> Maybe Text

-- | The state of the platform version's branch in its lifecycle.
--   
--   Possible values: <tt>Beta</tt> | <tt>Supported</tt> |
--   <tt>Deprecated</tt> | <tt>Retired</tt>
[$sel:platformBranchLifecycleState:PlatformDescription'] :: PlatformDescription -> Maybe Text

-- | The frameworks supported by the platform version.
[$sel:frameworks:PlatformDescription'] :: PlatformDescription -> Maybe [PlatformFramework]

-- | The date when the platform version was last updated.
[$sel:dateUpdated:PlatformDescription'] :: PlatformDescription -> Maybe ISO8601

-- | The tiers supported by the platform version.
[$sel:supportedTierList:PlatformDescription'] :: PlatformDescription -> Maybe [Text]

-- | Information about the maintainer of the platform version.
[$sel:maintainer:PlatformDescription'] :: PlatformDescription -> Maybe Text

-- | The description of the platform version.
[$sel:description:PlatformDescription'] :: PlatformDescription -> Maybe Text

-- | The state of the platform version in its lifecycle.
--   
--   Possible values: <tt>Recommended</tt> | <tt>null</tt>
--   
--   If a null value is returned, the platform version isn't the
--   recommended one for its branch. Each platform branch has a single
--   recommended platform version, typically the most recent one.
[$sel:platformLifecycleState:PlatformDescription'] :: PlatformDescription -> Maybe Text

-- | The name of the platform version.
[$sel:platformName:PlatformDescription'] :: PlatformDescription -> Maybe Text

-- | The programming languages supported by the platform version.
[$sel:programmingLanguages:PlatformDescription'] :: PlatformDescription -> Maybe [PlatformProgrammingLanguage]

-- | The version of the operating system used by the platform version.
[$sel:operatingSystemVersion:PlatformDescription'] :: PlatformDescription -> Maybe Text

--   omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.

module Network.AWS.ElasticBeanstalk.Types.PlatformSummary

-- | Summary information about a platform version.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newPlatformSummary</a> smart constructor.
data PlatformSummary
PlatformSummary' :: Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe [Text] -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe PlatformStatus -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe [Text] -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> PlatformSummary

-- | The operating system used by the platform version.
[$sel:operatingSystemName:PlatformSummary'] :: PlatformSummary -> Maybe Text

-- | The category of platform version.
[$sel:platformCategory:PlatformSummary'] :: PlatformSummary -> Maybe Text

-- | The additions associated with the platform version.
[$sel:supportedAddonList:PlatformSummary'] :: PlatformSummary -> Maybe [Text]

-- | The platform branch to which the platform version belongs.
[$sel:platformBranchName:PlatformSummary'] :: PlatformSummary -> Maybe Text

-- | The AWS account ID of the person who created the platform version.
[$sel:platformOwner:PlatformSummary'] :: PlatformSummary -> Maybe Text

-- | The status of the platform version. You can create an environment from
--   the platform version once it is ready.
[$sel:platformStatus:PlatformSummary'] :: PlatformSummary -> Maybe PlatformStatus

-- | The version string of the platform version.
[$sel:platformVersion:PlatformSummary'] :: PlatformSummary -> Maybe Text

-- | The ARN of the platform version.
[$sel:platformArn:PlatformSummary'] :: PlatformSummary -> Maybe Text

-- | The state of the platform version's branch in its lifecycle.
--   
--   Possible values: <tt>beta</tt> | <tt>supported</tt> |
--   <tt>deprecated</tt> | <tt>retired</tt>
[$sel:platformBranchLifecycleState:PlatformSummary'] :: PlatformSummary -> Maybe Text

-- | The tiers in which the platform version runs.
[$sel:supportedTierList:PlatformSummary'] :: PlatformSummary -> Maybe [Text]

-- | The state of the platform version in its lifecycle.
--   
--   Possible values: <tt>recommended</tt> | empty
--   
--   If an empty value is returned, the platform version is supported but
--   isn't the recommended one for its branch.
[$sel:platformLifecycleState:PlatformSummary'] :: PlatformSummary -> Maybe Text

-- | The version of the operating system used by the platform version.
[$sel:operatingSystemVersion:PlatformSummary'] :: PlatformSummary -> Maybe Text

-- | Create a value of <a>PlatformSummary</a> with all optional fields
--   omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:operatingSystemName:PlatformSummary'</a>,
--   <a>platformSummary_operatingSystemName</a> - The operating system used
--   by the platform version.
--   
--   <a>$sel:platformCategory:PlatformSummary'</a>,
--   <a>platformSummary_platformCategory</a> - The category of platform
--   version.
--   
--   <a>$sel:supportedAddonList:PlatformSummary'</a>,
--   <a>platformSummary_supportedAddonList</a> - The additions associated
--   with the platform version.
--   
--   <a>$sel:platformBranchName:PlatformSummary'</a>,
--   <a>platformSummary_platformBranchName</a> - The platform branch to
--   which the platform version belongs.
--   
--   <a>$sel:platformOwner:PlatformSummary'</a>,

--   person who created the platform version.
--

--   <a>platformSummary_platformStatus</a> - The status of the platform

--   it is ready.
--

--   <a>platformSummary_platformVersion</a> - The version string of the

--

module Network.AWS.ElasticBeanstalk.Types.ResourceQuota

-- | The AWS Elastic Beanstalk quota information for a single resource type
--   in an AWS account. It reflects the resource's limits for this account.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newResourceQuota</a> smart constructor.
data ResourceQuota
ResourceQuota' :: Maybe Int -> ResourceQuota

-- | The maximum number of instances of this Elastic Beanstalk resource
--   type that an AWS account can use.
[$sel:maximum:ResourceQuota'] :: ResourceQuota -> Maybe Int

-- | Create a value of <a>ResourceQuota</a> with all optional fields
--   omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:maximum:ResourceQuota'</a>, <a>resourceQuota_maximum</a> - The
--   maximum number of instances of this Elastic Beanstalk resource type
--   that an AWS account can use.
newResourceQuota :: ResourceQuota

-- | The maximum number of instances of this Elastic Beanstalk resource
--   type that an AWS account can use.
resourceQuota_maximum :: Lens' ResourceQuota (Maybe Int)
instance GHC.Generics.Generic Network.AWS.ElasticBeanstalk.Types.ResourceQuota.ResourceQuota
instance GHC.Show.Show Network.AWS.ElasticBeanstalk.Types.ResourceQuota.ResourceQuota
instance GHC.Read.Read Network.AWS.ElasticBeanstalk.Types.ResourceQuota.ResourceQuota
instance GHC.Classes.Eq Network.AWS.ElasticBeanstalk.Types.ResourceQuota.ResourceQuota

instance Data.Hashable.Class.Hashable Network.AWS.ElasticBeanstalk.Types.ResourceQuota.ResourceQuota
instance Control.DeepSeq.NFData Network.AWS.ElasticBeanstalk.Types.ResourceQuota.ResourceQuota


module Network.AWS.ElasticBeanstalk.Types.ResourceQuotas

-- | A set of per-resource AWS Elastic Beanstalk quotas associated with an
--   AWS account. They reflect Elastic Beanstalk resource limits for this
--   account.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newResourceQuotas</a> smart constructor.
data ResourceQuotas
ResourceQuotas' :: Maybe ResourceQuota -> Maybe ResourceQuota -> Maybe ResourceQuota -> Maybe ResourceQuota -> Maybe ResourceQuota -> ResourceQuotas

-- | The quota for applications in the AWS account.
[$sel:applicationQuota:ResourceQuotas'] :: ResourceQuotas -> Maybe ResourceQuota

-- | The quota for application versions in the AWS account.
[$sel:applicationVersionQuota:ResourceQuotas'] :: ResourceQuotas -> Maybe ResourceQuota

-- | The quota for configuration templates in the AWS account.
[$sel:configurationTemplateQuota:ResourceQuotas'] :: ResourceQuotas -> Maybe ResourceQuota

-- | The quota for environments in the AWS account.
[$sel:environmentQuota:ResourceQuotas'] :: ResourceQuotas -> Maybe ResourceQuota

-- | The quota for custom platforms in the AWS account.
[$sel:customPlatformQuota:ResourceQuotas'] :: ResourceQuotas -> Maybe ResourceQuota

-- | Create a value of <a>ResourceQuotas</a> with all optional fields
--   omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:applicationQuota:ResourceQuotas'</a>,
--   <a>resourceQuotas_applicationQuota</a> - The quota for applications in
--   the AWS account.
--   
--   <a>$sel:applicationVersionQuota:ResourceQuotas'</a>,
--   <a>resourceQuotas_applicationVersionQuota</a> - The quota for
--   application versions in the AWS account.
--   
--   <a>$sel:configurationTemplateQuota:ResourceQuotas'</a>,
--   <a>resourceQuotas_configurationTemplateQuota</a> - The quota for
--   configuration templates in the AWS account.
--   
--   <a>$sel:environmentQuota:ResourceQuotas'</a>,
--   <a>resourceQuotas_environmentQuota</a> - The quota for environments in
--   the AWS account.
--   
--   <a>$sel:customPlatformQuota:ResourceQuotas'</a>,
--   <a>resourceQuotas_customPlatformQuota</a> - The quota for custom
--   platforms in the AWS account.
newResourceQuotas :: ResourceQuotas

-- | The quota for applications in the AWS account.
resourceQuotas_applicationQuota :: Lens' ResourceQuotas (Maybe ResourceQuota)

-- | The quota for application versions in the AWS account.
resourceQuotas_applicationVersionQuota :: Lens' ResourceQuotas (Maybe ResourceQuota)

-- | The quota for configuration templates in the AWS account.
resourceQuotas_configurationTemplateQuota :: Lens' ResourceQuotas (Maybe ResourceQuota)

-- | The quota for environments in the AWS account.

-- | The quota for custom platforms in the AWS account.

module Network.AWS.ElasticBeanstalk.Types.S3Location

-- | The bucket and key of an item stored in Amazon S3.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newS3Location</a> smart constructor.
data S3Location
S3Location' :: Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> S3Location

-- | The Amazon S3 bucket where the data is located.
[$sel:s3Bucket:S3Location'] :: S3Location -> Maybe Text

-- | The Amazon S3 key where the data is located.
[$sel:s3Key:S3Location'] :: S3Location -> Maybe Text

-- | Create a value of <a>S3Location</a> with all optional fields omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:s3Bucket:S3Location'</a>, <a>s3Location_s3Bucket</a> - The
--   Amazon S3 bucket where the data is located.
--   
--   <a>$sel:s3Key:S3Location'</a>, <a>s3Location_s3Key</a> - The Amazon S3
--   key where the data is located.
newS3Location :: S3Location

-- | The Amazon S3 bucket where the data is located.
s3Location_s3Bucket :: Lens' S3Location (Maybe Text)

-- | The Amazon S3 key where the data is located.
s3Location_s3Key :: Lens' S3Location (Maybe Text)
instance GHC.Generics.Generic Network.AWS.ElasticBeanstalk.Types.S3Location.S3Location
instance GHC.Show.Show Network.AWS.ElasticBeanstalk.Types.S3Location.S3Location
instance GHC.Read.Read Network.AWS.ElasticBeanstalk.Types.S3Location.S3Location

module Network.AWS.ElasticBeanstalk.Types.SearchFilter

-- | Describes criteria to restrict a list of results.
--   
--   For operators that apply a single value to the attribute, the filter
--   is evaluated as follows: <tt>Attribute Operator Values[1]</tt>
--   
--   Some operators, e.g. <tt>in</tt>, can apply multiple values. In this
--   case, the filter is evaluated as a logical union (OR) of applications
--   of the operator to the attribute with each one of the values:
--   <tt>(Attribute Operator Values[1]) OR (Attribute Operator Values[2])
--   OR ...</tt>
--   
--   The valid values for attributes of <tt>SearchFilter</tt> depend on the
--   API action. For valid values, see the reference page for the API
--   action you're calling that takes a <tt>SearchFilter</tt> parameter.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newSearchFilter</a> smart constructor.
data SearchFilter
SearchFilter' :: Maybe [Text] -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> SearchFilter

-- | The list of values applied to the <tt>Attribute</tt> and
--   <tt>Operator</tt> attributes. Number of values and valid values vary
--   by <tt>Attribute</tt>.
[$sel:values:SearchFilter'] :: SearchFilter -> Maybe [Text]

-- | The operator to apply to the <tt>Attribute</tt> with each of the
--   <tt>Values</tt>. Valid values vary by <tt>Attribute</tt>.
[$sel:operator:SearchFilter'] :: SearchFilter -> Maybe Text

-- | The result attribute to which the filter values are applied. Valid
--   values vary by API action.
[$sel:attribute:SearchFilter'] :: SearchFilter -> Maybe Text

-- | Create a value of <a>SearchFilter</a> with all optional fields
--   omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:values:SearchFilter'</a>, <a>searchFilter_values</a> - The
--   list of values applied to the <tt>Attribute</tt> and <tt>Operator</tt>
--   attributes. Number of values and valid values vary by
--   <tt>Attribute</tt>.
--   
--   <a>$sel:operator:SearchFilter'</a>, <a>searchFilter_operator</a> - The
--   operator to apply to the <tt>Attribute</tt> with each of the
--   <tt>Values</tt>. Valid values vary by <tt>Attribute</tt>.
--   
--   <a>$sel:attribute:SearchFilter'</a>, <a>searchFilter_attribute</a> -
--   The result attribute to which the filter values are applied. Valid
--   values vary by API action.
newSearchFilter :: SearchFilter

-- | The list of values applied to the <tt>Attribute</tt> and
--   <tt>Operator</tt> attributes. Number of values and valid values vary
--   by <tt>Attribute</tt>.
searchFilter_values :: Lens' SearchFilter (Maybe [Text])

-- | The operator to apply to the <tt>Attribute</tt> with each of the
--   <tt>Values</tt>. Valid values vary by <tt>Attribute</tt>.
searchFilter_operator :: Lens' SearchFilter (Maybe Text)

-- | The result attribute to which the filter values are applied. Valid
--   values vary by API action.
searchFilter_attribute :: Lens' SearchFilter (Maybe Text)
instance GHC.Generics.Generic Network.AWS.ElasticBeanstalk.Types.SearchFilter.SearchFilter
instance GHC.Show.Show Network.AWS.ElasticBeanstalk.Types.SearchFilter.SearchFilter
instance GHC.Read.Read Network.AWS.ElasticBeanstalk.Types.SearchFilter.SearchFilter
instance GHC.Classes.Eq Network.AWS.ElasticBeanstalk.Types.SearchFilter.SearchFilter
instance Data.Hashable.Class.Hashable Network.AWS.ElasticBeanstalk.Types.SearchFilter.SearchFilter
instance Control.DeepSeq.NFData Network.AWS.ElasticBeanstalk.Types.SearchFilter.SearchFilter
instance Network.AWS.Data.Query.ToQuery Network.AWS.ElasticBeanstalk.Types.SearchFilter.SearchFilter

module Network.AWS.ElasticBeanstalk.Types.SourceBuildInformation

-- | Location of the source code for an application version.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newSourceBuildInformation</a> smart constructor.
data SourceBuildInformation
SourceBuildInformation' :: SourceType -> SourceRepository -> Text -> SourceBuildInformation

-- | The type of repository.
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li><pre>Git</pre></li>
--   <li><pre>Zip</pre></li>
--   </ul>
[$sel:sourceType:SourceBuildInformation'] :: SourceBuildInformation -> SourceType

-- | Location where the repository is stored.
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li><pre>CodeCommit</pre></li>
--   <li><pre>S3</pre></li>
--   </ul>
[$sel:sourceRepository:SourceBuildInformation'] :: SourceBuildInformation -> SourceRepository

-- | The location of the source code, as a formatted string, depending on
--   the value of <tt>SourceRepository</tt>
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li>For <tt>CodeCommit</tt>, the format is the repository name and
--   commit ID, separated by a forward slash. For example,
--   <tt>my-git-repo/265cfa0cf6af46153527f55d6503ec030551f57a</tt>.</li>
--   <li>For <tt>S3</tt>, the format is the S3 bucket name and object key,
--   separated by a forward slash. For example,
--   <tt>my-s3-bucket/Folders/my-source-file</tt>.</li>
--   </ul>
[$sel:sourceLocation:SourceBuildInformation'] :: SourceBuildInformation -> Text

-- | Create a value of <a>SourceBuildInformation</a> with all optional
--   fields omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:sourceType:SourceBuildInformation'</a>,
--   <a>sourceBuildInformation_sourceType</a> - The type of repository.
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li><pre>Git</pre></li>
--   <li><pre>Zip</pre></li>
--   </ul>
--   
--   <a>$sel:sourceRepository:SourceBuildInformation'</a>,
--   <a>sourceBuildInformation_sourceRepository</a> - Location where the
--   repository is stored.
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li><pre>CodeCommit</pre></li>
--   <li><pre>S3</pre></li>
--   </ul>
--   
--   <a>$sel:sourceLocation:SourceBuildInformation'</a>,
--   <a>sourceBuildInformation_sourceLocation</a> - The location of the
--   source code, as a formatted string, depending on the value of
--   <tt>SourceRepository</tt>
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li>For <tt>CodeCommit</tt>, the format is the repository name and
--   commit ID, separated by a forward slash. For example,
--   <tt>my-git-repo/265cfa0cf6af46153527f55d6503ec030551f57a</tt>.</li>
--   <li>For <tt>S3</tt>, the format is the S3 bucket name and object key,
--   separated by a forward slash. For example,
--   <tt>my-s3-bucket/Folders/my-source-file</tt>.</li>
--   </ul>
newSourceBuildInformation :: SourceType -> SourceRepository -> Text -> SourceBuildInformation

-- | The type of repository.
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li><pre>Git</pre></li>
--   <li><pre>Zip</pre></li>
--   </ul>
sourceBuildInformation_sourceType :: Lens' SourceBuildInformation SourceType

-- | Location where the repository is stored.
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li><pre>CodeCommit</pre></li>
--   <li><pre>S3</pre></li>
--   </ul>
sourceBuildInformation_sourceRepository :: Lens' SourceBuildInformation SourceRepository

-- | The location of the source code, as a formatted string, depending on
--   the value of <tt>SourceRepository</tt>
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li>For <tt>CodeCommit</tt>, the format is the repository name and
--   commit ID, separated by a forward slash. For example,
--   <tt>my-git-repo/265cfa0cf6af46153527f55d6503ec030551f57a</tt>.</li>
--   <li>For <tt>S3</tt>, the format is the S3 bucket name and object key,
--   separated by a forward slash. For example,
--   <tt>my-s3-bucket/Folders/my-source-file</tt>.</li>
--   </ul>
sourceBuildInformation_sourceLocation :: Lens' SourceBuildInformation Text
instance GHC.Generics.Generic Network.AWS.ElasticBeanstalk.Types.SourceBuildInformation.SourceBuildInformation
instance GHC.Show.Show Network.AWS.ElasticBeanstalk.Types.SourceBuildInformation.SourceBuildInformation
instance GHC.Read.Read Network.AWS.ElasticBeanstalk.Types.SourceBuildInformation.SourceBuildInformation
instance GHC.Classes.Eq Network.AWS.ElasticBeanstalk.Types.SourceBuildInformation.SourceBuildInformation
instance Network.AWS.Data.XML.FromXML Network.AWS.ElasticBeanstalk.Types.SourceBuildInformation.SourceBuildInformation
instance Data.Hashable.Class.Hashable Network.AWS.ElasticBeanstalk.Types.SourceBuildInformation.SourceBuildInformation

instance Network.AWS.Data.Query.ToQuery Network.AWS.ElasticBeanstalk.Types.SourceBuildInformation.SourceBuildInformation


module Network.AWS.ElasticBeanstalk.Types.ApplicationVersionDescription

-- | Describes the properties of an application version.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newApplicationVersionDescription</a> smart constructor.
data ApplicationVersionDescription
ApplicationVersionDescription' :: Maybe ApplicationVersionStatus -> Maybe ISO8601 -> Maybe S3Location -> Maybe SourceBuildInformation -> Maybe Text -> Maybe ISO8601 -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> ApplicationVersionDescription

-- | The processing status of the application version. Reflects the state
--   of the application version during its creation. Many of the values are
--   only applicable if you specified <tt>True</tt> for the
--   <tt>Process</tt> parameter of the <tt>CreateApplicationVersion</tt>
--   action. The following list describes the possible values.
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li><tt>Unprocessed</tt> – Application version wasn't pre-processed or
--   validated. Elastic Beanstalk will validate configuration files during
--   deployment of the application version to an environment.</li>
--   <li><tt>Processing</tt> – Elastic Beanstalk is currently processing
--   the application version.</li>
--   <li><tt>Building</tt> – Application version is currently undergoing an
--   AWS CodeBuild build.</li>
--   <li><tt>Processed</tt> – Elastic Beanstalk was successfully
--   pre-processed and validated.</li>
--   <li><tt>Failed</tt> – Either the AWS CodeBuild build failed or
--   configuration files didn't pass validation. This application version
--   isn't usable.</li>
--   </ul>
[$sel:status:ApplicationVersionDescription'] :: ApplicationVersionDescription -> Maybe ApplicationVersionStatus

-- | The creation date of the application version.
[$sel:dateCreated:ApplicationVersionDescription'] :: ApplicationVersionDescription -> Maybe ISO8601

-- | The storage location of the application version's source bundle in
--   Amazon S3.
[$sel:sourceBundle:ApplicationVersionDescription'] :: ApplicationVersionDescription -> Maybe S3Location

-- | If the version's source code was retrieved from AWS CodeCommit, the
--   location of the source code for the application version.
[$sel:sourceBuildInformation:ApplicationVersionDescription'] :: ApplicationVersionDescription -> Maybe SourceBuildInformation

-- | A unique identifier for the application version.
[$sel:versionLabel:ApplicationVersionDescription'] :: ApplicationVersionDescription -> Maybe Text

-- | The last modified date of the application version.
[$sel:dateUpdated:ApplicationVersionDescription'] :: ApplicationVersionDescription -> Maybe ISO8601

-- | The description of the application version.
[$sel:description:ApplicationVersionDescription'] :: ApplicationVersionDescription -> Maybe Text

-- | Reference to the artifact from the AWS CodeBuild build.
[$sel:buildArn:ApplicationVersionDescription'] :: ApplicationVersionDescription -> Maybe Text

-- | The name of the application to which the application version belongs.
[$sel:applicationName:ApplicationVersionDescription'] :: ApplicationVersionDescription -> Maybe Text

-- | The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the application version.
[$sel:applicationVersionArn:ApplicationVersionDescription'] :: ApplicationVersionDescription -> Maybe Text

-- | Create a value of <a>ApplicationVersionDescription</a> with all
--   optional fields omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:status:ApplicationVersionDescription'</a>,
--   <a>applicationVersionDescription_status</a> - The processing status of
--   the application version. Reflects the state of the application version
--   during its creation. Many of the values are only applicable if you
--   specified <tt>True</tt> for the <tt>Process</tt> parameter of the
--   <tt>CreateApplicationVersion</tt> action. The following list describes
--   the possible values.
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li><tt>Unprocessed</tt> – Application version wasn't pre-processed or
--   validated. Elastic Beanstalk will validate configuration files during
--   deployment of the application version to an environment.</li>
--   <li><tt>Processing</tt> – Elastic Beanstalk is currently processing
--   the application version.</li>
--   <li><tt>Building</tt> – Application version is currently undergoing an
--   AWS CodeBuild build.</li>
--   <li><tt>Processed</tt> – Elastic Beanstalk was successfully
--   pre-processed and validated.</li>
--   <li><tt>Failed</tt> – Either the AWS CodeBuild build failed or
--   configuration files didn't pass validation. This application version
--   isn't usable.</li>
--   </ul>
--   
--   <a>$sel:dateCreated:ApplicationVersionDescription'</a>,
--   <a>applicationVersionDescription_dateCreated</a> - The creation date
--   of the application version.
--   
--   <a>$sel:sourceBundle:ApplicationVersionDescription'</a>,
--   <a>applicationVersionDescription_sourceBundle</a> - The storage
--   location of the application version's source bundle in Amazon S3.
--   
--   <a>$sel:sourceBuildInformation:ApplicationVersionDescription'</a>,
--   <a>applicationVersionDescription_sourceBuildInformation</a> - If the
--   version's source code was retrieved from AWS CodeCommit, the location
--   of the source code for the application version.
--   
--   <a>$sel:versionLabel:ApplicationVersionDescription'</a>,
--   <a>applicationVersionDescription_versionLabel</a> - A unique
--   identifier for the application version.
--   
--   <a>$sel:dateUpdated:ApplicationVersionDescription'</a>,
--   <a>applicationVersionDescription_dateUpdated</a> - The last modified
--   date of the application version.
--   
--   <a>$sel:description:ApplicationVersionDescription'</a>,
--   <a>applicationVersionDescription_description</a> - The description of
--   the application version.
--   
--   <a>$sel:buildArn:ApplicationVersionDescription'</a>,
--   <a>applicationVersionDescription_buildArn</a> - Reference to the
--   artifact from the AWS CodeBuild build.
--   
--   <a>$sel:applicationName:ApplicationVersionDescription'</a>,
--   <a>applicationVersionDescription_applicationName</a> - The name of the
--   application to which the application version belongs.
--   
--   <a>$sel:applicationVersionArn:ApplicationVersionDescription'</a>,
--   <a>applicationVersionDescription_applicationVersionArn</a> - The
--   Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the application version.
newApplicationVersionDescription :: ApplicationVersionDescription

-- | The processing status of the application version. Reflects the state
--   of the application version during its creation. Many of the values are
--   only applicable if you specified <tt>True</tt> for the
--   <tt>Process</tt> parameter of the <tt>CreateApplicationVersion</tt>
--   action. The following list describes the possible values.
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li><tt>Unprocessed</tt> – Application version wasn't pre-processed or
--   validated. Elastic Beanstalk will validate configuration files during
--   deployment of the application version to an environment.</li>
--   <li><tt>Processing</tt> – Elastic Beanstalk is currently processing
--   the application version.</li>
--   <li><tt>Building</tt> – Application version is currently undergoing an
--   AWS CodeBuild build.</li>
--   <li><tt>Processed</tt> – Elastic Beanstalk was successfully
--   pre-processed and validated.</li>
--   <li><tt>Failed</tt> – Either the AWS CodeBuild build failed or
--   configuration files didn't pass validation. This application version
--   isn't usable.</li>
--   </ul>
applicationVersionDescription_status :: Lens' ApplicationVersionDescription (Maybe ApplicationVersionStatus)

-- | The creation date of the application version.
applicationVersionDescription_dateCreated :: Lens' ApplicationVersionDescription (Maybe UTCTime)

-- | The storage location of the application version's source bundle in
--   Amazon S3.
applicationVersionDescription_sourceBundle :: Lens' ApplicationVersionDescription (Maybe S3Location)

-- | If the version's source code was retrieved from AWS CodeCommit, the
--   location of the source code for the application version.
applicationVersionDescription_sourceBuildInformation :: Lens' ApplicationVersionDescription (Maybe SourceBuildInformation)

-- | A unique identifier for the application version.
applicationVersionDescription_versionLabel :: Lens' ApplicationVersionDescription (Maybe Text)

-- | The last modified date of the application version.
applicationVersionDescription_dateUpdated :: Lens' ApplicationVersionDescription (Maybe UTCTime)

-- | The description of the application version.
applicationVersionDescription_description :: Lens' ApplicationVersionDescription (Maybe Text)

-- | Reference to the artifact from the AWS CodeBuild build.
applicationVersionDescription_buildArn :: Lens' ApplicationVersionDescription (Maybe Text)

-- | The name of the application to which the application version belongs.
applicationVersionDescription_applicationName :: Lens' ApplicationVersionDescription (Maybe Text)

-- | The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the application version.
applicationVersionDescription_applicationVersionArn :: Lens' ApplicationVersionDescription (Maybe Text)
instance GHC.Generics.Generic Network.AWS.ElasticBeanstalk.Types.ApplicationVersionDescription.ApplicationVersionDescription
instance GHC.Show.Show Network.AWS.ElasticBeanstalk.Types.ApplicationVersionDescription.ApplicationVersionDescription
instance GHC.Read.Read Network.AWS.ElasticBeanstalk.Types.ApplicationVersionDescription.ApplicationVersionDescription
instance GHC.Classes.Eq Network.AWS.ElasticBeanstalk.Types.ApplicationVersionDescription.ApplicationVersionDescription

module Network.AWS.ElasticBeanstalk.Types.StatusCodes

-- | Represents the percentage of requests over the last 10 seconds that
--   resulted in each type of status code response. For more information,
--   see <a>Status Code Definitions</a>.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newStatusCodes</a> smart constructor.
data StatusCodes
StatusCodes' :: Maybe Int -> Maybe Int -> Maybe Int -> Maybe Int -> StatusCodes

-- | The percentage of requests over the last 10 seconds that resulted in a
--   3xx (300, 301, etc.) status code.
[$sel:status3xx:StatusCodes'] :: StatusCodes -> Maybe Int

-- | The percentage of requests over the last 10 seconds that resulted in a
--   5xx (500, 501, etc.) status code.
[$sel:status5xx:StatusCodes'] :: StatusCodes -> Maybe Int

-- | The percentage of requests over the last 10 seconds that resulted in a
--   2xx (200, 201, etc.) status code.
[$sel:status2xx:StatusCodes'] :: StatusCodes -> Maybe Int

-- | The percentage of requests over the last 10 seconds that resulted in a
--   4xx (400, 401, etc.) status code.
[$sel:status4xx:StatusCodes'] :: StatusCodes -> Maybe Int

-- | Create a value of <a>StatusCodes</a> with all optional fields omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:status3xx:StatusCodes'</a>, <a>statusCodes_status3xx</a> - The
--   percentage of requests over the last 10 seconds that resulted in a 3xx
--   (300, 301, etc.) status code.
--   
--   <a>$sel:status5xx:StatusCodes'</a>, <a>statusCodes_status5xx</a> - The
--   percentage of requests over the last 10 seconds that resulted in a 5xx
--   (500, 501, etc.) status code.
--   
--   <a>$sel:status2xx:StatusCodes'</a>, <a>statusCodes_status2xx</a> - The
--   percentage of requests over the last 10 seconds that resulted in a 2xx
--   (200, 201, etc.) status code.
--   
--   <a>$sel:status4xx:StatusCodes'</a>, <a>statusCodes_status4xx</a> - The
--   percentage of requests over the last 10 seconds that resulted in a 4xx
--   (400, 401, etc.) status code.
newStatusCodes :: StatusCodes

-- | The percentage of requests over the last 10 seconds that resulted in a
--   3xx (300, 301, etc.) status code.
statusCodes_status3xx :: Lens' StatusCodes (Maybe Int)

-- | The percentage of requests over the last 10 seconds that resulted in a
--   5xx (500, 501, etc.) status code.
statusCodes_status5xx :: Lens' StatusCodes (Maybe Int)

-- | The percentage of requests over the last 10 seconds that resulted in a
--   2xx (200, 201, etc.) status code.
statusCodes_status2xx :: Lens' StatusCodes (Maybe Int)

-- | The percentage of requests over the last 10 seconds that resulted in a
--   4xx (400, 401, etc.) status code.
statusCodes_status4xx :: Lens' StatusCodes (Maybe Int)

module Network.AWS.ElasticBeanstalk.Types.ApplicationMetrics

-- | Application request metrics for an AWS Elastic Beanstalk environment.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newApplicationMetrics</a> smart constructor.
data ApplicationMetrics
ApplicationMetrics' :: Maybe Int -> Maybe Int -> Maybe StatusCodes -> Maybe Latency -> ApplicationMetrics

-- | The amount of time that the metrics cover (usually 10 seconds). For
--   example, you might have 5 requests (<tt>request_count</tt>) within the
--   most recent time slice of 10 seconds (<tt>duration</tt>).
[$sel:duration:ApplicationMetrics'] :: ApplicationMetrics -> Maybe Int

-- | Average number of requests handled by the web server per second over
--   the last 10 seconds.
[$sel:requestCount:ApplicationMetrics'] :: ApplicationMetrics -> Maybe Int

-- | Represents the percentage of requests over the last 10 seconds that
--   resulted in each type of status code response.
[$sel:statusCodes:ApplicationMetrics'] :: ApplicationMetrics -> Maybe StatusCodes

-- | Represents the average latency for the slowest X percent of requests
--   over the last 10 seconds. Latencies are in seconds with one
--   millisecond resolution.
[$sel:latency:ApplicationMetrics'] :: ApplicationMetrics -> Maybe Latency

-- | Create a value of <a>ApplicationMetrics</a> with all optional fields
--   omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:duration:ApplicationMetrics'</a>,
--   <a>applicationMetrics_duration</a> - The amount of time that the
--   metrics cover (usually 10 seconds). For example, you might have 5
--   requests (<tt>request_count</tt>) within the most recent time slice of
--   10 seconds (<tt>duration</tt>).
--   
--   <a>$sel:requestCount:ApplicationMetrics'</a>,
--   <a>applicationMetrics_requestCount</a> - Average number of requests
--   handled by the web server per second over the last 10 seconds.
--   
--   <a>$sel:statusCodes:ApplicationMetrics'</a>,
--   <a>applicationMetrics_statusCodes</a> - Represents the percentage of
--   requests over the last 10 seconds that resulted in each type of status
--   code response.
--   
--   <a>$sel:latency:ApplicationMetrics'</a>,
--   <a>applicationMetrics_latency</a> - Represents the average latency for
--   the slowest X percent of requests over the last 10 seconds. Latencies
--   are in seconds with one millisecond resolution.
newApplicationMetrics :: ApplicationMetrics

-- | The amount of time that the metrics cover (usually 10 seconds). For
--   example, you might have 5 requests (<tt>request_count</tt>) within the
--   most recent time slice of 10 seconds (<tt>duration</tt>).
applicationMetrics_duration :: Lens' ApplicationMetrics (Maybe Int)

-- | Average number of requests handled by the web server per second over
--   the last 10 seconds.
applicationMetrics_requestCount :: Lens' ApplicationMetrics (Maybe Int)

-- | Represents the percentage of requests over the last 10 seconds that
--   resulted in each type of status code response.
applicationMetrics_statusCodes :: Lens' ApplicationMetrics (Maybe StatusCodes)

-- | Represents the average latency for the slowest X percent of requests
--   over the last 10 seconds. Latencies are in seconds with one
--   millisecond resolution.
applicationMetrics_latency :: Lens' ApplicationMetrics (Maybe Latency)
instance GHC.Generics.Generic Network.AWS.ElasticBeanstalk.Types.ApplicationMetrics.ApplicationMetrics
instance GHC.Show.Show Network.AWS.ElasticBeanstalk.Types.ApplicationMetrics.ApplicationMetrics
instance GHC.Read.Read Network.AWS.ElasticBeanstalk.Types.ApplicationMetrics.ApplicationMetrics
instance GHC.Classes.Eq Network.AWS.ElasticBeanstalk.Types.ApplicationMetrics.ApplicationMetrics
instance Network.AWS.Data.XML.FromXML Network.AWS.ElasticBeanstalk.Types.ApplicationMetrics.ApplicationMetrics
instance Data.Hashable.Class.Hashable Network.AWS.ElasticBeanstalk.Types.ApplicationMetrics.ApplicationMetrics
instance Control.DeepSeq.NFData Network.AWS.ElasticBeanstalk.Types.ApplicationMetrics.ApplicationMetrics

module Network.AWS.ElasticBeanstalk.Types.SingleInstanceHealth

-- | Detailed health information about an Amazon EC2 instance in your
--   Elastic Beanstalk environment.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newSingleInstanceHealth</a> smart constructor.
data SingleInstanceHealth
SingleInstanceHealth' :: Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe [Text] -> Maybe Text -> Maybe ISO8601 -> Maybe Deployment -> Maybe Text -> Maybe SystemStatus -> Maybe ApplicationMetrics -> SingleInstanceHealth

-- | The ID of the Amazon EC2 instance.
[$sel:instanceId:SingleInstanceHealth'] :: SingleInstanceHealth -> Maybe Text

-- | The instance's type.
[$sel:instanceType:SingleInstanceHealth'] :: SingleInstanceHealth -> Maybe Text

--   and Statuses</a>.

--   current health status.

-- | The time at which the EC2 instance was launched.
[$sel:launchedAt:SingleInstanceHealth'] :: SingleInstanceHealth -> Maybe ISO8601

-- | Information about the most recent deployment to an instance.
[$sel:deployment:SingleInstanceHealth'] :: SingleInstanceHealth -> Maybe Deployment

-- | Returns the health status of the specified instance. For more
--   information, see <a>Health Colors and Statuses</a>.
[$sel:healthStatus:SingleInstanceHealth'] :: SingleInstanceHealth -> Maybe Text

-- | Operating system metrics from the instance.
[$sel:system:SingleInstanceHealth'] :: SingleInstanceHealth -> Maybe SystemStatus

-- | Request metrics from your application.
[$sel:applicationMetrics:SingleInstanceHealth'] :: SingleInstanceHealth -> Maybe ApplicationMetrics

--   fields.

--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:

--   instance.

--   <a>singleInstanceHealth_instanceType</a> - The instance's type.
--   
--   <a>$sel:color:SingleInstanceHealth'</a>,
--   <a>singleInstanceHealth_color</a> - Represents the color indicator
--   that gives you information about the health of the EC2 instance. For
--   more information, see <a>Health Colors and Statuses</a>.
--   
--   <a>$sel:causes:SingleInstanceHealth'</a>,
--   <a>singleInstanceHealth_causes</a> - Represents the causes, which

--   
--   <a>$sel:availabilityZone:SingleInstanceHealth'</a>,

module Network.AWS.ElasticBeanstalk.Types.EnvironmentResourceDescription

--   live.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newEnvironmentResourceDescription</a> smart
--   constructor.
data EnvironmentResourceDescription

[$sel:queues:EnvironmentResourceDescription'] :: EnvironmentResourceDescription -> Maybe [Queue]

[$sel:instances:EnvironmentResourceDescription'] :: EnvironmentResourceDescription -> Maybe [Instance]

[$sel:environmentName:EnvironmentResourceDescription'] :: EnvironmentResourceDescription -> Maybe Text

-- | The LoadBalancers in use by this environment.
[$sel:loadBalancers:EnvironmentResourceDescription'] :: EnvironmentResourceDescription -> Maybe [LoadBalancer]

-- | The <tt>AutoScalingGroups</tt> used by this environment.

--   Scaling launch configurations in use by this environment.

--   <tt>AutoScaling</tt> triggers in use by this environment.

module Network.AWS.ElasticBeanstalk.Types.ValidationMessage

-- | An error or warning for a desired configuration option value.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newValidationMessage</a> smart constructor.
data ValidationMessage
ValidationMessage' :: Maybe Text -> Maybe ValidationSeverity -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> ValidationMessage

-- | The name of the option.
[$sel:optionName:ValidationMessage'] :: ValidationMessage -> Maybe Text

-- | An indication of the severity of this message:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li><tt>error</tt>: This message indicates that this is not a valid
--   setting for an option.</li>
--   <li><tt>warning</tt>: This message is providing information you should
--   take into account.</li>
--   </ul>
[$sel:severity:ValidationMessage'] :: ValidationMessage -> Maybe ValidationSeverity

-- | A message describing the error or warning.
[$sel:message:ValidationMessage'] :: ValidationMessage -> Maybe Text

-- | The namespace to which the option belongs.
[$sel:namespace:ValidationMessage'] :: ValidationMessage -> Maybe Text

-- | Create a value of <a>ValidationMessage</a> with all optional fields
--   omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:optionName:ValidationMessage'</a>,
--   <a>validationMessage_optionName</a> - The name of the option.
--   
--   <a>$sel:severity:ValidationMessage'</a>,
--   <a>validationMessage_severity</a> - An indication of the severity of
--   this message:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li><tt>error</tt>: This message indicates that this is not a valid
--   setting for an option.</li>
--   <li><tt>warning</tt>: This message is providing information you should
--   take into account.</li>
--   </ul>
--   
--   <a>$sel:message:ValidationMessage'</a>,
--   <a>validationMessage_message</a> - A message describing the error or
--   warning.
--   
--   <a>$sel:namespace:ValidationMessage'</a>,
--   <a>validationMessage_namespace</a> - The namespace to which the option
--   belongs.
newValidationMessage :: ValidationMessage

-- | The name of the option.
validationMessage_optionName :: Lens' ValidationMessage (Maybe Text)

-- | An indication of the severity of this message:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li><tt>error</tt>: This message indicates that this is not a valid
--   setting for an option.</li>
--   <li><tt>warning</tt>: This message is providing information you should
--   take into account.</li>
--   </ul>
validationMessage_severity :: Lens' ValidationMessage (Maybe ValidationSeverity)

-- | A message describing the error or warning.
validationMessage_message :: Lens' ValidationMessage (Maybe Text)

-- | The namespace to which the option belongs.
validationMessage_namespace :: Lens' ValidationMessage (Maybe Text)

instance GHC.Show.Show Network.AWS.ElasticBeanstalk.Types.ValidationMessage.ValidationMessage

module Network.AWS.ElasticBeanstalk.Types

-- | API version <tt>2010-12-01</tt> of the Amazon Elastic Beanstalk SDK
--   configuration.
defaultService :: Service

-- | You have exceeded the maximum number of allowed platforms associated
--   with the account.
_TooManyPlatformsException :: AsError a => Getting (First ServiceError) a ServiceError

-- | The number of tags in the resource would exceed the number of tags
--   that each resource can have.
--   
--   To calculate this, the operation considers both the number of tags the
--   resource already has and the tags this operation would add if it
--   succeeded.
_TooManyTagsException :: AsError a => Getting (First ServiceError) a ServiceError

-- | The specified account has reached its limit of applications.
_TooManyApplicationsException :: AsError a => Getting (First ServiceError) a ServiceError

-- | The specified account has reached its limit of environments.
_TooManyEnvironmentsException :: AsError a => Getting (First ServiceError) a ServiceError

-- | The specified account does not have sufficient privileges for one or
--   more AWS services.
_InsufficientPrivilegesException :: AsError a => Getting (First ServiceError) a ServiceError

-- | The type of the specified Amazon Resource Name (ARN) isn't supported
--   for this operation.
_ResourceTypeNotSupportedException :: AsError a => Getting (First ServiceError) a ServiceError

-- | The specified account has reached its limit of configuration
--   templates.
_TooManyConfigurationTemplatesException :: AsError a => Getting (First ServiceError) a ServiceError

-- | Unable to perform the specified operation because another operation
--   that effects an element in this activity is already in progress.
_OperationInProgressException :: AsError a => Getting (First ServiceError) a ServiceError

-- | The specified account has reached its limit of Amazon S3 buckets.
_TooManyBucketsException :: AsError a => Getting (First ServiceError) a ServiceError

-- | The specified account does not have a subscription to Amazon S3.
_S3SubscriptionRequiredException :: AsError a => Getting (First ServiceError) a ServiceError

-- | Unable to delete the Amazon S3 source bundle associated with the
--   application version. The application version was deleted successfully.
_SourceBundleDeletionException :: AsError a => Getting (First ServiceError) a ServiceError

-- | One or more input parameters is not valid. Please correct the input
--   parameters and try the operation again.
_InvalidRequestException :: AsError a => Getting (First ServiceError) a ServiceError

-- | A generic service exception has occurred.
_ElasticBeanstalkServiceException :: AsError a => Getting (First ServiceError) a ServiceError

-- | A resource doesn't exist for the specified Amazon Resource Name (ARN).
_ResourceNotFoundException :: AsError a => Getting (First ServiceError) a ServiceError

-- | The specified account has reached its limit of application versions.
_TooManyApplicationVersionsException :: AsError a => Getting (First ServiceError) a ServiceError

-- | AWS CodeBuild is not available in the specified region.
_CodeBuildNotInServiceRegionException :: AsError a => Getting (First ServiceError) a ServiceError

-- | You cannot delete the platform version because there are still
--   environments running on it.
_PlatformVersionStillReferencedException :: AsError a => Getting (First ServiceError) a ServiceError

-- | The specified S3 bucket does not belong to the S3 region in which the
--   service is running. The following regions are supported:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li>IAD/us-east-1</li>
--   <li>PDX/us-west-2</li>
--   <li>DUB/eu-west-1</li>
--   </ul>
_S3LocationNotInServiceRegionException :: AsError a => Getting (First ServiceError) a ServiceError

-- | Cannot modify the managed action in its current state.
_ManagedActionInvalidStateException :: AsError a => Getting (First ServiceError) a ServiceError

-- | Describes the properties of an application.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newApplicationDescription</a> smart constructor.
data ApplicationDescription
ApplicationDescription' :: Maybe Text -> Maybe ISO8601 -> Maybe [Text] -> Maybe ISO8601 -> Maybe ApplicationResourceLifecycleConfig -> Maybe Text -> Maybe [Text] -> Maybe Text -> ApplicationDescription

-- | The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the application.
[$sel:applicationArn:ApplicationDescription'] :: ApplicationDescription -> Maybe Text

-- | The date when the application was created.
[$sel:dateCreated:ApplicationDescription'] :: ApplicationDescription -> Maybe ISO8601

-- | The names of the versions for this application.
[$sel:versions:ApplicationDescription'] :: ApplicationDescription -> Maybe [Text]

-- | The date when the application was last modified.
[$sel:dateUpdated:ApplicationDescription'] :: ApplicationDescription -> Maybe ISO8601

-- | The lifecycle settings for the application.
[$sel:resourceLifecycleConfig:ApplicationDescription'] :: ApplicationDescription -> Maybe ApplicationResourceLifecycleConfig

-- | User-defined description of the application.
[$sel:description:ApplicationDescription'] :: ApplicationDescription -> Maybe Text

-- | The names of the configuration templates associated with this
--   application.
[$sel:configurationTemplates:ApplicationDescription'] :: ApplicationDescription -> Maybe [Text]

-- | The name of the application.
[$sel:applicationName:ApplicationDescription'] :: ApplicationDescription -> Maybe Text

-- | Create a value of <a>ApplicationDescription</a> with all optional
--   fields omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:applicationArn:ApplicationDescription'</a>,
--   <a>applicationDescription_applicationArn</a> - The Amazon Resource
--   Name (ARN) of the application.
--   
--   <a>$sel:dateCreated:ApplicationDescription'</a>,
--   <a>applicationDescription_dateCreated</a> - The date when the
--   application was created.
--   
--   <a>$sel:versions:ApplicationDescription'</a>,
--   <a>applicationDescription_versions</a> - The names of the versions for
--   this application.
--   
--   <a>$sel:dateUpdated:ApplicationDescription'</a>,
--   <a>applicationDescription_dateUpdated</a> - The date when the
--   application was last modified.
--   
--   <a>$sel:resourceLifecycleConfig:ApplicationDescription'</a>,
--   <a>applicationDescription_resourceLifecycleConfig</a> - The lifecycle
--   settings for the application.
--   
--   <a>$sel:description:ApplicationDescription'</a>,
--   <a>applicationDescription_description</a> - User-defined description
--   of the application.
--   
--   <a>$sel:configurationTemplates:ApplicationDescription'</a>,
--   <a>applicationDescription_configurationTemplates</a> - The names of
--   the configuration templates associated with this application.
--   
--   <a>$sel:applicationName:ApplicationDescription'</a>,
--   <a>applicationDescription_applicationName</a> - The name of the
--   application.
newApplicationDescription :: ApplicationDescription

-- | The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the application.
applicationDescription_applicationArn :: Lens' ApplicationDescription (Maybe Text)

-- | The date when the application was created.
applicationDescription_dateCreated :: Lens' ApplicationDescription (Maybe UTCTime)

-- | The names of the versions for this application.
applicationDescription_versions :: Lens' ApplicationDescription (Maybe [Text])

-- | The date when the application was last modified.
applicationDescription_dateUpdated :: Lens' ApplicationDescription (Maybe UTCTime)

-- | The lifecycle settings for the application.
applicationDescription_resourceLifecycleConfig :: Lens' ApplicationDescription (Maybe ApplicationResourceLifecycleConfig)

-- | User-defined description of the application.
applicationDescription_description :: Lens' ApplicationDescription (Maybe Text)

-- | The names of the configuration templates associated with this
--   application.
applicationDescription_configurationTemplates :: Lens' ApplicationDescription (Maybe [Text])

-- | The name of the application.
applicationDescription_applicationName :: Lens' ApplicationDescription (Maybe Text)

-- | Application request metrics for an AWS Elastic Beanstalk environment.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newApplicationMetrics</a> smart constructor.
data ApplicationMetrics
ApplicationMetrics' :: Maybe Int -> Maybe Int -> Maybe StatusCodes -> Maybe Latency -> ApplicationMetrics

-- | The amount of time that the metrics cover (usually 10 seconds). For
--   example, you might have 5 requests (<tt>request_count</tt>) within the
--   most recent time slice of 10 seconds (<tt>duration</tt>).
[$sel:duration:ApplicationMetrics'] :: ApplicationMetrics -> Maybe Int

-- | Average number of requests handled by the web server per second over
--   the last 10 seconds.
[$sel:requestCount:ApplicationMetrics'] :: ApplicationMetrics -> Maybe Int

-- | Represents the percentage of requests over the last 10 seconds that
--   resulted in each type of status code response.
[$sel:statusCodes:ApplicationMetrics'] :: ApplicationMetrics -> Maybe StatusCodes

-- | Represents the average latency for the slowest X percent of requests
--   over the last 10 seconds. Latencies are in seconds with one
--   millisecond resolution.
[$sel:latency:ApplicationMetrics'] :: ApplicationMetrics -> Maybe Latency

-- | Create a value of <a>ApplicationMetrics</a> with all optional fields
--   omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:duration:ApplicationMetrics'</a>,
--   <a>applicationMetrics_duration</a> - The amount of time that the
--   metrics cover (usually 10 seconds). For example, you might have 5
--   requests (<tt>request_count</tt>) within the most recent time slice of
--   10 seconds (<tt>duration</tt>).
--   
--   <a>$sel:requestCount:ApplicationMetrics'</a>,
--   <a>applicationMetrics_requestCount</a> - Average number of requests
--   handled by the web server per second over the last 10 seconds.
--   
--   <a>$sel:statusCodes:ApplicationMetrics'</a>,
--   <a>applicationMetrics_statusCodes</a> - Represents the percentage of
--   requests over the last 10 seconds that resulted in each type of status
--   code response.
--   
--   <a>$sel:latency:ApplicationMetrics'</a>,
--   <a>applicationMetrics_latency</a> - Represents the average latency for
--   the slowest X percent of requests over the last 10 seconds. Latencies
--   are in seconds with one millisecond resolution.
newApplicationMetrics :: ApplicationMetrics

-- | The amount of time that the metrics cover (usually 10 seconds). For
--   example, you might have 5 requests (<tt>request_count</tt>) within the
--   most recent time slice of 10 seconds (<tt>duration</tt>).
applicationMetrics_duration :: Lens' ApplicationMetrics (Maybe Int)

-- | Average number of requests handled by the web server per second over
--   the last 10 seconds.
applicationMetrics_requestCount :: Lens' ApplicationMetrics (Maybe Int)

-- | Represents the percentage of requests over the last 10 seconds that
--   resulted in each type of status code response.
applicationMetrics_statusCodes :: Lens' ApplicationMetrics (Maybe StatusCodes)

-- | Represents the average latency for the slowest X percent of requests
--   over the last 10 seconds. Latencies are in seconds with one
--   millisecond resolution.
applicationMetrics_latency :: Lens' ApplicationMetrics (Maybe Latency)

-- | The resource lifecycle configuration for an application. Defines
--   lifecycle settings for resources that belong to the application, and
--   the service role that AWS Elastic Beanstalk assumes in order to apply
--   lifecycle settings. The version lifecycle configuration defines
--   lifecycle settings for application versions.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newApplicationResourceLifecycleConfig</a> smart
--   constructor.
data ApplicationResourceLifecycleConfig
ApplicationResourceLifecycleConfig' :: Maybe Text -> Maybe ApplicationVersionLifecycleConfig -> ApplicationResourceLifecycleConfig

-- | The ARN of an IAM service role that Elastic Beanstalk has permission
--   to assume.
--   
--   The <tt>ServiceRole</tt> property is required the first time that you
--   provide a <tt>VersionLifecycleConfig</tt> for the application in one
--   of the supporting calls (<tt>CreateApplication</tt> or
--   <tt>UpdateApplicationResourceLifecycle</tt>). After you provide it
--   once, in either one of the calls, Elastic Beanstalk persists the
--   Service Role with the application, and you don't need to specify it
--   again in subsequent <tt>UpdateApplicationResourceLifecycle</tt> calls.
--   You can, however, specify it in subsequent calls to change the Service
--   Role to another value.
[$sel:serviceRole:ApplicationResourceLifecycleConfig'] :: ApplicationResourceLifecycleConfig -> Maybe Text

-- | Defines lifecycle settings for application versions.
[$sel:versionLifecycleConfig:ApplicationResourceLifecycleConfig'] :: ApplicationResourceLifecycleConfig -> Maybe ApplicationVersionLifecycleConfig

-- | Create a value of <a>ApplicationResourceLifecycleConfig</a> with all
--   optional fields omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:serviceRole:ApplicationResourceLifecycleConfig'</a>,
--   <a>applicationResourceLifecycleConfig_serviceRole</a> - The ARN of an
--   IAM service role that Elastic Beanstalk has permission to assume.
--   
--   The <tt>ServiceRole</tt> property is required the first time that you
--   provide a <tt>VersionLifecycleConfig</tt> for the application in one
--   of the supporting calls (<tt>CreateApplication</tt> or
--   <tt>UpdateApplicationResourceLifecycle</tt>). After you provide it
--   once, in either one of the calls, Elastic Beanstalk persists the
--   Service Role with the application, and you don't need to specify it
--   again in subsequent <tt>UpdateApplicationResourceLifecycle</tt> calls.
--   You can, however, specify it in subsequent calls to change the Service
--   Role to another value.
--   
--   
--   <a>$sel:versionLifecycleConfig:ApplicationResourceLifecycleConfig'</a>,
--   <a>applicationResourceLifecycleConfig_versionLifecycleConfig</a> -
--   Defines lifecycle settings for application versions.
newApplicationResourceLifecycleConfig :: ApplicationResourceLifecycleConfig

-- | The ARN of an IAM service role that Elastic Beanstalk has permission
--   to assume.
--   
--   The <tt>ServiceRole</tt> property is required the first time that you
--   provide a <tt>VersionLifecycleConfig</tt> for the application in one
--   of the supporting calls (<tt>CreateApplication</tt> or
--   <tt>UpdateApplicationResourceLifecycle</tt>). After you provide it
--   once, in either one of the calls, Elastic Beanstalk persists the
--   Service Role with the application, and you don't need to specify it
--   again in subsequent <tt>UpdateApplicationResourceLifecycle</tt> calls.
--   You can, however, specify it in subsequent calls to change the Service
--   Role to another value.
applicationResourceLifecycleConfig_serviceRole :: Lens' ApplicationResourceLifecycleConfig (Maybe Text)

-- | Defines lifecycle settings for application versions.
applicationResourceLifecycleConfig_versionLifecycleConfig :: Lens' ApplicationResourceLifecycleConfig (Maybe ApplicationVersionLifecycleConfig)

-- | Describes the properties of an application version.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newApplicationVersionDescription</a> smart constructor.
data ApplicationVersionDescription
ApplicationVersionDescription' :: Maybe ApplicationVersionStatus -> Maybe ISO8601 -> Maybe S3Location -> Maybe SourceBuildInformation -> Maybe Text -> Maybe ISO8601 -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> ApplicationVersionDescription

-- | The processing status of the application version. Reflects the state
--   of the application version during its creation. Many of the values are
--   only applicable if you specified <tt>True</tt> for the
--   <tt>Process</tt> parameter of the <tt>CreateApplicationVersion</tt>
--   action. The following list describes the possible values.
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li><tt>Unprocessed</tt> – Application version wasn't pre-processed or
--   validated. Elastic Beanstalk will validate configuration files during
--   deployment of the application version to an environment.</li>
--   <li><tt>Processing</tt> – Elastic Beanstalk is currently processing
--   the application version.</li>
--   <li><tt>Building</tt> – Application version is currently undergoing an
--   AWS CodeBuild build.</li>
--   <li><tt>Processed</tt> – Elastic Beanstalk was successfully
--   pre-processed and validated.</li>
--   <li><tt>Failed</tt> – Either the AWS CodeBuild build failed or
--   configuration files didn't pass validation. This application version
--   isn't usable.</li>
--   </ul>
[$sel:status:ApplicationVersionDescription'] :: ApplicationVersionDescription -> Maybe ApplicationVersionStatus

-- | The creation date of the application version.
[$sel:dateCreated:ApplicationVersionDescription'] :: ApplicationVersionDescription -> Maybe ISO8601

-- | The storage location of the application version's source bundle in
--   Amazon S3.
[$sel:sourceBundle:ApplicationVersionDescription'] :: ApplicationVersionDescription -> Maybe S3Location

-- | If the version's source code was retrieved from AWS CodeCommit, the
--   location of the source code for the application version.
[$sel:sourceBuildInformation:ApplicationVersionDescription'] :: ApplicationVersionDescription -> Maybe SourceBuildInformation

-- | A unique identifier for the application version.
[$sel:versionLabel:ApplicationVersionDescription'] :: ApplicationVersionDescription -> Maybe Text

--   the application version.</li>

--   AWS CodeBuild build.</li>

-- | The application version lifecycle settings for an application. Defines
--   the rules that Elastic Beanstalk applies to an application's versions
--   in order to avoid hitting the per-region limit for application
--   versions.
--   
--   When Elastic Beanstalk deletes an application version from its
--   database, you can no longer deploy that version to an environment. The
--   source bundle remains in S3 unless you configure the rule to delete
--   it.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newApplicationVersionLifecycleConfig</a> smart
--   constructor.
data ApplicationVersionLifecycleConfig
ApplicationVersionLifecycleConfig' :: Maybe MaxCountRule -> Maybe MaxAgeRule -> ApplicationVersionLifecycleConfig

-- | Specify a max count rule to restrict the number of application
--   versions that are retained for an application.
[$sel:maxCountRule:ApplicationVersionLifecycleConfig'] :: ApplicationVersionLifecycleConfig -> Maybe MaxCountRule

-- | Specify a max age rule to restrict the length of time that application
--   versions are retained for an application.
[$sel:maxAgeRule:ApplicationVersionLifecycleConfig'] :: ApplicationVersionLifecycleConfig -> Maybe MaxAgeRule

-- | Create a value of <a>ApplicationVersionLifecycleConfig</a> with all
--   optional fields omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:maxCountRule:ApplicationVersionLifecycleConfig'</a>,
--   <a>applicationVersionLifecycleConfig_maxCountRule</a> - Specify a max
--   count rule to restrict the number of application versions that are
--   retained for an application.
--   
--   <a>$sel:maxAgeRule:ApplicationVersionLifecycleConfig'</a>,
--   <a>applicationVersionLifecycleConfig_maxAgeRule</a> - Specify a max
--   age rule to restrict the length of time that application versions are
--   retained for an application.
newApplicationVersionLifecycleConfig :: ApplicationVersionLifecycleConfig

-- | Specify a max count rule to restrict the number of application
--   versions that are retained for an application.
applicationVersionLifecycleConfig_maxCountRule :: Lens' ApplicationVersionLifecycleConfig (Maybe MaxCountRule)

-- | Specify a max age rule to restrict the length of time that application
--   versions are retained for an application.
applicationVersionLifecycleConfig_maxAgeRule :: Lens' ApplicationVersionLifecycleConfig (Maybe MaxAgeRule)

-- | Settings for an AWS CodeBuild build.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newBuildConfiguration</a> smart constructor.
data BuildConfiguration
BuildConfiguration' :: Maybe Text -> Maybe Int -> Maybe ComputeType -> Text -> Text -> BuildConfiguration

-- | The name of the artifact of the CodeBuild build. If provided, Elastic
--   Beanstalk stores the build artifact in the S3 location
--   <i>S3-bucket</i>/resources/<i>application-name</i>/codebuild/codebuild-<i>version-label</i>-<i>artifact-name</i>.zip.
--   If not provided, Elastic Beanstalk stores the build artifact in the S3
--   location
--   <i>S3-bucket</i>/resources/<i>application-name</i>/codebuild/codebuild-<i>version-label</i>.zip.
[$sel:artifactName:BuildConfiguration'] :: BuildConfiguration -> Maybe Text

-- | How long in minutes, from 5 to 480 (8 hours), for AWS CodeBuild to
--   wait until timing out any related build that does not get marked as
--   completed. The default is 60 minutes.
[$sel:timeoutInMinutes:BuildConfiguration'] :: BuildConfiguration -> Maybe Int

-- | Information about the compute resources the build project will use.
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li><pre>BUILD_GENERAL1_SMALL: Use up to 3 GB memory and 2 vCPUs for
--   builds</pre></li>
--   <li><pre>BUILD_GENERAL1_MEDIUM: Use up to 7 GB memory and 4 vCPUs for
--   builds</pre></li>
--   <li><pre>BUILD_GENERAL1_LARGE: Use up to 15 GB memory and 8 vCPUs for
--   builds</pre></li>
--   </ul>
[$sel:computeType:BuildConfiguration'] :: BuildConfiguration -> Maybe ComputeType

--   Management (IAM) role that enables AWS CodeBuild to interact with
--   dependent AWS services on behalf of the AWS account.
[$sel:codeBuildServiceRole:BuildConfiguration'] :: BuildConfiguration -> Text

-- | The ID of the Docker image to use for this build project.
[$sel:image:BuildConfiguration'] :: BuildConfiguration -> Text
