-- | Location of the source code for an application version.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newSourceBuildInformation</a> smart constructor.
data SourceBuildInformation
SourceBuildInformation' :: SourceType -> SourceRepository -> Text -> SourceBuildInformation

-- | The type of repository.
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li><pre>Git</pre></li>
--   <li><pre>Zip</pre></li>
--   </ul>
[$sel:sourceType:SourceBuildInformation'] :: SourceBuildInformation -> SourceType

-- | Location where the repository is stored.
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li><pre>CodeCommit</pre></li>
--   <li><pre>S3</pre></li>
--   </ul>
[$sel:sourceRepository:SourceBuildInformation'] :: SourceBuildInformation -> SourceRepository

-- | The location of the source code, as a formatted string, depending on
--   the value of <tt>SourceRepository</tt>
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li>For <tt>CodeCommit</tt>, the format is the repository name and
--   commit ID, separated by a forward slash. For example,
--   <tt>my-git-repo/265cfa0cf6af46153527f55d6503ec030551f57a</tt>.</li>
--   <li>For <tt>S3</tt>, the format is the S3 bucket name and object key,
--   separated by a forward slash. For example,
--   <tt>my-s3-bucket/Folders/my-source-file</tt>.</li>
--   </ul>
[$sel:sourceLocation:SourceBuildInformation'] :: SourceBuildInformation -> Text

-- | Create a value of <a>SourceBuildInformation</a> with all optional
--   fields omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:sourceType:SourceBuildInformation'</a>,
--   <a>sourceBuildInformation_sourceType</a> - The type of repository.
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li><pre>Git</pre></li>
--   <li><pre>Zip</pre></li>
--   </ul>
--   
--   <a>$sel:sourceRepository:SourceBuildInformation'</a>,
--   <a>sourceBuildInformation_sourceRepository</a> - Location where the
--   repository is stored.
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li><pre>CodeCommit</pre></li>
--   <li><pre>S3</pre></li>
--   </ul>
--   
--   <a>$sel:sourceLocation:SourceBuildInformation'</a>,
--   <a>sourceBuildInformation_sourceLocation</a> - The location of the
--   source code, as a formatted string, depending on the value of
--   <tt>SourceRepository</tt>
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li>For <tt>CodeCommit</tt>, the format is the repository name and
--   commit ID, separated by a forward slash. For example,
--   <tt>my-git-repo/265cfa0cf6af46153527f55d6503ec030551f57a</tt>.</li>
--   <li>For <tt>S3</tt>, the format is the S3 bucket name and object key,
--   separated by a forward slash. For example,
--   <tt>my-s3-bucket/Folders/my-source-file</tt>.</li>
--   </ul>
newSourceBuildInformation :: SourceType -> SourceRepository -> Text -> SourceBuildInformation

-- | The type of repository.
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li><pre>Git</pre></li>
--   <li><pre>Zip</pre></li>
--   </ul>
sourceBuildInformation_sourceType :: Lens' SourceBuildInformation SourceType

-- | Location where the repository is stored.
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li><pre>CodeCommit</pre></li>
--   <li><pre>S3</pre></li>
--   </ul>
sourceBuildInformation_sourceRepository :: Lens' SourceBuildInformation SourceRepository

-- | The location of the source code, as a formatted string, depending on
--   the value of <tt>SourceRepository</tt>
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li>For <tt>CodeCommit</tt>, the format is the repository name and
--   commit ID, separated by a forward slash. For example,
--   <tt>my-git-repo/265cfa0cf6af46153527f55d6503ec030551f57a</tt>.</li>
--   <li>For <tt>S3</tt>, the format is the S3 bucket name and object key,
--   separated by a forward slash. For example,
--   <tt>my-s3-bucket/Folders/my-source-file</tt>.</li>
--   </ul>
sourceBuildInformation_sourceLocation :: Lens' SourceBuildInformation Text

-- | A specification for an environment configuration.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newSourceConfiguration</a> smart constructor.
data SourceConfiguration
SourceConfiguration' :: Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> SourceConfiguration

-- | The name of the configuration template.
[$sel:templateName:SourceConfiguration'] :: SourceConfiguration -> Maybe Text

-- | The name of the application associated with the configuration.
[$sel:applicationName:SourceConfiguration'] :: SourceConfiguration -> Maybe Text

--   configuration template.
--   
--   <a>$sel:applicationName:SourceConfiguration'</a>,
--   <a>sourceConfiguration_applicationName</a> - The name of the
--   application associated with the configuration.
newSourceConfiguration :: SourceConfiguration

-- | The name of the configuration template.
sourceConfiguration_templateName :: Lens' SourceConfiguration (Maybe Text)

-- | The name of the application associated with the configuration.
sourceConfiguration_applicationName :: Lens' SourceConfiguration (Maybe Text)

-- | Represents the percentage of requests over the last 10 seconds that
--   resulted in each type of status code response. For more information,
--   see <a>Status Code Definitions</a>.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newStatusCodes</a> smart constructor.
data StatusCodes
StatusCodes' :: Maybe Int -> Maybe Int -> Maybe Int -> Maybe Int -> StatusCodes

-- | The percentage of requests over the last 10 seconds that resulted in a
--   3xx (300, 301, etc.) status code.
[$sel:status3xx:StatusCodes'] :: StatusCodes -> Maybe Int

-- | The percentage of requests over the last 10 seconds that resulted in a
--   5xx (500, 501, etc.) status code.
[$sel:status5xx:StatusCodes'] :: StatusCodes -> Maybe Int

-- | The percentage of requests over the last 10 seconds that resulted in a
--   2xx (200, 201, etc.) status code.
[$sel:status2xx:StatusCodes'] :: StatusCodes -> Maybe Int

-- | The percentage of requests over the last 10 seconds that resulted in a
--   4xx (400, 401, etc.) status code.
[$sel:status4xx:StatusCodes'] :: StatusCodes -> Maybe Int

-- | Create a value of <a>StatusCodes</a> with all optional fields omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:status3xx:StatusCodes'</a>, <a>statusCodes_status3xx</a> - The
--   percentage of requests over the last 10 seconds that resulted in a 3xx
--   (300, 301, etc.) status code.
--   
--   <a>$sel:status5xx:StatusCodes'</a>, <a>statusCodes_status5xx</a> - The
--   percentage of requests over the last 10 seconds that resulted in a 5xx
--   (500, 501, etc.) status code.
--   
--   <a>$sel:status2xx:StatusCodes'</a>, <a>statusCodes_status2xx</a> - The
--   percentage of requests over the last 10 seconds that resulted in a 2xx
--   (200, 201, etc.) status code.
--   
--   <a>$sel:status4xx:StatusCodes'</a>, <a>statusCodes_status4xx</a> - The
--   percentage of requests over the last 10 seconds that resulted in a 4xx
--   (400, 401, etc.) status code.
newStatusCodes :: StatusCodes

-- | The percentage of requests over the last 10 seconds that resulted in a
--   3xx (300, 301, etc.) status code.
statusCodes_status3xx :: Lens' StatusCodes (Maybe Int)

-- | The percentage of requests over the last 10 seconds that resulted in a
--   5xx (500, 501, etc.) status code.
statusCodes_status5xx :: Lens' StatusCodes (Maybe Int)

-- | The percentage of requests over the last 10 seconds that resulted in a
--   2xx (200, 201, etc.) status code.
statusCodes_status2xx :: Lens' StatusCodes (Maybe Int)

-- | The percentage of requests over the last 10 seconds that resulted in a
--   4xx (400, 401, etc.) status code.
statusCodes_status4xx :: Lens' StatusCodes (Maybe Int)

-- | CPU utilization and load average metrics for an Amazon EC2 instance.
--

data SystemStatus

-- | CPU utilization metrics for the instance.

--   For more information, see <a>Operating System Metrics</a>.

systemStatus_loadAverage :: Lens' SystemStatus (Maybe [Double])

-- | An error or warning for a desired configuration option value.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newValidationMessage</a> smart constructor.
data ValidationMessage
ValidationMessage' :: Maybe Text -> Maybe ValidationSeverity -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> ValidationMessage

-- | The name of the option.
[$sel:optionName:ValidationMessage'] :: ValidationMessage -> Maybe Text

-- | An indication of the severity of this message:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li><tt>error</tt>: This message indicates that this is not a valid
--   setting for an option.</li>
--   <li><tt>warning</tt>: This message is providing information you should
--   take into account.</li>
--   </ul>
[$sel:severity:ValidationMessage'] :: ValidationMessage -> Maybe ValidationSeverity

-- | A message describing the error or warning.
[$sel:message:ValidationMessage'] :: ValidationMessage -> Maybe Text

-- | The namespace to which the option belongs.
[$sel:namespace:ValidationMessage'] :: ValidationMessage -> Maybe Text

-- | Create a value of <a>ValidationMessage</a> with all optional fields
--   omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:optionName:ValidationMessage'</a>,
--   <a>validationMessage_optionName</a> - The name of the option.
--   
--   <a>$sel:severity:ValidationMessage'</a>,
--   <a>validationMessage_severity</a> - An indication of the severity of
--   this message:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li><tt>error</tt>: This message indicates that this is not a valid
--   setting for an option.</li>
--   <li><tt>warning</tt>: This message is providing information you should
--   take into account.</li>
--   </ul>
--   
--   <a>$sel:message:ValidationMessage'</a>,
--   <a>validationMessage_message</a> - A message describing the error or
--   warning.
--   
--   <a>$sel:namespace:ValidationMessage'</a>,
--   <a>validationMessage_namespace</a> - The namespace to which the option
--   belongs.
newValidationMessage :: ValidationMessage

-- | The name of the option.
validationMessage_optionName :: Lens' ValidationMessage (Maybe Text)

-- | An indication of the severity of this message:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li><tt>error</tt>: This message indicates that this is not a valid
--   setting for an option.</li>
--   <li><tt>warning</tt>: This message is providing information you should
--   take into account.</li>
--   </ul>
validationMessage_severity :: Lens' ValidationMessage (Maybe ValidationSeverity)

-- | A message describing the error or warning.
validationMessage_message :: Lens' ValidationMessage (Maybe Text)

-- | The namespace to which the option belongs.
validationMessage_namespace :: Lens' ValidationMessage (Maybe Text)


-- | Terminates the specified environment.
module Network.AWS.ElasticBeanstalk.TerminateEnvironment

-- | Request to terminate an environment.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newTerminateEnvironment</a> smart constructor.
data TerminateEnvironment
TerminateEnvironment' :: Maybe Bool -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Bool -> Maybe Text -> TerminateEnvironment

-- | Terminates the target environment even if another environment in the
--   same group is dependent on it.
[$sel:forceTerminate:TerminateEnvironment'] :: TerminateEnvironment -> Maybe Bool

-- | The ID of the environment to terminate.
--   
--   Condition: You must specify either this or an EnvironmentName, or
--   both. If you do not specify either, AWS Elastic Beanstalk returns
--   <tt>MissingRequiredParameter</tt> error.
[$sel:environmentId:TerminateEnvironment'] :: TerminateEnvironment -> Maybe Text

-- | Indicates whether the associated AWS resources should shut down when
--   the environment is terminated:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li><tt>true</tt>: The specified environment as well as the associated
--   AWS resources, such as Auto Scaling group and LoadBalancer, are
--   terminated.</li>
--   <li><tt>false</tt>: AWS Elastic Beanstalk resource management is
--   removed from the environment, but the AWS resources continue to
--   operate.</li>
--   </ul>
--   
--   For more information, see the <a>AWS Elastic Beanstalk User Guide.</a>
--   
--   Default: <tt>true</tt>
--   
--   Valid Values: <tt>true</tt> | <tt>false</tt>
[$sel:terminateResources:TerminateEnvironment'] :: TerminateEnvironment -> Maybe Bool

-- | The name of the environment to terminate.
--   
--   Condition: You must specify either this or an EnvironmentId, or both.
--   If you do not specify either, AWS Elastic Beanstalk returns
--   <tt>MissingRequiredParameter</tt> error.
[$sel:environmentName:TerminateEnvironment'] :: TerminateEnvironment -> Maybe Text

-- | Create a value of <a>TerminateEnvironment</a> with all optional fields
--   omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:forceTerminate:TerminateEnvironment'</a>,
--   <a>terminateEnvironment_forceTerminate</a> - Terminates the target
--   environment even if another environment in the same group is dependent
--   on it.
--   
--   <a>$sel:environmentId:TerminateEnvironment'</a>,
--   <a>terminateEnvironment_environmentId</a> - The ID of the environment
--   to terminate.
--   
--   Condition: You must specify either this or an EnvironmentName, or
--   both. If you do not specify either, AWS Elastic Beanstalk returns
--   <tt>MissingRequiredParameter</tt> error.
--   
--   <a>$sel:terminateResources:TerminateEnvironment'</a>,
--   <a>terminateEnvironment_terminateResources</a> - Indicates whether the
--   associated AWS resources should shut down when the environment is
--   terminated:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li><tt>true</tt>: The specified environment as well as the associated
--   AWS resources, such as Auto Scaling group and LoadBalancer, are
--   terminated.</li>
--   <li><tt>false</tt>: AWS Elastic Beanstalk resource management is
--   removed from the environment, but the AWS resources continue to
--   operate.</li>
--   </ul>
--   
--   For more information, see the <a>AWS Elastic Beanstalk User Guide.</a>
--   
--   Default: <tt>true</tt>
--   
--   Valid Values: <tt>true</tt> | <tt>false</tt>
--   
--   <a>$sel:environmentName:TerminateEnvironment'</a>,
--   <a>terminateEnvironment_environmentName</a> - The name of the
--   environment to terminate.
--   
--   Condition: You must specify either this or an EnvironmentId, or both.
--   If you do not specify either, AWS Elastic Beanstalk returns
--   <tt>MissingRequiredParameter</tt> error.
newTerminateEnvironment :: TerminateEnvironment

-- | Terminates the target environment even if another environment in the
--   same group is dependent on it.
terminateEnvironment_forceTerminate :: Lens' TerminateEnvironment (Maybe Bool)

-- | The ID of the environment to terminate.
--   
--   Condition: You must specify either this or an EnvironmentName, or
--   both. If you do not specify either, AWS Elastic Beanstalk returns
--   <tt>MissingRequiredParameter</tt> error.
terminateEnvironment_environmentId :: Lens' TerminateEnvironment (Maybe Text)

-- | Indicates whether the associated AWS resources should shut down when
--   the environment is terminated:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li><tt>true</tt>: The specified environment as well as the associated
--   AWS resources, such as Auto Scaling group and LoadBalancer, are
--   terminated.</li>
--   <li><tt>false</tt>: AWS Elastic Beanstalk resource management is
--   removed from the environment, but the AWS resources continue to
--   operate.</li>
--   </ul>
--   
--   For more information, see the <a>AWS Elastic Beanstalk User Guide.</a>
--   
--   Default: <tt>true</tt>
--   
--   Valid Values: <tt>true</tt> | <tt>false</tt>
terminateEnvironment_terminateResources :: Lens' TerminateEnvironment (Maybe Bool)

-- | The name of the environment to terminate.
--   
--   Condition: You must specify either this or an EnvironmentId, or both.
--   If you do not specify either, AWS Elastic Beanstalk returns
--   <tt>MissingRequiredParameter</tt> error.
terminateEnvironment_environmentName :: Lens' TerminateEnvironment (Maybe Text)

-- | Describes the properties of an environment.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newEnvironmentDescription</a> smart constructor.
data EnvironmentDescription
EnvironmentDescription' :: Maybe Bool -> Maybe Text -> Maybe EnvironmentStatus -> Maybe ISO8601 -> Maybe [EnvironmentLink] -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe EnvironmentHealth -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe ISO8601 -> Maybe EnvironmentResourcesDescription -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe EnvironmentHealthStatus -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe EnvironmentTier -> Maybe Text -> EnvironmentDescription

-- | Indicates if there is an in-progress environment configuration update
--   or application version deployment that you can cancel.
--   
--   <tt>true:</tt> There is an update in progress.
--   
--   <tt>false:</tt> There are no updates currently in progress.
[$sel:abortableOperationInProgress:EnvironmentDescription'] :: EnvironmentDescription -> Maybe Bool

-- | The name of the configuration template used to originally launch this
--   environment.
[$sel:templateName:EnvironmentDescription'] :: EnvironmentDescription -> Maybe Text

-- | The current operational status of the environment:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li><tt>Launching</tt>: Environment is in the process of initial
--   deployment.</li>
--   <li><tt>Updating</tt>: Environment is in the process of updating its
--   configuration settings or application version.</li>
--   <li><tt>Ready</tt>: Environment is available to have an action
--   performed on it, such as update or terminate.</li>
--   <li><tt>Terminating</tt>: Environment is in the shut-down
--   process.</li>
--   <li><tt>Terminated</tt>: Environment is not running.</li>
--   </ul>
[$sel:status:EnvironmentDescription'] :: EnvironmentDescription -> Maybe EnvironmentStatus

-- | The creation date for this environment.
[$sel:dateCreated:EnvironmentDescription'] :: EnvironmentDescription -> Maybe ISO8601

-- | A list of links to other environments in the same group.
[$sel:environmentLinks:EnvironmentDescription'] :: EnvironmentDescription -> Maybe [EnvironmentLink]

-- | The ID of this environment.
[$sel:environmentId:EnvironmentDescription'] :: EnvironmentDescription -> Maybe Text

-- | The name of the <tt>SolutionStack</tt> deployed with this environment.
[$sel:solutionStackName:EnvironmentDescription'] :: EnvironmentDescription -> Maybe Text

-- | The ARN of the platform version.
[$sel:platformArn:EnvironmentDescription'] :: EnvironmentDescription -> Maybe Text

-- | The name of this environment.
[$sel:environmentName:EnvironmentDescription'] :: EnvironmentDescription -> Maybe Text

-- | Describes the health status of the environment. AWS Elastic Beanstalk
--   indicates the failure levels for a running environment:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li><tt>Red</tt>: Indicates the environment is not responsive. Occurs
--   when three or more consecutive failures occur for an environment.</li>
--   <li><tt>Yellow</tt>: Indicates that something is wrong. Occurs when
--   two consecutive failures occur for an environment.</li>
--   <li><tt>Green</tt>: Indicates the environment is healthy and fully
--   functional.</li>
--   <li><tt>Grey</tt>: Default health for a new environment. The
--   environment is not fully launched and health checks have not started
--   or health checks are suspended during an <tt>UpdateEnvironment</tt> or
--   <tt>RestartEnvironment</tt> request.</li>
--   </ul>
--   
--   Default: <tt>Grey</tt>
[$sel:health:EnvironmentDescription'] :: EnvironmentDescription -> Maybe EnvironmentHealth

-- | The application version deployed in this environment.
[$sel:versionLabel:EnvironmentDescription'] :: EnvironmentDescription -> Maybe Text

-- | The URL to the CNAME for this environment.
[$sel:cname:EnvironmentDescription'] :: EnvironmentDescription -> Maybe Text

-- | The last modified date for this environment.
[$sel:dateUpdated:EnvironmentDescription'] :: EnvironmentDescription -> Maybe ISO8601

-- | The description of the AWS resources used by this environment.
[$sel:resources:EnvironmentDescription'] :: EnvironmentDescription -> Maybe EnvironmentResourcesDescription

-- | Describes this environment.
[$sel:description:EnvironmentDescription'] :: EnvironmentDescription -> Maybe Text

-- | For load-balanced, autoscaling environments, the URL to the
--   LoadBalancer. For single-instance environments, the IP address of the
--   instance.
[$sel:endpointURL:EnvironmentDescription'] :: EnvironmentDescription -> Maybe Text

-- | Returns the health status of the application running in your
--   environment. For more information, see <a>Health Colors and
--   Statuses</a>.
[$sel:healthStatus:EnvironmentDescription'] :: EnvironmentDescription -> Maybe EnvironmentHealthStatus

-- | The environment's Amazon Resource Name (ARN), which can be used in
--   other API requests that require an ARN.
[$sel:environmentArn:EnvironmentDescription'] :: EnvironmentDescription -> Maybe Text

-- | The name of the application associated with this environment.
[$sel:applicationName:EnvironmentDescription'] :: EnvironmentDescription -> Maybe Text

-- | Describes the current tier of this environment.
[$sel:tier:EnvironmentDescription'] :: EnvironmentDescription -> Maybe EnvironmentTier

-- | The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the environment's operations role.
--   For more information, see <a>Operations roles</a> in the <i>AWS
--   Elastic Beanstalk Developer Guide</i>.
[$sel:operationsRole:EnvironmentDescription'] :: EnvironmentDescription -> Maybe Text

-- | Create a value of <a>EnvironmentDescription</a> with all optional
--   fields omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:abortableOperationInProgress:EnvironmentDescription'</a>,
--   <a>environmentDescription_abortableOperationInProgress</a> - Indicates
--   if there is an in-progress environment configuration update or
--   application version deployment that you can cancel.
--   
--   <tt>true:</tt> There is an update in progress.
--   
--   <tt>false:</tt> There are no updates currently in progress.
--   
--   <a>$sel:templateName:EnvironmentDescription'</a>,
--   <a>environmentDescription_templateName</a> - The name of the
--   configuration template used to originally launch this environment.
--   
--   <a>$sel:status:EnvironmentDescription'</a>,
--   <a>environmentDescription_status</a> - The current operational status
--   of the environment:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li><tt>Launching</tt>: Environment is in the process of initial
--   deployment.</li>
--   <li><tt>Updating</tt>: Environment is in the process of updating its
--   configuration settings or application version.</li>
--   <li><tt>Ready</tt>: Environment is available to have an action
--   performed on it, such as update or terminate.</li>
--   <li><tt>Terminating</tt>: Environment is in the shut-down
--   process.</li>
--   <li><tt>Terminated</tt>: Environment is not running.</li>
--   </ul>
--   
--   <a>$sel:dateCreated:EnvironmentDescription'</a>,
--   <a>environmentDescription_dateCreated</a> - The creation date for this
--   environment.
--   
--   <a>$sel:environmentLinks:EnvironmentDescription'</a>,
--   <a>environmentDescription_environmentLinks</a> - A list of links to
--   other environments in the same group.
--   
--   <a>$sel:environmentId:EnvironmentDescription'</a>,
--   <a>environmentDescription_environmentId</a> - The ID of this
--   environment.
--   
--   <a>$sel:solutionStackName:EnvironmentDescription'</a>,
--   <a>environmentDescription_solutionStackName</a> - The name of the
--   <tt>SolutionStack</tt> deployed with this environment.
--   
--   <a>$sel:platformArn:EnvironmentDescription'</a>,
--   <a>environmentDescription_platformArn</a> - The ARN of the platform
--   version.
--   
--   <a>$sel:environmentName:EnvironmentDescription'</a>,
--   <a>environmentDescription_environmentName</a> - The name of this
--   environment.
--   
--   <a>$sel:health:EnvironmentDescription'</a>,
--   <a>environmentDescription_health</a> - Describes the health status of
--   the environment. AWS Elastic Beanstalk indicates the failure levels
--   for a running environment:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li><tt>Red</tt>: Indicates the environment is not responsive. Occurs
--   when three or more consecutive failures occur for an environment.</li>
--   <li><tt>Yellow</tt>: Indicates that something is wrong. Occurs when
--   two consecutive failures occur for an environment.</li>
--   <li><tt>Green</tt>: Indicates the environment is healthy and fully
--   functional.</li>
--   <li><tt>Grey</tt>: Default health for a new environment. The
--   environment is not fully launched and health checks have not started
--   or health checks are suspended during an <tt>UpdateEnvironment</tt> or
--   <tt>RestartEnvironment</tt> request.</li>
--   </ul>
--   
--   Default: <tt>Grey</tt>
--   
--   <a>$sel:versionLabel:EnvironmentDescription'</a>,
--   <a>environmentDescription_versionLabel</a> - The application version
--   deployed in this environment.
--   
--   <a>$sel:cname:EnvironmentDescription'</a>,
--   <a>environmentDescription_cname</a> - The URL to the CNAME for this
--   environment.
--   
--   <a>$sel:dateUpdated:EnvironmentDescription'</a>,
--   <a>environmentDescription_dateUpdated</a> - The last modified date for
--   this environment.
--   
--   <a>$sel:resources:EnvironmentDescription'</a>,
--   <a>environmentDescription_resources</a> - The description of the AWS
--   resources used by this environment.
--   
--   <a>$sel:description:EnvironmentDescription'</a>,
--   <a>environmentDescription_description</a> - Describes this
--   environment.
--   
--   <a>$sel:endpointURL:EnvironmentDescription'</a>,
--   <a>environmentDescription_endpointURL</a> - For load-balanced,
--   autoscaling environments, the URL to the LoadBalancer. For
--   single-instance environments, the IP address of the instance.
--   
--   <a>$sel:healthStatus:EnvironmentDescription'</a>,
--   <a>environmentDescription_healthStatus</a> - Returns the health status
--   of the application running in your environment. For more information,
--   see <a>Health Colors and Statuses</a>.
--   
--   <a>$sel:environmentArn:EnvironmentDescription'</a>,
--   <a>environmentDescription_environmentArn</a> - The environment's
--   Amazon Resource Name (ARN), which can be used in other API requests
--   that require an ARN.
--   
--   <a>$sel:applicationName:EnvironmentDescription'</a>,
--   <a>environmentDescription_applicationName</a> - The name of the
--   application associated with this environment.
--   
--   <a>$sel:tier:EnvironmentDescription'</a>,
--   <a>environmentDescription_tier</a> - Describes the current tier of
--   this environment.
--   
--   <a>$sel:operationsRole:EnvironmentDescription'</a>,
--   <a>environmentDescription_operationsRole</a> - The Amazon Resource
--   Name (ARN) of the environment's operations role. For more information,
--   see <a>Operations roles</a> in the <i>AWS Elastic Beanstalk Developer
--   Guide</i>.
newEnvironmentDescription :: EnvironmentDescription

-- | Indicates if there is an in-progress environment configuration update
--   or application version deployment that you can cancel.
--   
--   <tt>true:</tt> There is an update in progress.
--   
--   <tt>false:</tt> There are no updates currently in progress.
environmentDescription_abortableOperationInProgress :: Lens' EnvironmentDescription (Maybe Bool)

-- | The name of the configuration template used to originally launch this
--   environment.
environmentDescription_templateName :: Lens' EnvironmentDescription (Maybe Text)

-- | The current operational status of the environment:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li><tt>Launching</tt>: Environment is in the process of initial
--   deployment.</li>
--   <li><tt>Updating</tt>: Environment is in the process of updating its
--   configuration settings or application version.</li>
--   <li><tt>Ready</tt>: Environment is available to have an action
--   performed on it, such as update or terminate.</li>
--   <li><tt>Terminating</tt>: Environment is in the shut-down
--   process.</li>
--   <li><tt>Terminated</tt>: Environment is not running.</li>
--   </ul>
environmentDescription_status :: Lens' EnvironmentDescription (Maybe EnvironmentStatus)

-- | The creation date for this environment.
environmentDescription_dateCreated :: Lens' EnvironmentDescription (Maybe UTCTime)

-- | A list of links to other environments in the same group.
environmentDescription_environmentLinks :: Lens' EnvironmentDescription (Maybe [EnvironmentLink])

-- | The ID of this environment.
environmentDescription_environmentId :: Lens' EnvironmentDescription (Maybe Text)

-- | The name of the <tt>SolutionStack</tt> deployed with this environment.
environmentDescription_solutionStackName :: Lens' EnvironmentDescription (Maybe Text)

-- | The ARN of the platform version.
environmentDescription_platformArn :: Lens' EnvironmentDescription (Maybe Text)

-- | The name of this environment.
environmentDescription_environmentName :: Lens' EnvironmentDescription (Maybe Text)

-- | Describes the health status of the environment. AWS Elastic Beanstalk
--   indicates the failure levels for a running environment:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li><tt>Red</tt>: Indicates the environment is not responsive. Occurs
--   when three or more consecutive failures occur for an environment.</li>
--   <li><tt>Yellow</tt>: Indicates that something is wrong. Occurs when
--   two consecutive failures occur for an environment.</li>
--   <li><tt>Green</tt>: Indicates the environment is healthy and fully
--   functional.</li>
--   <li><tt>Grey</tt>: Default health for a new environment. The
--   environment is not fully launched and health checks have not started
--   or health checks are suspended during an <tt>UpdateEnvironment</tt> or
--   <tt>RestartEnvironment</tt> request.</li>
--   </ul>
--   
--   Default: <tt>Grey</tt>
environmentDescription_health :: Lens' EnvironmentDescription (Maybe EnvironmentHealth)

-- | The application version deployed in this environment.
environmentDescription_versionLabel :: Lens' EnvironmentDescription (Maybe Text)

-- | The URL to the CNAME for this environment.
environmentDescription_cname :: Lens' EnvironmentDescription (Maybe Text)

-- | The last modified date for this environment.
environmentDescription_dateUpdated :: Lens' EnvironmentDescription (Maybe UTCTime)

-- | The description of the AWS resources used by this environment.
environmentDescription_resources :: Lens' EnvironmentDescription (Maybe EnvironmentResourcesDescription)

-- | Describes this environment.
environmentDescription_description :: Lens' EnvironmentDescription (Maybe Text)

-- | For load-balanced, autoscaling environments, the URL to the
--   LoadBalancer. For single-instance environments, the IP address of the
--   instance.
environmentDescription_endpointURL :: Lens' EnvironmentDescription (Maybe Text)

-- | Returns the health status of the application running in your
--   environment. For more information, see <a>Health Colors and
--   Statuses</a>.
environmentDescription_healthStatus :: Lens' EnvironmentDescription (Maybe EnvironmentHealthStatus)

-- | The environment's Amazon Resource Name (ARN), which can be used in
--   other API requests that require an ARN.
environmentDescription_environmentArn :: Lens' EnvironmentDescription (Maybe Text)

-- | The name of the application associated with this environment.
environmentDescription_applicationName :: Lens' EnvironmentDescription (Maybe Text)

-- | Describes the current tier of this environment.
environmentDescription_tier :: Lens' EnvironmentDescription (Maybe EnvironmentTier)

-- | The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the environment's operations role.
--   For more information, see <a>Operations roles</a> in the <i>AWS
--   Elastic Beanstalk Developer Guide</i>.
environmentDescription_operationsRole :: Lens' EnvironmentDescription (Maybe Text)
instance GHC.Generics.Generic Network.AWS.ElasticBeanstalk.TerminateEnvironment.TerminateEnvironment
instance GHC.Show.Show Network.AWS.ElasticBeanstalk.TerminateEnvironment.TerminateEnvironment
instance GHC.Read.Read Network.AWS.ElasticBeanstalk.TerminateEnvironment.TerminateEnvironment

-- | Swaps the CNAMEs of two environments.
module Network.AWS.ElasticBeanstalk.SwapEnvironmentCNAMEs

-- | Swaps the CNAMEs of two environments.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newSwapEnvironmentCNAMEs</a> smart constructor.
data SwapEnvironmentCNAMEs
SwapEnvironmentCNAMEs' :: Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> SwapEnvironmentCNAMEs

-- | The name of the source environment.
--   
--   Condition: You must specify at least the <tt>SourceEnvironmentID</tt>
--   or the <tt>SourceEnvironmentName</tt>. You may also specify both. If
--   you specify the <tt>SourceEnvironmentName</tt>, you must specify the
--   <tt>DestinationEnvironmentName</tt>.
[$sel:sourceEnvironmentName:SwapEnvironmentCNAMEs'] :: SwapEnvironmentCNAMEs -> Maybe Text

-- | The ID of the destination environment.
--   
--   Condition: You must specify at least the
--   <tt>DestinationEnvironmentID</tt> or the
--   <tt>DestinationEnvironmentName</tt>. You may also specify both. You
--   must specify the <tt>SourceEnvironmentId</tt> with the
--   <tt>DestinationEnvironmentId</tt>.
[$sel:destinationEnvironmentId:SwapEnvironmentCNAMEs'] :: SwapEnvironmentCNAMEs -> Maybe Text

-- | The name of the destination environment.
--   
--   Condition: You must specify at least the
--   <tt>DestinationEnvironmentID</tt> or the
--   <tt>DestinationEnvironmentName</tt>. You may also specify both. You
--   must specify the <tt>SourceEnvironmentName</tt> with the
--   <tt>DestinationEnvironmentName</tt>.
[$sel:destinationEnvironmentName:SwapEnvironmentCNAMEs'] :: SwapEnvironmentCNAMEs -> Maybe Text

-- | The ID of the source environment.
--   
--   Condition: You must specify at least the <tt>SourceEnvironmentID</tt>
--   or the <tt>SourceEnvironmentName</tt>. You may also specify both. If
--   you specify the <tt>SourceEnvironmentId</tt>, you must specify the
--   <tt>DestinationEnvironmentId</tt>.
[$sel:sourceEnvironmentId:SwapEnvironmentCNAMEs'] :: SwapEnvironmentCNAMEs -> Maybe Text

-- | Create a value of <a>SwapEnvironmentCNAMEs</a> with all optional
--   fields omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.

-- | Retrieves the compiled information from a RequestEnvironmentInfo
--   request.
--   
--   Related Topics
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li>RequestEnvironmentInfo</li>
--   </ul>
module Network.AWS.ElasticBeanstalk.RetrieveEnvironmentInfo

--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newRetrieveEnvironmentInfo</a> smart constructor.
data RetrieveEnvironmentInfo
RetrieveEnvironmentInfo' :: Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> EnvironmentInfoType -> RetrieveEnvironmentInfo

-- | The ID of the data's environment.
--   
--   If no such environment is found, returns an
--   <tt>InvalidParameterValue</tt> error.
--   
--   Condition: You must specify either this or an EnvironmentName, or
--   both. If you do not specify either, AWS Elastic Beanstalk returns
--   <tt>MissingRequiredParameter</tt> error.
[$sel:environmentId:RetrieveEnvironmentInfo'] :: RetrieveEnvironmentInfo -> Maybe Text

-- | The name of the data's environment.
--   
--   If no such environment is found, returns an
--   <tt>InvalidParameterValue</tt> error.
--   
--   Condition: You must specify either this or an EnvironmentId, or both.
--   If you do not specify either, AWS Elastic Beanstalk returns
--   <tt>MissingRequiredParameter</tt> error.
[$sel:environmentName:RetrieveEnvironmentInfo'] :: RetrieveEnvironmentInfo -> Maybe Text

-- | The type of information to retrieve.
[$sel:infoType:RetrieveEnvironmentInfo'] :: RetrieveEnvironmentInfo -> EnvironmentInfoType

-- | Create a value of <a>RetrieveEnvironmentInfo</a> with all optional
--   fields omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:

--   environment.
--   
--   If no such environment is found, returns an
--   <tt>InvalidParameterValue</tt> error.
--   
--   Condition: You must specify either this or an EnvironmentName, or
--   both. If you do not specify either, AWS Elastic Beanstalk returns
--   <tt>MissingRequiredParameter</tt> error.
--   
--   <a>$sel:environmentName:RetrieveEnvironmentInfo'</a>,
--   <a>retrieveEnvironmentInfo_environmentName</a> - The name of the
--   data's environment.
--   
--   If no such environment is found, returns an
--   <tt>InvalidParameterValue</tt> error.
--   
--   Condition: You must specify either this or an EnvironmentId, or both.
--   If you do not specify either, AWS Elastic Beanstalk returns
--   <tt>MissingRequiredParameter</tt> error.
--   
--   <a>$sel:infoType:RetrieveEnvironmentInfo'</a>,

--   retrieve.

--   
--   If no such environment is found, returns an
--   <tt>InvalidParameterValue</tt> error.
--

--   both. If you do not specify either, AWS Elastic Beanstalk returns
--   <tt>MissingRequiredParameter</tt> error.
retrieveEnvironmentInfo_environmentId :: Lens' RetrieveEnvironmentInfo (Maybe Text)

--

-- | Initiates a request to compile the specified type of information of
--   the deployed environment.
--   
--   Setting the <tt>InfoType</tt> to <tt>tail</tt> compiles the last lines
--   from the application server log files of every Amazon EC2 instance in
--   your environment.
--   
--   Setting the <tt>InfoType</tt> to <tt>bundle</tt> compresses the
--   application server log files for every Amazon EC2 instance into a
--   <tt>.zip</tt> file. Legacy and .NET containers do not support bundle
--   logs.
--   
--   Use RetrieveEnvironmentInfo to obtain the set of logs.
--   
--   Related Topics
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li>RetrieveEnvironmentInfo</li>
--   </ul>
module Network.AWS.ElasticBeanstalk.RequestEnvironmentInfo

-- | Request to retrieve logs from an environment and store them in your
--   Elastic Beanstalk storage bucket.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newRequestEnvironmentInfo</a> smart constructor.
data RequestEnvironmentInfo
RequestEnvironmentInfo' :: Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> EnvironmentInfoType -> RequestEnvironmentInfo

-- | The ID of the environment of the requested data.
--   
--   If no such environment is found, <tt>RequestEnvironmentInfo</tt>
--   returns an <tt>InvalidParameterValue</tt> error.
--   
--   Condition: You must specify either this or an EnvironmentName, or
--   both. If you do not specify either, AWS Elastic Beanstalk returns
--   <tt>MissingRequiredParameter</tt> error.
[$sel:environmentId:RequestEnvironmentInfo'] :: RequestEnvironmentInfo -> Maybe Text

-- | The name of the environment of the requested data.
--   
--   If no such environment is found, <tt>RequestEnvironmentInfo</tt>
--   returns an <tt>InvalidParameterValue</tt> error.
--   
--   Condition: You must specify either this or an EnvironmentId, or both.
--   If you do not specify either, AWS Elastic Beanstalk returns
--   <tt>MissingRequiredParameter</tt> error.
[$sel:environmentName:RequestEnvironmentInfo'] :: RequestEnvironmentInfo -> Maybe Text

-- | The type of information to request.
[$sel:infoType:RequestEnvironmentInfo'] :: RequestEnvironmentInfo -> EnvironmentInfoType

-- | Create a value of <a>RequestEnvironmentInfo</a> with all optional
--   fields omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:environmentId:RequestEnvironmentInfo'</a>,
--   <a>requestEnvironmentInfo_environmentId</a> - The ID of the
--   environment of the requested data.
--   
--   If no such environment is found, <tt>RequestEnvironmentInfo</tt>
--   returns an <tt>InvalidParameterValue</tt> error.
--   
--   Condition: You must specify either this or an EnvironmentName, or
--   both. If you do not specify either, AWS Elastic Beanstalk returns
--   <tt>MissingRequiredParameter</tt> error.
--

--   
--   This operation returns paginated results.

--   
--   If no <tt>NextToken</tt> is specified, the first page is retrieved.

-- | Criteria for restricting the resulting list of platform versions. The
--   filter is interpreted as a logical conjunction (AND) of the separate
--   <tt>PlatformFilter</tt> terms.
[$sel:filters:ListPlatformVersions'] :: ListPlatformVersions -> Maybe [PlatformFilter]

-- | Lists the platform branches available for your account in an AWS
--   Region. Provides summary information about each platform branch.
--   
--   For definitions of platform branch and other platform-related terms,
--   see <a>AWS Elastic Beanstalk Platforms Glossary</a>.
module Network.AWS.ElasticBeanstalk.ListPlatformBranches

-- | <i>See:</i> <a>newListPlatformBranches</a> smart constructor.
data ListPlatformBranches
ListPlatformBranches' :: Maybe Text -> Maybe [SearchFilter] -> Maybe Natural -> ListPlatformBranches

-- | For a paginated request. Specify a token from a previous response page
--   to retrieve the next response page. All other parameter values must be
--   identical to the ones specified in the initial request.
--   
--   If no <tt>NextToken</tt> is specified, the first page is retrieved.
[$sel:nextToken:ListPlatformBranches'] :: ListPlatformBranches -> Maybe Text

-- | Criteria for restricting the resulting list of platform branches. The
--   filter is evaluated as a logical conjunction (AND) of the separate
--   <tt>SearchFilter</tt> terms.
--   
--   The following list shows valid attribute values for each of the
--   <tt>SearchFilter</tt> terms. Most operators take a single value. The
--   <tt>in</tt> and <tt>not_in</tt> operators can take multiple values.
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li><tt>Attribute = BranchName</tt>:<ul><li><tt>Operator</tt>:
--   <tt>=</tt> | <tt>!=</tt> | <tt>begins_with</tt> | <tt>ends_with</tt> |
--   <tt>contains</tt> | <tt>in</tt> | <tt>not_in</tt></li></ul></li>
--   <li><tt>Attribute = LifecycleState</tt>:<ul><li><tt>Operator</tt>:
--   <tt>=</tt> | <tt>!=</tt> | <tt>in</tt> |
--   <tt>not_in</tt></li><li><tt>Values</tt>: <tt>beta</tt> |
--   <tt>supported</tt> | <tt>deprecated</tt> |
--   <tt>retired</tt></li></ul></li>
--   <li><tt>Attribute = PlatformName</tt>:<ul><li><tt>Operator</tt>:
--   <tt>=</tt> | <tt>!=</tt> | <tt>begins_with</tt> | <tt>ends_with</tt> |
--   <tt>contains</tt> | <tt>in</tt> | <tt>not_in</tt></li></ul></li>
--   <li><tt>Attribute = TierType</tt>:<ul><li><tt>Operator</tt>:
--   <tt>=</tt> | <tt>!=</tt></li><li><tt>Values</tt>:
--   <tt>WebServer/Standard</tt> | <tt>Worker/SQS/HTTP</tt></li></ul></li>
--   </ul>
--   
--   Array size: limited to 10 <tt>SearchFilter</tt> objects.
--   
--   Within each <tt>SearchFilter</tt> item, the <tt>Values</tt> array is
--   limited to 10 items.
[$sel:filters:ListPlatformBranches'] :: ListPlatformBranches -> Maybe [SearchFilter]

-- | The maximum number of platform branch values returned in one call.
[$sel:maxRecords:ListPlatformBranches'] :: ListPlatformBranches -> Maybe Natural

-- | Create a value of <a>ListPlatformBranches</a> with all optional fields

-- | For a paginated request. Specify a token from a previous response page

-- | Criteria for restricting the resulting list of platform branches. The

--   <tt>=</tt> | <tt>!=</tt> | <tt>begins_with</tt> | <tt>ends_with</tt> |
--   <tt>contains</tt> | <tt>in</tt> | <tt>not_in</tt></li></ul></li>
--   <li><tt>Attribute = LifecycleState</tt>:<ul><li><tt>Operator</tt>:
--   <tt>=</tt> | <tt>!=</tt> | <tt>in</tt> |
--   <tt>not_in</tt></li><li><tt>Values</tt>: <tt>beta</tt> |
--   <tt>supported</tt> | <tt>deprecated</tt> |
--   <tt>retired</tt></li></ul></li>
--   <li><tt>Attribute = PlatformName</tt>:<ul><li><tt>Operator</tt>:
--   <tt>=</tt> | <tt>!=</tt> | <tt>begins_with</tt> | <tt>ends_with</tt> |
--   <tt>contains</tt> | <tt>in</tt> | <tt>not_in</tt></li></ul></li>
--   <li><tt>Attribute = TierType</tt>:<ul><li><tt>Operator</tt>:
--   <tt>=</tt> | <tt>!=</tt></li><li><tt>Values</tt>:
--   <tt>WebServer/Standard</tt> | <tt>Worker/SQS/HTTP</tt></li></ul></li>
--   </ul>
--   
--   Array size: limited to 10 <tt>SearchFilter</tt> objects.
--   
--   Within each <tt>SearchFilter</tt> item, the <tt>Values</tt> array is
--   limited to 10 items.
listPlatformBranches_filters :: Lens' ListPlatformBranches (Maybe [SearchFilter])

-- | The maximum number of platform branch values returned in one call.
listPlatformBranches_maxRecords :: Lens' ListPlatformBranches (Maybe Natural)

-- | <i>See:</i> <a>newListPlatformBranchesResponse</a> smart constructor.
data ListPlatformBranchesResponse

--   token that you can pass in a subsequent request to get the next
--   response page.

--   optional fields omitted.

-- | Returns list of event descriptions matching criteria up to the last 6
--   weeks.
--   
--   This action returns the most recent 1,000 events from the specified
--   <tt>NextToken</tt>.
--   
--   This operation returns paginated results.
module Network.AWS.ElasticBeanstalk.DescribeEvents

-- | Request to retrieve a list of events for an environment.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newDescribeEvents</a> smart constructor.
data DescribeEvents
DescribeEvents' :: Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe EventSeverity -> Maybe Text -> Maybe ISO8601 -> Maybe Text -> Maybe ISO8601 -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Natural -> DescribeEvents

-- | If specified, AWS Elastic Beanstalk restricts the returned
--   descriptions to those that are associated with this environment
--   configuration.
[$sel:templateName:DescribeEvents'] :: DescribeEvents -> Maybe Text

-- | Pagination token. If specified, the events return the next batch of
--   results.
[$sel:nextToken:DescribeEvents'] :: DescribeEvents -> Maybe Text

-- | If specified, limits the events returned from this call to include
--   only those with the specified severity or higher.
[$sel:severity:DescribeEvents'] :: DescribeEvents -> Maybe EventSeverity

-- | If specified, AWS Elastic Beanstalk restricts the returned
--   descriptions to those associated with this environment.
[$sel:environmentId:DescribeEvents'] :: DescribeEvents -> Maybe Text

-- | If specified, AWS Elastic Beanstalk restricts the returned
--   descriptions to those that occur on or after this time.
[$sel:startTime:DescribeEvents'] :: DescribeEvents -> Maybe ISO8601

-- | The ARN of a custom platform version. If specified, AWS Elastic
--   Beanstalk restricts the returned descriptions to those associated with
--   this custom platform version.
[$sel:platformArn:DescribeEvents'] :: DescribeEvents -> Maybe Text

-- | If specified, AWS Elastic Beanstalk restricts the returned
--   descriptions to those that occur up to, but not including, the
--   <tt>EndTime</tt>.

-- | Returns descriptions for existing environments.
--   
--   This operation returns paginated results.
module Network.AWS.ElasticBeanstalk.DescribeEnvironments

-- | Request to describe one or more environments.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newDescribeEnvironments</a> smart constructor.
data DescribeEnvironments
DescribeEnvironments' :: Maybe Text -> Maybe [Text] -> Maybe [Text] -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Bool -> Maybe ISO8601 -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Natural -> DescribeEnvironments

-- | For a paginated request. Specify a token from a previous response page
--   to retrieve the next response page. All other parameter values must be
--   identical to the ones specified in the initial request.
--   
--   If no <tt>NextToken</tt> is specified, the first page is retrieved.

--   descriptions to include only those that have the specified names.
[$sel:environmentNames:DescribeEnvironments'] :: DescribeEnvironments -> Maybe [Text]

-- | If specified, AWS Elastic Beanstalk restricts the returned
--   descriptions to include only those that have the specified IDs.

-- | If specified, AWS Elastic Beanstalk restricts the returned

--   application version.
[$sel:versionLabel:DescribeEnvironments'] :: DescribeEnvironments -> Maybe Text

-- | Indicates whether to include deleted environments:
--   
--   <tt>true</tt>: Environments that have been deleted after
--   <tt>IncludedDeletedBackTo</tt> are displayed.
--   
--   <tt>false</tt>: Do not include deleted environments.
[$sel:includeDeleted:DescribeEnvironments'] :: DescribeEnvironments -> Maybe Bool

-- | If specified when <tt>IncludeDeleted</tt> is set to <tt>true</tt>,
--   then environments deleted after this date are displayed.
[$sel:includedDeletedBackTo:DescribeEnvironments'] :: DescribeEnvironments -> Maybe ISO8601

-- | If specified, AWS Elastic Beanstalk restricts the returned
--   descriptions to include only those that are associated with this
--   application.
[$sel:applicationName:DescribeEnvironments'] :: DescribeEnvironments -> Maybe Text

-- | For a paginated request. Specify a maximum number of environments to
--   include in each response.
--   
--   If no <tt>MaxRecords</tt> is specified, all available environments are
--   retrieved in a single response.
[$sel:maxRecords:DescribeEnvironments'] :: DescribeEnvironments -> Maybe Natural

-- | Returns a description of the settings for the specified configuration
--   set, that is, either a configuration template or the configuration set
--   associated with a running environment.
--   
--   When describing the settings for the configuration set associated with
--   a running environment, it is possible to receive two sets of setting
--   descriptions. One is the deployed configuration set, and the other is
--   a draft configuration of an environment that is either in the process
--   of deployment or that failed to deploy.
--   
--   Related Topics
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li>DeleteEnvironmentConfiguration</li>
--   </ul>

-- | Describes the configuration options that are used in a particular
--   configuration template or environment, or that a specified solution
--   stack defines. The description includes the values the options, their
--   default values, and an indication of the required action on a running
--   environment if an option value is changed.
module Network.AWS.ElasticBeanstalk.DescribeConfigurationOptions

-- | Result message containing a list of application version descriptions.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newDescribeConfigurationOptions</a> smart constructor.
data DescribeConfigurationOptions
DescribeConfigurationOptions' :: Maybe Text -> Maybe [OptionSpecification] -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> DescribeConfigurationOptions

-- | The name of the configuration template whose configuration options you
--   want to describe.
[$sel:templateName:DescribeConfigurationOptions'] :: DescribeConfigurationOptions -> Maybe Text

-- | If specified, restricts the descriptions to only the specified
--   options.
[$sel:options:DescribeConfigurationOptions'] :: DescribeConfigurationOptions -> Maybe [OptionSpecification]

--

--   application.

--   versions to include in each response.
--

--   versions are retrieved in a single response.

-- | Deletes the draft configuration associated with the running
--   environment.
--   
--   Updating a running environment with any configuration changes creates
--   a draft configuration set. You can get the draft configuration using
--   DescribeConfigurationSettings while the update is in progress or if
--   the update fails. The <tt>DeploymentStatus</tt> for the draft
--   configuration indicates whether the deployment is in process or has
--   failed. The draft configuration remains in existence until it is
--   deleted with this action.
module Network.AWS.ElasticBeanstalk.DeleteEnvironmentConfiguration

-- | Request to delete a draft environment configuration.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newDeleteEnvironmentConfiguration</a> smart
--   constructor.
data DeleteEnvironmentConfiguration
DeleteEnvironmentConfiguration' :: Text -> Text -> DeleteEnvironmentConfiguration

-- | The name of the application the environment is associated with.
[$sel:applicationName:DeleteEnvironmentConfiguration'] :: DeleteEnvironmentConfiguration -> Text

-- | The name of the environment to delete the draft configuration from.
[$sel:environmentName:DeleteEnvironmentConfiguration'] :: DeleteEnvironmentConfiguration -> Text

-- | Create a value of <a>DeleteEnvironmentConfiguration</a> with all
--   optional fields omitted.

-- | Launches an AWS Elastic Beanstalk environment for the specified
--   application using the specified configuration.
module Network.AWS.ElasticBeanstalk.CreateEnvironment

-- | <i>See:</i> <a>newCreateEnvironment</a> smart constructor.
data CreateEnvironment
CreateEnvironment' :: Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe [OptionSpecification] -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe [Tag] -> Maybe [ConfigurationOptionSetting] -> Maybe Text -> Maybe EnvironmentTier -> Maybe Text -> Text -> CreateEnvironment

-- | The name of the Elastic Beanstalk configuration template to use with
--   the environment.
--   
--   If you specify <tt>TemplateName</tt>, then don't specify
--   <tt>SolutionStackName</tt>.
[$sel:templateName:CreateEnvironment'] :: CreateEnvironment -> Maybe Text

-- | The name of an Elastic Beanstalk solution stack (platform version) to
--   use with the environment. If specified, Elastic Beanstalk sets the
--   configuration values to the default values associated with the
--   specified solution stack. For a list of current solution stacks, see
--   <a>Elastic Beanstalk Supported Platforms</a> in the <i>AWS Elastic
--   Beanstalk Platforms</i> guide.
--   
--   If you specify <tt>SolutionStackName</tt>, don't specify
--   <tt>PlatformArn</tt> or <tt>TemplateName</tt>.
[$sel:solutionStackName:CreateEnvironment'] :: CreateEnvironment -> Maybe Text

-- | The name of the group to which the target environment belongs. Specify
--   a group name only if the environment's name is specified in an
--   environment manifest and not with the environment name parameter. See
--   <a>Environment Manifest (env.yaml)</a> for details.
[$sel:groupName:CreateEnvironment'] :: CreateEnvironment -> Maybe Text

-- | A list of custom user-defined configuration options to remove from the
--   configuration set for this new environment.
[$sel:optionsToRemove:CreateEnvironment'] :: CreateEnvironment -> Maybe [OptionSpecification]

-- | The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the custom platform to use with the
--   environment. For more information, see <a>Custom Platforms</a> in the
--   <i>AWS Elastic Beanstalk Developer Guide</i>.
--   
--   If you specify <tt>PlatformArn</tt>, don't specify
--   <tt>SolutionStackName</tt>.
[$sel:platformArn:CreateEnvironment'] :: CreateEnvironment -> Maybe Text

-- | A unique name for the environment.
--   
--   Constraint: Must be from 4 to 40 characters in length. The name can
--   contain only letters, numbers, and hyphens. It can't start or end with
--   a hyphen. This name must be unique within a region in your account. If
--   the specified name already exists in the region, Elastic Beanstalk
--   returns an <tt>InvalidParameterValue</tt> error.
--   
--   If you don't specify the <tt>CNAMEPrefix</tt> parameter, the
--   environment name becomes part of the CNAME, and therefore part of the
--   visible URL for your application.
[$sel:environmentName:CreateEnvironment'] :: CreateEnvironment -> Maybe Text

-- | If specified, the environment attempts to use this value as the prefix
--   for the CNAME in your Elastic Beanstalk environment URL. If not
--   specified, the CNAME is generated automatically by appending a random
--   alphanumeric string to the environment name.
[$sel:cNAMEPrefix:CreateEnvironment'] :: CreateEnvironment -> Maybe Text

-- | The name of the application version to deploy.
--   
--   Default: If not specified, Elastic Beanstalk attempts to deploy the
--   sample application.
[$sel:versionLabel:CreateEnvironment'] :: CreateEnvironment -> Maybe Text

-- | Specifies the tags applied to resources in the environment.
[$sel:tags:CreateEnvironment'] :: CreateEnvironment -> Maybe [Tag]

-- | If specified, AWS Elastic Beanstalk sets the specified configuration
--   options to the requested value in the configuration set for the new
--   environment. These override the values obtained from the solution
--   stack or the configuration template.
[$sel:optionSettings:CreateEnvironment'] :: CreateEnvironment -> Maybe [ConfigurationOptionSetting]

-- | Your description for this environment.
[$sel:description:CreateEnvironment'] :: CreateEnvironment -> Maybe Text

-- | Specifies the tier to use in creating this environment. The
--   environment tier that you choose determines whether Elastic Beanstalk
--   provisions resources to support a web application that handles HTTP(S)
--   requests or a web application that handles background-processing
--   tasks.
[$sel:tier:CreateEnvironment'] :: CreateEnvironment -> Maybe EnvironmentTier

-- | The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of an existing IAM role to be used as
--   the environment's operations role. If specified, Elastic Beanstalk
--   uses the operations role for permissions to downstream services during
--   this call and during subsequent calls acting on this environment. To
--   specify an operations role, you must have the <tt>iam:PassRole</tt>
--   permission for the role. For more information, see <a>Operations
--   roles</a> in the <i>AWS Elastic Beanstalk Developer Guide</i>.
[$sel:operationsRole:CreateEnvironment'] :: CreateEnvironment -> Maybe Text

-- | The name of the application that is associated with this environment.
[$sel:applicationName:CreateEnvironment'] :: CreateEnvironment -> Text

-- | Create a value of <a>CreateEnvironment</a> with all optional fields
--   omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:templateName:CreateEnvironment'</a>,
--   <a>createEnvironment_templateName</a> - The name of the Elastic
--   Beanstalk configuration template to use with the environment.
--   
--   If you specify <tt>TemplateName</tt>, then don't specify
--   <tt>SolutionStackName</tt>.
--   
--   <a>$sel:solutionStackName:CreateEnvironment'</a>,
--   <a>createEnvironment_solutionStackName</a> - The name of an Elastic
--   Beanstalk solution stack (platform version) to use with the
--   environment. If specified, Elastic Beanstalk sets the configuration
--   values to the default values associated with the specified solution
--   stack. For a list of current solution stacks, see <a>Elastic Beanstalk
--   Supported Platforms</a> in the <i>AWS Elastic Beanstalk Platforms</i>
--   guide.
--   
--   If you specify <tt>SolutionStackName</tt>, don't specify
--   <tt>PlatformArn</tt> or <tt>TemplateName</tt>.
--   
--   <a>$sel:groupName:CreateEnvironment'</a>,
--   <a>createEnvironment_groupName</a> - The name of the group to which
--   the target environment belongs. Specify a group name only if the
--   environment's name is specified in an environment manifest and not
--   with the environment name parameter. See <a>Environment Manifest
--   (env.yaml)</a> for details.
--   
--   <a>$sel:optionsToRemove:CreateEnvironment'</a>,
--   <a>createEnvironment_optionsToRemove</a> - A list of custom
--   user-defined configuration options to remove from the configuration
--   set for this new environment.
--   
--   <a>$sel:platformArn:CreateEnvironment'</a>,
--   <a>createEnvironment_platformArn</a> - The Amazon Resource Name (ARN)
--   of the custom platform to use with the environment. For more
--   information, see <a>Custom Platforms</a> in the <i>AWS Elastic
--   Beanstalk Developer Guide</i>.
--   
--   If you specify <tt>PlatformArn</tt>, don't specify
--   <tt>SolutionStackName</tt>.
--   
--   <a>$sel:environmentName:CreateEnvironment'</a>,
--   <a>createEnvironment_environmentName</a> - A unique name for the
--   environment.
--   
--   Constraint: Must be from 4 to 40 characters in length. The name can
--   contain only letters, numbers, and hyphens. It can't start or end with
--   a hyphen. This name must be unique within a region in your account. If
--   the specified name already exists in the region, Elastic Beanstalk
--   returns an <tt>InvalidParameterValue</tt> error.
--   
--   If you don't specify the <tt>CNAMEPrefix</tt> parameter, the
--   environment name becomes part of the CNAME, and therefore part of the
--   visible URL for your application.
--   
--   <a>$sel:cNAMEPrefix:CreateEnvironment'</a>,
--   <a>createEnvironment_cNAMEPrefix</a> - If specified, the environment
--   attempts to use this value as the prefix for the CNAME in your Elastic
--   Beanstalk environment URL. If not specified, the CNAME is generated
--   automatically by appending a random alphanumeric string to the
--   environment name.
--   
--   <a>$sel:versionLabel:CreateEnvironment'</a>,
--   <a>createEnvironment_versionLabel</a> - The name of the application
--   version to deploy.
--   
--   Default: If not specified, Elastic Beanstalk attempts to deploy the
--   sample application.
--   
--   <a>$sel:tags:CreateEnvironment'</a>, <a>createEnvironment_tags</a> -
--   Specifies the tags applied to resources in the environment.
--   
--   <a>$sel:optionSettings:CreateEnvironment'</a>,
--   <a>createEnvironment_optionSettings</a> - If specified, AWS Elastic
--   Beanstalk sets the specified configuration options to the requested
--   value in the configuration set for the new environment. These override
--   the values obtained from the solution stack or the configuration
--   template.
--   
--   <a>$sel:description:CreateEnvironment'</a>,
--   <a>createEnvironment_description</a> - Your description for this
--   environment.
--   
--   <a>$sel:tier:CreateEnvironment'</a>, <a>createEnvironment_tier</a> -
--   Specifies the tier to use in creating this environment. The
--   environment tier that you choose determines whether Elastic Beanstalk
--   provisions resources to support a web application that handles HTTP(S)
--   requests or a web application that handles background-processing
--   tasks.
--   
--   <a>$sel:operationsRole:CreateEnvironment'</a>,
--   <a>createEnvironment_operationsRole</a> - The Amazon Resource Name
--   (ARN) of an existing IAM role to be used as the environment's
--   operations role. If specified, Elastic Beanstalk uses the operations
--   role for permissions to downstream services during this call and
--   during subsequent calls acting on this environment. To specify an
--   operations role, you must have the <tt>iam:PassRole</tt> permission
--   for the role. For more information, see <a>Operations roles</a> in the
--   <i>AWS Elastic Beanstalk Developer Guide</i>.
--   
--   <a>$sel:applicationName:CreateEnvironment'</a>,
--   <a>createEnvironment_applicationName</a> - The name of the application
--   that is associated with this environment.
newCreateEnvironment :: Text -> CreateEnvironment

-- | Describes the properties of an environment.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newEnvironmentDescription</a> smart constructor.
data EnvironmentDescription
EnvironmentDescription' :: Maybe Bool -> Maybe Text -> Maybe EnvironmentStatus -> Maybe ISO8601 -> Maybe [EnvironmentLink] -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe EnvironmentHealth -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe ISO8601 -> Maybe EnvironmentResourcesDescription -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe EnvironmentHealthStatus -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe EnvironmentTier -> Maybe Text -> EnvironmentDescription

-- | Indicates if there is an in-progress environment configuration update
--   or application version deployment that you can cancel.
--   
--   <tt>true:</tt> There is an update in progress.
--   
--   <tt>false:</tt> There are no updates currently in progress.
[$sel:abortableOperationInProgress:EnvironmentDescription'] :: EnvironmentDescription -> Maybe Bool

-- | The name of the configuration template used to originally launch this
--   environment.
[$sel:templateName:EnvironmentDescription'] :: EnvironmentDescription -> Maybe Text

-- | The current operational status of the environment:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li><tt>Launching</tt>: Environment is in the process of initial
--   deployment.</li>
--   <li><tt>Updating</tt>: Environment is in the process of updating its
--   configuration settings or application version.</li>
--   <li><tt>Ready</tt>: Environment is available to have an action
--   performed on it, such as update or terminate.</li>
--   <li><tt>Terminating</tt>: Environment is in the shut-down
--   process.</li>
--   <li><tt>Terminated</tt>: Environment is not running.</li>
--   </ul>
[$sel:status:EnvironmentDescription'] :: EnvironmentDescription -> Maybe EnvironmentStatus

-- | The creation date for this environment.
[$sel:dateCreated:EnvironmentDescription'] :: EnvironmentDescription -> Maybe ISO8601

-- | A list of links to other environments in the same group.
[$sel:environmentLinks:EnvironmentDescription'] :: EnvironmentDescription -> Maybe [EnvironmentLink]

-- | The ID of this environment.
[$sel:environmentId:EnvironmentDescription'] :: EnvironmentDescription -> Maybe Text

-- | The name of the <tt>SolutionStack</tt> deployed with this environment.
[$sel:solutionStackName:EnvironmentDescription'] :: EnvironmentDescription -> Maybe Text

-- | The ARN of the platform version.
[$sel:platformArn:EnvironmentDescription'] :: EnvironmentDescription -> Maybe Text

-- | The name of this environment.
[$sel:environmentName:EnvironmentDescription'] :: EnvironmentDescription -> Maybe Text

-- | Describes the health status of the environment. AWS Elastic Beanstalk
--   indicates the failure levels for a running environment:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li><tt>Red</tt>: Indicates the environment is not responsive. Occurs
--   when three or more consecutive failures occur for an environment.</li>
--   <li><tt>Yellow</tt>: Indicates that something is wrong. Occurs when
--   two consecutive failures occur for an environment.</li>
--   <li><tt>Green</tt>: Indicates the environment is healthy and fully
--   functional.</li>
--   <li><tt>Grey</tt>: Default health for a new environment. The
--   environment is not fully launched and health checks have not started
--   or health checks are suspended during an <tt>UpdateEnvironment</tt> or
--   <tt>RestartEnvironment</tt> request.</li>
--   </ul>
--   
--   Default: <tt>Grey</tt>
[$sel:health:EnvironmentDescription'] :: EnvironmentDescription -> Maybe EnvironmentHealth

-- | The application version deployed in this environment.
[$sel:versionLabel:EnvironmentDescription'] :: EnvironmentDescription -> Maybe Text

-- | The URL to the CNAME for this environment.
[$sel:cname:EnvironmentDescription'] :: EnvironmentDescription -> Maybe Text

-- | The last modified date for this environment.
[$sel:dateUpdated:EnvironmentDescription'] :: EnvironmentDescription -> Maybe ISO8601

-- | The description of the AWS resources used by this environment.
[$sel:resources:EnvironmentDescription'] :: EnvironmentDescription -> Maybe EnvironmentResourcesDescription

-- | Describes this environment.
[$sel:description:EnvironmentDescription'] :: EnvironmentDescription -> Maybe Text

-- | For load-balanced, autoscaling environments, the URL to the
--   LoadBalancer. For single-instance environments, the IP address of the
--   instance.
[$sel:endpointURL:EnvironmentDescription'] :: EnvironmentDescription -> Maybe Text

-- | Returns the health status of the application running in your
--   environment. For more information, see <a>Health Colors and
--   Statuses</a>.
[$sel:healthStatus:EnvironmentDescription'] :: EnvironmentDescription -> Maybe EnvironmentHealthStatus

-- | The environment's Amazon Resource Name (ARN), which can be used in
--   other API requests that require an ARN.
[$sel:environmentArn:EnvironmentDescription'] :: EnvironmentDescription -> Maybe Text

-- | The name of the application associated with this environment.
[$sel:applicationName:EnvironmentDescription'] :: EnvironmentDescription -> Maybe Text

-- | Describes the current tier of this environment.
[$sel:tier:EnvironmentDescription'] :: EnvironmentDescription -> Maybe EnvironmentTier

-- | The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the environment's operations role.
--   For more information, see <a>Operations roles</a> in the <i>AWS
--   Elastic Beanstalk Developer Guide</i>.
[$sel:operationsRole:EnvironmentDescription'] :: EnvironmentDescription -> Maybe Text

-- | Create a value of <a>EnvironmentDescription</a> with all optional
--   fields omitted.
--

newEnvironmentDescription :: EnvironmentDescription

-- | Creates an AWS Elastic Beanstalk configuration template, associated
--   with a specific Elastic Beanstalk application. You define application
--   configuration settings in a configuration template. You can then use
--   the configuration template to deploy different versions of the
--   application with the same configuration settings.
--   
--   Templates aren't associated with any environment. The
--   <tt>EnvironmentName</tt> response element is always <tt>null</tt>.
--   
--   Related Topics
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li>DescribeConfigurationOptions</li>
--   <li>DescribeConfigurationSettings</li>
--   <li>ListAvailableSolutionStacks</li>
--   </ul>
module Network.AWS.ElasticBeanstalk.CreateConfigurationTemplate

-- | Request to create a configuration template.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newCreateConfigurationTemplate</a> smart constructor.
data CreateConfigurationTemplate
CreateConfigurationTemplate' :: Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe [Tag] -> Maybe [ConfigurationOptionSetting] -> Maybe Text -> Maybe SourceConfiguration -> Text -> Text -> CreateConfigurationTemplate

-- | The ID of an environment whose settings you want to use to create the
--   configuration template. You must specify <tt>EnvironmentId</tt> if you
--   don't specify <tt>PlatformArn</tt>, <tt>SolutionStackName</tt>, or
--   <tt>SourceConfiguration</tt>.
[$sel:environmentId:CreateConfigurationTemplate'] :: CreateConfigurationTemplate -> Maybe Text

-- | The name of an Elastic Beanstalk solution stack (platform version)
--   that this configuration uses. For example, <tt>64bit Amazon Linux
--   2013.09 running Tomcat 7 Java 7</tt>. A solution stack specifies the
--   operating system, runtime, and application server for a configuration
--   template. It also determines the set of configuration options as well
--   as the possible and default values. For more information, see
--   <a>Supported Platforms</a> in the <i>AWS Elastic Beanstalk Developer
--   Guide</i>.
--   
--   You must specify <tt>SolutionStackName</tt> if you don't specify
--   <tt>PlatformArn</tt>, <tt>EnvironmentId</tt>, or
--   <tt>SourceConfiguration</tt>.
--   
--   Use the <a>ListAvailableSolutionStacks</a> API to obtain a list of
--   available solution stacks.
[$sel:solutionStackName:CreateConfigurationTemplate'] :: CreateConfigurationTemplate -> Maybe Text

-- | The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the custom platform. For more
--   information, see <a>Custom Platforms</a> in the <i>AWS Elastic
--   Beanstalk Developer Guide</i>.
--   
--   If you specify <tt>PlatformArn</tt>, then don't specify
--   <tt>SolutionStackName</tt>.
[$sel:platformArn:CreateConfigurationTemplate'] :: CreateConfigurationTemplate -> Maybe Text

-- | Specifies the tags applied to the configuration template.
[$sel:tags:CreateConfigurationTemplate'] :: CreateConfigurationTemplate -> Maybe [Tag]

-- | Option values for the Elastic Beanstalk configuration, such as the
--   instance type. If specified, these values override the values obtained
--   from the solution stack or the source configuration template. For a
--   complete list of Elastic Beanstalk configuration options, see
--   <a>Option Values</a> in the <i>AWS Elastic Beanstalk Developer
--   Guide</i>.
[$sel:optionSettings:CreateConfigurationTemplate'] :: CreateConfigurationTemplate -> Maybe [ConfigurationOptionSetting]

-- | An optional description for this configuration.
[$sel:description:CreateConfigurationTemplate'] :: CreateConfigurationTemplate -> Maybe Text

-- | An Elastic Beanstalk configuration template to base this one on. If
--   specified, Elastic Beanstalk uses the configuration values from the
--   specified configuration template to create a new configuration.
--   
--   Values specified in <tt>OptionSettings</tt> override any values
--   obtained from the <tt>SourceConfiguration</tt>.
--   
--   You must specify <tt>SourceConfiguration</tt> if you don't specify
--   <tt>PlatformArn</tt>, <tt>EnvironmentId</tt>, or
--   <tt>SolutionStackName</tt>.
--   
--   Constraint: If both solution stack name and source configuration are
--   specified, the solution stack of the source configuration template
--   must match the specified solution stack name.
[$sel:sourceConfiguration:CreateConfigurationTemplate'] :: CreateConfigurationTemplate -> Maybe SourceConfiguration

--   configuration template.
[$sel:applicationName:CreateConfigurationTemplate'] :: CreateConfigurationTemplate -> Text

-- | The name of the configuration template.
--   
--   Constraint: This name must be unique per application.
[$sel:templateName:CreateConfigurationTemplate'] :: CreateConfigurationTemplate -> Text

-- | Describes the settings for a configuration set.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newConfigurationSettingsDescription</a> smart
--   constructor.
data ConfigurationSettingsDescription
ConfigurationSettingsDescription' :: Maybe Text -> Maybe ISO8601 -> Maybe Text -> Maybe ConfigurationDeploymentStatus -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe ISO8601 -> Maybe [ConfigurationOptionSetting] -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> ConfigurationSettingsDescription

-- | If not <tt>null</tt>, the name of the configuration template for this
--   configuration set.
[$sel:templateName:ConfigurationSettingsDescription'] :: ConfigurationSettingsDescription -> Maybe Text

-- | The date (in UTC time) when this configuration set was created.
[$sel:dateCreated:ConfigurationSettingsDescription'] :: ConfigurationSettingsDescription -> Maybe ISO8601

-- | The name of the solution stack this configuration set uses.
[$sel:solutionStackName:ConfigurationSettingsDescription'] :: ConfigurationSettingsDescription -> Maybe Text

-- | If this configuration set is associated with an environment, the
--   <tt>DeploymentStatus</tt> parameter indicates the deployment status of
--   this configuration set:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li><tt>null</tt>: This configuration is not associated with a running
--   environment.</li>
--   <li><tt>pending</tt>: This is a draft configuration that is not
--   deployed to the associated environment but is in the process of
--   deploying.</li>
--   <li><tt>deployed</tt>: This is the configuration that is currently
--   deployed to the associated running environment.</li>
--   <li><tt>failed</tt>: This is a draft configuration that failed to
--   successfully deploy.</li>
--   </ul>
[$sel:deploymentStatus:ConfigurationSettingsDescription'] :: ConfigurationSettingsDescription -> Maybe ConfigurationDeploymentStatus

-- | The ARN of the platform version.
[$sel:platformArn:ConfigurationSettingsDescription'] :: ConfigurationSettingsDescription -> Maybe Text

-- | If not <tt>null</tt>, the name of the environment for this
--   configuration set.
[$sel:environmentName:ConfigurationSettingsDescription'] :: ConfigurationSettingsDescription -> Maybe Text

-- | The date (in UTC time) when this configuration set was last modified.
[$sel:dateUpdated:ConfigurationSettingsDescription'] :: ConfigurationSettingsDescription -> Maybe ISO8601

-- | A list of the configuration options and their values in this
--   configuration set.
[$sel:optionSettings:ConfigurationSettingsDescription'] :: ConfigurationSettingsDescription -> Maybe [ConfigurationOptionSetting]

-- | Describes this configuration set.
[$sel:description:ConfigurationSettingsDescription'] :: ConfigurationSettingsDescription -> Maybe Text

-- | The name of the application associated with this configuration set.
[$sel:applicationName:ConfigurationSettingsDescription'] :: ConfigurationSettingsDescription -> Maybe Text

-- | Create a value of <a>ConfigurationSettingsDescription</a> with all
--   optional fields omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.

--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
