-- | Creates an application version for the specified application. You can
--   create an application version from a source bundle in Amazon S3, a
--   commit in AWS CodeCommit, or the output of an AWS CodeBuild build as
--   follows:
--   
--   Specify a commit in an AWS CodeCommit repository with
--   <tt>SourceBuildInformation</tt>.
--   
--   Specify a build in an AWS CodeBuild with
--   <tt>SourceBuildInformation</tt> and <tt>BuildConfiguration</tt>.
--   
--   Specify a source bundle in S3 with <tt>SourceBundle</tt>
--   
--   Omit both <tt>SourceBuildInformation</tt> and <tt>SourceBundle</tt> to
--   use the default sample application.
--   
--   After you create an application version with a specified Amazon S3
--   bucket and key location, you can't change that Amazon S3 location. If
--   you change the Amazon S3 location, you receive an exception when you
--   attempt to launch an environment from the application version.
module Network.AWS.ElasticBeanstalk.CreateApplicationVersion

-- | <i>See:</i> <a>newCreateApplicationVersion</a> smart constructor.
data CreateApplicationVersion
CreateApplicationVersion' :: Maybe S3Location -> Maybe BuildConfiguration -> Maybe SourceBuildInformation -> Maybe [Tag] -> Maybe Bool -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Bool -> Text -> Text -> CreateApplicationVersion

-- | The Amazon S3 bucket and key that identify the location of the source
--   bundle for this version.
--   
--   The Amazon S3 bucket must be in the same region as the environment.
--   
--   Specify a source bundle in S3 or a commit in an AWS CodeCommit
--   repository (with <tt>SourceBuildInformation</tt>), but not both. If
--   neither <tt>SourceBundle</tt> nor <tt>SourceBuildInformation</tt> are
--   provided, Elastic Beanstalk uses a sample application.
[$sel:sourceBundle:CreateApplicationVersion'] :: CreateApplicationVersion -> Maybe S3Location

-- | Settings for an AWS CodeBuild build.
[$sel:buildConfiguration:CreateApplicationVersion'] :: CreateApplicationVersion -> Maybe BuildConfiguration

-- | Specify a commit in an AWS CodeCommit Git repository to use as the
--   source code for the application version.
[$sel:sourceBuildInformation:CreateApplicationVersion'] :: CreateApplicationVersion -> Maybe SourceBuildInformation

-- | Specifies the tags applied to the application version.
--   
--   Elastic Beanstalk applies these tags only to the application version.
--   Environments that use the application version don't inherit the tags.
[$sel:tags:CreateApplicationVersion'] :: CreateApplicationVersion -> Maybe [Tag]

-- | Set to <tt>true</tt> to create an application with the specified name
--   if it doesn't already exist.
[$sel:autoCreateApplication:CreateApplicationVersion'] :: CreateApplicationVersion -> Maybe Bool

-- | A description of this application version.
[$sel:description:CreateApplicationVersion'] :: CreateApplicationVersion -> Maybe Text

-- | Pre-processes and validates the environment manifest
--   (<tt>env.yaml</tt>) and configuration files (<tt>*.config</tt> files
--   in the <tt>.ebextensions</tt> folder) in the source bundle. Validating
--   configuration files can identify issues prior to deploying the
--   application version to an environment.
--   
--   You must turn processing on for application versions that you create
--   using AWS CodeBuild or AWS CodeCommit. For application versions built
--   from a source bundle in Amazon S3, processing is optional.
--   
--   The <tt>Process</tt> option validates Elastic Beanstalk configuration
--   files. It doesn't validate your application's configuration files,
--   like proxy server or Docker configuration.
[$sel:process:CreateApplicationVersion'] :: CreateApplicationVersion -> Maybe Bool

-- | The name of the application. If no application is found with this
--   name, and <tt>AutoCreateApplication</tt> is <tt>false</tt>, returns an
--   <tt>InvalidParameterValue</tt> error.
[$sel:applicationName:CreateApplicationVersion'] :: CreateApplicationVersion -> Text

-- | A label identifying this version.
--   
--   Constraint: Must be unique per application. If an application version
--   already exists with this label for the specified application, AWS
--   Elastic Beanstalk returns an <tt>InvalidParameterValue</tt> error.
[$sel:versionLabel:CreateApplicationVersion'] :: CreateApplicationVersion -> Text

-- | Create a value of <a>CreateApplicationVersion</a> with all optional
--   fields omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:sourceBundle:CreateApplicationVersion'</a>,

--   and key that identify the location of the source bundle for this
--   version.
--   
--   The Amazon S3 bucket must be in the same region as the environment.
--   
--   Specify a source bundle in S3 or a commit in an AWS CodeCommit
--   repository (with <tt>SourceBuildInformation</tt>), but not both. If
--   neither <tt>SourceBundle</tt> nor <tt>SourceBuildInformation</tt> are
--   provided, Elastic Beanstalk uses a sample application.
--   
--   <a>$sel:buildConfiguration:CreateApplicationVersion'</a>,
--   <a>createApplicationVersion_buildConfiguration</a> - Settings for an
--   AWS CodeBuild build.
--   
--   <a>$sel:sourceBuildInformation:CreateApplicationVersion'</a>,
--   <a>createApplicationVersion_sourceBuildInformation</a> - Specify a
--   commit in an AWS CodeCommit Git repository to use as the source code
--   for the application version.
--   
--   <a>$sel:tags:CreateApplicationVersion'</a>,

--   the application version.
--

--   Environments that use the application version don't inherit the tags.
--   
--   <a>$sel:autoCreateApplication:CreateApplicationVersion'</a>,

--   doesn't already exist.
--   
--   <a>$sel:description:CreateApplicationVersion'</a>,
--   <a>createApplicationVersion_description</a> - A description of this
--   application version.
--   
--   <a>$sel:process:CreateApplicationVersion'</a>,
--   <a>createApplicationVersion_process</a> - Pre-processes and validates
--   the environment manifest (<tt>env.yaml</tt>) and configuration files

--   application. If no application is found with this name, and
--   <tt>AutoCreateApplication</tt> is <tt>false</tt>, returns an
--   <tt>InvalidParameterValue</tt> error.
--   
--   <a>$sel:versionLabel:CreateApplicationVersion'</a>,
--   <a>createApplicationVersion_versionLabel</a> - A label identifying
--   this version.
--   
--   Constraint: Must be unique per application. If an application version
--   already exists with this label for the specified application, AWS
--   Elastic Beanstalk returns an <tt>InvalidParameterValue</tt> error.
newCreateApplicationVersion :: Text -> Text -> CreateApplicationVersion

-- | The Amazon S3 bucket and key that identify the location of the source
--   bundle for this version.
--   
--   The Amazon S3 bucket must be in the same region as the environment.
--   
--   Specify a source bundle in S3 or a commit in an AWS CodeCommit
--   repository (with <tt>SourceBuildInformation</tt>), but not both. If

-- | A description of this application version.
createApplicationVersion_description :: Lens' CreateApplicationVersion (Maybe Text)

-- | Pre-processes and validates the environment manifest
--   (<tt>env.yaml</tt>) and configuration files (<tt>*.config</tt> files
--   in the <tt>.ebextensions</tt> folder) in the source bundle. Validating
--   configuration files can identify issues prior to deploying the
--   application version to an environment.
--   
--   You must turn processing on for application versions that you create
--   using AWS CodeBuild or AWS CodeCommit. For application versions built
--   from a source bundle in Amazon S3, processing is optional.
--   
--   The <tt>Process</tt> option validates Elastic Beanstalk configuration
--   files. It doesn't validate your application's configuration files,
--   like proxy server or Docker configuration.
createApplicationVersion_process :: Lens' CreateApplicationVersion (Maybe Bool)

-- | The name of the application. If no application is found with this
--   name, and <tt>AutoCreateApplication</tt> is <tt>false</tt>, returns an
--   <tt>InvalidParameterValue</tt> error.
createApplicationVersion_applicationName :: Lens' CreateApplicationVersion Text

-- | A label identifying this version.
--   
--   Constraint: Must be unique per application. If an application version
--   already exists with this label for the specified application, AWS
--   Elastic Beanstalk returns an <tt>InvalidParameterValue</tt> error.
createApplicationVersion_versionLabel :: Lens' CreateApplicationVersion Text

--   version.

--   constructor.

applicationVersionDescriptionMessage_applicationVersion :: Lens' ApplicationVersionDescriptionMessage (Maybe ApplicationVersionDescription)

-- | Creates an application that has one configuration template named
--   <tt>default</tt> and no application versions.
module Network.AWS.ElasticBeanstalk.CreateApplication

-- | Request to create an application.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newCreateApplication</a> smart constructor.
data CreateApplication
CreateApplication' :: Maybe [Tag] -> Maybe ApplicationResourceLifecycleConfig -> Maybe Text -> Text -> CreateApplication

-- | Specifies the tags applied to the application.
--   
--   Elastic Beanstalk applies these tags only to the application.
--   Environments that you create in the application don't inherit the
--   tags.

--   your application from accumulating too many versions.

--   application.

-- | Create or update a group of environments that each run a separate
--   component of a single application. Takes a list of version labels that
--   specify application source bundles for each of the environments to
--   create or update. The name of each environment and other required
--   information must be included in the source bundles in an environment
--   manifest named <tt>env.yaml</tt>. See <a>Compose Environments</a> for
--   details.
module Network.AWS.ElasticBeanstalk.ComposeEnvironments

-- | Request to create or update a group of environments.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newComposeEnvironments</a> smart constructor.
data ComposeEnvironments
ComposeEnvironments' :: Maybe Text -> Maybe [Text] -> Maybe Text -> ComposeEnvironments

-- | The name of the group to which the target environments belong. Specify
--   a group name only if the environment name defined in each target
--   environment's manifest ends with a + (plus) character. See
--   <a>Environment Manifest (env.yaml)</a> for details.
[$sel:groupName:ComposeEnvironments'] :: ComposeEnvironments -> Maybe Text

-- | A list of version labels, specifying one or more application source
--   bundles that belong to the target application. Each source bundle must
--   include an environment manifest that specifies the name of the
--   environment and the name of the solution stack to use, and optionally
--   can specify environment links to create.
[$sel:versionLabels:ComposeEnvironments'] :: ComposeEnvironments -> Maybe [Text]

-- | The name of the application to which the specified source bundles
--   belong.
[$sel:applicationName:ComposeEnvironments'] :: ComposeEnvironments -> Maybe Text

-- | Create a value of <a>ComposeEnvironments</a> with all optional fields
--   omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:groupName:ComposeEnvironments'</a>,
--   <a>composeEnvironments_groupName</a> - The name of the group to which
--   the target environments belong. Specify a group name only if the
--   environment name defined in each target environment's manifest ends
--   with a + (plus) character. See <a>Environment Manifest (env.yaml)</a>
--   for details.
--   
--   <a>$sel:versionLabels:ComposeEnvironments'</a>,
--   <a>composeEnvironments_versionLabels</a> - A list of version labels,
--   specifying one or more application source bundles that belong to the
--   target application. Each source bundle must include an environment
--   manifest that specifies the name of the environment and the name of
--   the solution stack to use, and optionally can specify environment
--   links to create.
--   
--   <a>$sel:applicationName:ComposeEnvironments'</a>,
--   <a>composeEnvironments_applicationName</a> - The name of the
--   application to which the specified source bundles belong.
newComposeEnvironments :: ComposeEnvironments

-- | The name of the group to which the target environments belong. Specify
--   a group name only if the environment name defined in each target
--   environment's manifest ends with a + (plus) character. See
--   <a>Environment Manifest (env.yaml)</a> for details.
composeEnvironments_groupName :: Lens' ComposeEnvironments (Maybe Text)

-- | A list of version labels, specifying one or more application source

--   environment and the name of the solution stack to use, and optionally
--   can specify environment links to create.
composeEnvironments_versionLabels :: Lens' ComposeEnvironments (Maybe [Text])

--   belong.
composeEnvironments_applicationName :: Lens' ComposeEnvironments (Maybe Text)

-- | Applies a scheduled managed action immediately. A managed action can
--   be applied only if its status is <tt>Scheduled</tt>. Get the status
--   and action ID of a managed action with
--   DescribeEnvironmentManagedActions.
module Network.AWS.ElasticBeanstalk.ApplyEnvironmentManagedAction

--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newApplyEnvironmentManagedAction</a> smart constructor.

-- | Describes the settings for a configuration set.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newConfigurationSettingsDescription</a> smart
--   constructor.
data ConfigurationSettingsDescription
ConfigurationSettingsDescription' :: Maybe Text -> Maybe ISO8601 -> Maybe Text -> Maybe ConfigurationDeploymentStatus -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe ISO8601 -> Maybe [ConfigurationOptionSetting] -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> ConfigurationSettingsDescription

-- | If not <tt>null</tt>, the name of the configuration template for this
--   configuration set.
[$sel:templateName:ConfigurationSettingsDescription'] :: ConfigurationSettingsDescription -> Maybe Text

-- | The date (in UTC time) when this configuration set was created.
[$sel:dateCreated:ConfigurationSettingsDescription'] :: ConfigurationSettingsDescription -> Maybe ISO8601

-- | The name of the solution stack this configuration set uses.
[$sel:solutionStackName:ConfigurationSettingsDescription'] :: ConfigurationSettingsDescription -> Maybe Text

-- | If this configuration set is associated with an environment, the
--   <tt>DeploymentStatus</tt> parameter indicates the deployment status of
--   this configuration set:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li><tt>null</tt>: This configuration is not associated with a running
--   environment.</li>
--   <li><tt>pending</tt>: This is a draft configuration that is not
--   deployed to the associated environment but is in the process of
--   deploying.</li>
--   <li><tt>deployed</tt>: This is the configuration that is currently
--   deployed to the associated running environment.</li>
--   <li><tt>failed</tt>: This is a draft configuration that failed to
--   successfully deploy.</li>
--   </ul>
[$sel:deploymentStatus:ConfigurationSettingsDescription'] :: ConfigurationSettingsDescription -> Maybe ConfigurationDeploymentStatus

-- | The ARN of the platform version.
[$sel:platformArn:ConfigurationSettingsDescription'] :: ConfigurationSettingsDescription -> Maybe Text

-- | If not <tt>null</tt>, the name of the environment for this
--   configuration set.
[$sel:environmentName:ConfigurationSettingsDescription'] :: ConfigurationSettingsDescription -> Maybe Text

-- | The date (in UTC time) when this configuration set was last modified.
[$sel:dateUpdated:ConfigurationSettingsDescription'] :: ConfigurationSettingsDescription -> Maybe ISO8601

-- | A list of the configuration options and their values in this
--   configuration set.
[$sel:optionSettings:ConfigurationSettingsDescription'] :: ConfigurationSettingsDescription -> Maybe [ConfigurationOptionSetting]

-- | Describes this configuration set.
[$sel:description:ConfigurationSettingsDescription'] :: ConfigurationSettingsDescription -> Maybe Text

-- | The name of the application associated with this configuration set.
[$sel:applicationName:ConfigurationSettingsDescription'] :: ConfigurationSettingsDescription -> Maybe Text

-- | Create a value of <a>ConfigurationSettingsDescription</a> with all
--   optional fields omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:templateName:ConfigurationSettingsDescription'</a>,
--   <a>configurationSettingsDescription_templateName</a> - If not
--   <tt>null</tt>, the name of the configuration template for this
--   configuration set.
--   
--   <a>$sel:dateCreated:ConfigurationSettingsDescription'</a>,
--   <a>configurationSettingsDescription_dateCreated</a> - The date (in UTC
--   time) when this configuration set was created.
--   
--   <a>$sel:solutionStackName:ConfigurationSettingsDescription'</a>,
--   <a>configurationSettingsDescription_solutionStackName</a> - The name
--   of the solution stack this configuration set uses.
--   
--   <a>$sel:deploymentStatus:ConfigurationSettingsDescription'</a>,
--   <a>configurationSettingsDescription_deploymentStatus</a> - If this
--   configuration set is associated with an environment, the
--   <tt>DeploymentStatus</tt> parameter indicates the deployment status of
--   this configuration set:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li><tt>null</tt>: This configuration is not associated with a running
--   environment.</li>
--   <li><tt>pending</tt>: This is a draft configuration that is not
--   deployed to the associated environment but is in the process of
--   deploying.</li>
--   <li><tt>deployed</tt>: This is the configuration that is currently
--   deployed to the associated running environment.</li>
--   <li><tt>failed</tt>: This is a draft configuration that failed to
--   successfully deploy.</li>
--   </ul>
--   
--   <a>$sel:platformArn:ConfigurationSettingsDescription'</a>,
--   <a>configurationSettingsDescription_platformArn</a> - The ARN of the
--   platform version.
--   
--   <a>$sel:environmentName:ConfigurationSettingsDescription'</a>,
--   <a>configurationSettingsDescription_environmentName</a> - If not
--   <tt>null</tt>, the name of the environment for this configuration set.
--   
--   <a>$sel:dateUpdated:ConfigurationSettingsDescription'</a>,
--   <a>configurationSettingsDescription_dateUpdated</a> - The date (in UTC
--   time) when this configuration set was last modified.
--   
--   <a>$sel:optionSettings:ConfigurationSettingsDescription'</a>,
--   <a>configurationSettingsDescription_optionSettings</a> - A list of the
--   configuration options and their values in this configuration set.
--   
--   <a>$sel:description:ConfigurationSettingsDescription'</a>,
--   <a>configurationSettingsDescription_description</a> - Describes this
--   configuration set.
--   
--   <a>$sel:applicationName:ConfigurationSettingsDescription'</a>,
--   <a>configurationSettingsDescription_applicationName</a> - The name of
--   the application associated with this configuration set.
newConfigurationSettingsDescription :: ConfigurationSettingsDescription

-- | If not <tt>null</tt>, the name of the configuration template for this
--   configuration set.
configurationSettingsDescription_templateName :: Lens' ConfigurationSettingsDescription (Maybe Text)

-- | The date (in UTC time) when this configuration set was created.
configurationSettingsDescription_dateCreated :: Lens' ConfigurationSettingsDescription (Maybe UTCTime)

-- | The name of the solution stack this configuration set uses.
configurationSettingsDescription_solutionStackName :: Lens' ConfigurationSettingsDescription (Maybe Text)

-- | If this configuration set is associated with an environment, the
--   <tt>DeploymentStatus</tt> parameter indicates the deployment status of
--   this configuration set:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li><tt>null</tt>: This configuration is not associated with a running
--   environment.</li>
--   <li><tt>pending</tt>: This is a draft configuration that is not
--   deployed to the associated environment but is in the process of
--   deploying.</li>
--   <li><tt>deployed</tt>: This is the configuration that is currently
--   deployed to the associated running environment.</li>
--   <li><tt>failed</tt>: This is a draft configuration that failed to
--   successfully deploy.</li>
--   </ul>
configurationSettingsDescription_deploymentStatus :: Lens' ConfigurationSettingsDescription (Maybe ConfigurationDeploymentStatus)

-- | The ARN of the platform version.
configurationSettingsDescription_platformArn :: Lens' ConfigurationSettingsDescription (Maybe Text)

-- | If not <tt>null</tt>, the name of the environment for this
--   configuration set.
configurationSettingsDescription_environmentName :: Lens' ConfigurationSettingsDescription (Maybe Text)

-- | The date (in UTC time) when this configuration set was last modified.
configurationSettingsDescription_dateUpdated :: Lens' ConfigurationSettingsDescription (Maybe UTCTime)

-- | A list of the configuration options and their values in this
--   configuration set.
configurationSettingsDescription_optionSettings :: Lens' ConfigurationSettingsDescription (Maybe [ConfigurationOptionSetting])

-- | Describes this configuration set.
configurationSettingsDescription_description :: Lens' ConfigurationSettingsDescription (Maybe Text)

-- | The name of the application associated with this configuration set.
configurationSettingsDescription_applicationName :: Lens' ConfigurationSettingsDescription (Maybe Text)
instance GHC.Generics.Generic Network.AWS.ElasticBeanstalk.UpdateConfigurationTemplate.UpdateConfigurationTemplate
instance GHC.Show.Show Network.AWS.ElasticBeanstalk.UpdateConfigurationTemplate.UpdateConfigurationTemplate
instance GHC.Read.Read Network.AWS.ElasticBeanstalk.UpdateConfigurationTemplate.UpdateConfigurationTemplate
instance GHC.Classes.Eq Network.AWS.ElasticBeanstalk.UpdateConfigurationTemplate.UpdateConfigurationTemplate
instance Network.AWS.Types.AWSRequest Network.AWS.ElasticBeanstalk.UpdateConfigurationTemplate.UpdateConfigurationTemplate
instance Data.Hashable.Class.Hashable Network.AWS.ElasticBeanstalk.UpdateConfigurationTemplate.UpdateConfigurationTemplate
instance Control.DeepSeq.NFData Network.AWS.ElasticBeanstalk.UpdateConfigurationTemplate.UpdateConfigurationTemplate
instance Network.AWS.Data.Headers.ToHeaders Network.AWS.ElasticBeanstalk.UpdateConfigurationTemplate.UpdateConfigurationTemplate
instance Network.AWS.Data.Path.ToPath Network.AWS.ElasticBeanstalk.UpdateConfigurationTemplate.UpdateConfigurationTemplate
instance Network.AWS.Data.Query.ToQuery Network.AWS.ElasticBeanstalk.UpdateConfigurationTemplate.UpdateConfigurationTemplate


-- | Updates the environment description, deploys a new application
--   version, updates the configuration settings to an entirely new
--   configuration template, or updates select configuration option values
--   in the running environment.
--   
--   Attempting to update both the release and configuration is not allowed
--   and AWS Elastic Beanstalk returns an
--   <tt>InvalidParameterCombination</tt> error.
--   
--   When updating the configuration settings to a new template or
--   individual settings, a draft configuration is created and
--   DescribeConfigurationSettings for this environment returns two setting
--   descriptions with different <tt>DeploymentStatus</tt> values.
module Network.AWS.ElasticBeanstalk.UpdateEnvironment

-- | Request to update an environment.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newUpdateEnvironment</a> smart constructor.
data UpdateEnvironment
UpdateEnvironment' :: Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe [OptionSpecification] -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe [ConfigurationOptionSetting] -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe EnvironmentTier -> UpdateEnvironment

-- | If this parameter is specified, AWS Elastic Beanstalk deploys this
--   configuration template to the environment. If no such configuration
--   template is found, AWS Elastic Beanstalk returns an
--   <tt>InvalidParameterValue</tt> error.
[$sel:templateName:UpdateEnvironment'] :: UpdateEnvironment -> Maybe Text

-- | The ID of the environment to update.
--   
--   If no environment with this ID exists, AWS Elastic Beanstalk returns
--   an <tt>InvalidParameterValue</tt> error.
--   
--   Condition: You must specify either this or an EnvironmentName, or
--   both. If you do not specify either, AWS Elastic Beanstalk returns
--   <tt>MissingRequiredParameter</tt> error.
[$sel:environmentId:UpdateEnvironment'] :: UpdateEnvironment -> Maybe Text

-- | This specifies the platform version that the environment will run
--   after the environment is updated.
[$sel:solutionStackName:UpdateEnvironment'] :: UpdateEnvironment -> Maybe Text

-- | The name of the group to which the target environment belongs. Specify
--   a group name only if the environment's name is specified in an
--   environment manifest and not with the environment name or environment
--   ID parameters. See <a>Environment Manifest (env.yaml)</a> for details.
[$sel:groupName:UpdateEnvironment'] :: UpdateEnvironment -> Maybe Text

-- | A list of custom user-defined configuration options to remove from the
--   configuration set for this environment.
[$sel:optionsToRemove:UpdateEnvironment'] :: UpdateEnvironment -> Maybe [OptionSpecification]

-- | The ARN of the platform, if used.
[$sel:platformArn:UpdateEnvironment'] :: UpdateEnvironment -> Maybe Text

-- | The name of the environment to update. If no environment with this
--   name exists, AWS Elastic Beanstalk returns an
--   <tt>InvalidParameterValue</tt> error.
--   
--   Condition: You must specify either this or an EnvironmentId, or both.
--   If you do not specify either, AWS Elastic Beanstalk returns
--   <tt>MissingRequiredParameter</tt> error.
[$sel:environmentName:UpdateEnvironment'] :: UpdateEnvironment -> Maybe Text

-- | If this parameter is specified, AWS Elastic Beanstalk deploys the
--   named application version to the environment. If no such application
--   version is found, returns an <tt>InvalidParameterValue</tt> error.
[$sel:versionLabel:UpdateEnvironment'] :: UpdateEnvironment -> Maybe Text

-- | If specified, AWS Elastic Beanstalk updates the configuration set
--   associated with the running environment and sets the specified
--   configuration options to the requested value.
[$sel:optionSettings:UpdateEnvironment'] :: UpdateEnvironment -> Maybe [ConfigurationOptionSetting]

-- | If this parameter is specified, AWS Elastic Beanstalk updates the
--   description of this environment.
[$sel:description:UpdateEnvironment'] :: UpdateEnvironment -> Maybe Text

-- | The name of the application with which the environment is associated.
[$sel:applicationName:UpdateEnvironment'] :: UpdateEnvironment -> Maybe Text

-- | This specifies the tier to use to update the environment.
--   
--   Condition: At this time, if you change the tier version, name, or
--   type, AWS Elastic Beanstalk returns <tt>InvalidParameterValue</tt>
--   error.
[$sel:tier:UpdateEnvironment'] :: UpdateEnvironment -> Maybe EnvironmentTier

-- | Create a value of <a>UpdateEnvironment</a> with all optional fields
--   omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:templateName:UpdateEnvironment'</a>,

--   Elastic Beanstalk returns an <tt>InvalidParameterValue</tt> error.

--   <a>$sel:environmentId:UpdateEnvironment'</a>,

--   update.

--   an <tt>InvalidParameterValue</tt> error.
--   
--   Condition: You must specify either this or an EnvironmentName, or
--   both. If you do not specify either, AWS Elastic Beanstalk returns
--   <tt>MissingRequiredParameter</tt> error.
--   
--   <a>$sel:solutionStackName:UpdateEnvironment'</a>,
--   <a>updateEnvironment_solutionStackName</a> - This specifies the
--   platform version that the environment will run after the environment
--   is updated.

--   <a>$sel:groupName:UpdateEnvironment'</a>,

--   the target environment belongs. Specify a group name only if the

--   Beanstalk returns an <tt>InvalidParameterValue</tt> error.

--   requested value.

--   AWS Elastic Beanstalk updates the description of this environment.

--   <a>updateEnvironment_applicationName</a> - The name of the application
--   with which the environment is associated.

--   This specifies the tier to use to update the environment.
--   
--   Condition: At this time, if you change the tier version, name, or
--   type, AWS Elastic Beanstalk returns <tt>InvalidParameterValue</tt>
--   error.
newUpdateEnvironment :: UpdateEnvironment

-- | If this parameter is specified, AWS Elastic Beanstalk deploys this
--   configuration template to the environment. If no such configuration
--   template is found, AWS Elastic Beanstalk returns an
--   <tt>InvalidParameterValue</tt> error.
updateEnvironment_templateName :: Lens' UpdateEnvironment (Maybe Text)

-- | The ID of the environment to update.
--   
--   If no environment with this ID exists, AWS Elastic Beanstalk returns
--   an <tt>InvalidParameterValue</tt> error.
--   
--   Condition: You must specify either this or an EnvironmentName, or
--   both. If you do not specify either, AWS Elastic Beanstalk returns
--   <tt>MissingRequiredParameter</tt> error.
updateEnvironment_environmentId :: Lens' UpdateEnvironment (Maybe Text)

updateEnvironment_solutionStackName :: Lens' UpdateEnvironment (Maybe Text)

-- | The name of the group to which the target environment belongs. Specify

updateEnvironment_description :: Lens' UpdateEnvironment (Maybe Text)

updateEnvironment_applicationName :: Lens' UpdateEnvironment (Maybe Text)

--

--   type, AWS Elastic Beanstalk returns <tt>InvalidParameterValue</tt>

updateEnvironment_tier :: Lens' UpdateEnvironment (Maybe EnvironmentTier)

-- | Describes the properties of an environment.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newEnvironmentDescription</a> smart constructor.
data EnvironmentDescription
EnvironmentDescription' :: Maybe Bool -> Maybe Text -> Maybe EnvironmentStatus -> Maybe ISO8601 -> Maybe [EnvironmentLink] -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe EnvironmentHealth -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe ISO8601 -> Maybe EnvironmentResourcesDescription -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe EnvironmentHealthStatus -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe EnvironmentTier -> Maybe Text -> EnvironmentDescription

-- | Indicates if there is an in-progress environment configuration update
--   or application version deployment that you can cancel.
--   
--   <tt>true:</tt> There is an update in progress.
--   
--   <tt>false:</tt> There are no updates currently in progress.
[$sel:abortableOperationInProgress:EnvironmentDescription'] :: EnvironmentDescription -> Maybe Bool

-- | The name of the configuration template used to originally launch this
--   environment.
[$sel:templateName:EnvironmentDescription'] :: EnvironmentDescription -> Maybe Text

-- | The current operational status of the environment:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li><tt>Launching</tt>: Environment is in the process of initial
--   deployment.</li>
--   <li><tt>Updating</tt>: Environment is in the process of updating its
--   configuration settings or application version.</li>
--   <li><tt>Ready</tt>: Environment is available to have an action
--   performed on it, such as update or terminate.</li>
--   <li><tt>Terminating</tt>: Environment is in the shut-down
--   process.</li>
--   <li><tt>Terminated</tt>: Environment is not running.</li>
--   </ul>
[$sel:status:EnvironmentDescription'] :: EnvironmentDescription -> Maybe EnvironmentStatus

-- | The creation date for this environment.
[$sel:dateCreated:EnvironmentDescription'] :: EnvironmentDescription -> Maybe ISO8601

-- | A list of links to other environments in the same group.
[$sel:environmentLinks:EnvironmentDescription'] :: EnvironmentDescription -> Maybe [EnvironmentLink]

-- | The ID of this environment.
[$sel:environmentId:EnvironmentDescription'] :: EnvironmentDescription -> Maybe Text

-- | The name of the <tt>SolutionStack</tt> deployed with this environment.
[$sel:solutionStackName:EnvironmentDescription'] :: EnvironmentDescription -> Maybe Text

-- | The ARN of the platform version.
[$sel:platformArn:EnvironmentDescription'] :: EnvironmentDescription -> Maybe Text

-- | The name of this environment.
[$sel:environmentName:EnvironmentDescription'] :: EnvironmentDescription -> Maybe Text

-- | Describes the health status of the environment. AWS Elastic Beanstalk
--   indicates the failure levels for a running environment:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li><tt>Red</tt>: Indicates the environment is not responsive. Occurs
--   when three or more consecutive failures occur for an environment.</li>
--   <li><tt>Yellow</tt>: Indicates that something is wrong. Occurs when
--   two consecutive failures occur for an environment.</li>
--   <li><tt>Green</tt>: Indicates the environment is healthy and fully
--   functional.</li>
--   <li><tt>Grey</tt>: Default health for a new environment. The
--   environment is not fully launched and health checks have not started
--   or health checks are suspended during an <tt>UpdateEnvironment</tt> or
--   <tt>RestartEnvironment</tt> request.</li>
--   </ul>
--   
--   Default: <tt>Grey</tt>
[$sel:health:EnvironmentDescription'] :: EnvironmentDescription -> Maybe EnvironmentHealth

-- | The application version deployed in this environment.
[$sel:versionLabel:EnvironmentDescription'] :: EnvironmentDescription -> Maybe Text

-- | The URL to the CNAME for this environment.
[$sel:cname:EnvironmentDescription'] :: EnvironmentDescription -> Maybe Text

-- | The last modified date for this environment.
[$sel:dateUpdated:EnvironmentDescription'] :: EnvironmentDescription -> Maybe ISO8601

-- | The description of the AWS resources used by this environment.
[$sel:resources:EnvironmentDescription'] :: EnvironmentDescription -> Maybe EnvironmentResourcesDescription

-- | Describes this environment.
[$sel:description:EnvironmentDescription'] :: EnvironmentDescription -> Maybe Text

-- | For load-balanced, autoscaling environments, the URL to the
--   LoadBalancer. For single-instance environments, the IP address of the
--   instance.
[$sel:endpointURL:EnvironmentDescription'] :: EnvironmentDescription -> Maybe Text

-- | Returns the health status of the application running in your
--   environment. For more information, see <a>Health Colors and
--   Statuses</a>.
[$sel:healthStatus:EnvironmentDescription'] :: EnvironmentDescription -> Maybe EnvironmentHealthStatus

-- | The environment's Amazon Resource Name (ARN), which can be used in
--   other API requests that require an ARN.
[$sel:environmentArn:EnvironmentDescription'] :: EnvironmentDescription -> Maybe Text

-- | The name of the application associated with this environment.
[$sel:applicationName:EnvironmentDescription'] :: EnvironmentDescription -> Maybe Text

-- | Describes the current tier of this environment.
[$sel:tier:EnvironmentDescription'] :: EnvironmentDescription -> Maybe EnvironmentTier

-- | The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the environment's operations role.
--   For more information, see <a>Operations roles</a> in the <i>AWS
--   Elastic Beanstalk Developer Guide</i>.
[$sel:operationsRole:EnvironmentDescription'] :: EnvironmentDescription -> Maybe Text

-- | Create a value of <a>EnvironmentDescription</a> with all optional
--   fields omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:abortableOperationInProgress:EnvironmentDescription'</a>,
--   <a>environmentDescription_abortableOperationInProgress</a> - Indicates
--   if there is an in-progress environment configuration update or
--   application version deployment that you can cancel.
--   
--   <tt>true:</tt> There is an update in progress.
--   
--   <tt>false:</tt> There are no updates currently in progress.
--   
--   <a>$sel:templateName:EnvironmentDescription'</a>,

--   configuration template used to originally launch this environment.
--   
--   <a>$sel:status:EnvironmentDescription'</a>,
--   <a>environmentDescription_status</a> - The current operational status
--   of the environment:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li><tt>Launching</tt>: Environment is in the process of initial
--   deployment.</li>
--   <li><tt>Updating</tt>: Environment is in the process of updating its
--   configuration settings or application version.</li>
--   <li><tt>Ready</tt>: Environment is available to have an action
--   performed on it, such as update or terminate.</li>
--   <li><tt>Terminating</tt>: Environment is in the shut-down

--   when three or more consecutive failures occur for an environment.</li>

--   </ul>

--   
--   <a>$sel:versionLabel:EnvironmentDescription'</a>,

--   environment.

--   <a>environmentDescription_dateUpdated</a> - The last modified date for
--   this environment.
--   
--   <a>$sel:resources:EnvironmentDescription'</a>,
--   <a>environmentDescription_resources</a> - The description of the AWS
--   resources used by this environment.
--   
--   <a>$sel:description:EnvironmentDescription'</a>,
--   <a>environmentDescription_description</a> - Describes this
--   environment.
--   
--   <a>$sel:endpointURL:EnvironmentDescription'</a>,
--   <a>environmentDescription_endpointURL</a> - For load-balanced,
--   autoscaling environments, the URL to the LoadBalancer. For
--   single-instance environments, the IP address of the instance.
--   
--   <a>$sel:healthStatus:EnvironmentDescription'</a>,
--   <a>environmentDescription_healthStatus</a> - Returns the health status
--   of the application running in your environment. For more information,
--   see <a>Health Colors and Statuses</a>.
--   
--   <a>$sel:environmentArn:EnvironmentDescription'</a>,
--   <a>environmentDescription_environmentArn</a> - The environment's
--   Amazon Resource Name (ARN), which can be used in other API requests
--   that require an ARN.
--   
--   <a>$sel:applicationName:EnvironmentDescription'</a>,
--   <a>environmentDescription_applicationName</a> - The name of the
--   application associated with this environment.
--   
--   <a>$sel:tier:EnvironmentDescription'</a>,
--   <a>environmentDescription_tier</a> - Describes the current tier of
--   this environment.
--   
--   <a>$sel:operationsRole:EnvironmentDescription'</a>,
--   <a>environmentDescription_operationsRole</a> - The Amazon Resource
--   Name (ARN) of the environment's operations role. For more information,
--   see <a>Operations roles</a> in the <i>AWS Elastic Beanstalk Developer
--   Guide</i>.
newEnvironmentDescription :: EnvironmentDescription

-- | Indicates if there is an in-progress environment configuration update
--   or application version deployment that you can cancel.
--   
--   <tt>true:</tt> There is an update in progress.
--   
--   <tt>false:</tt> There are no updates currently in progress.
environmentDescription_abortableOperationInProgress :: Lens' EnvironmentDescription (Maybe Bool)

-- | The name of the configuration template used to originally launch this
--   environment.
environmentDescription_templateName :: Lens' EnvironmentDescription (Maybe Text)

-- | The current operational status of the environment:
--   
--   <ul>

--   deployment.</li>
--   <li><tt>Updating</tt>: Environment is in the process of updating its
--   configuration settings or application version.</li>

--   performed on it, such as update or terminate.</li>
--   <li><tt>Terminating</tt>: Environment is in the shut-down
--   process.</li>
--   <li><tt>Terminated</tt>: Environment is not running.</li>
--   </ul>
environmentDescription_status :: Lens' EnvironmentDescription (Maybe EnvironmentStatus)

-- | The creation date for this environment.

-- | The name of the <tt>SolutionStack</tt> deployed with this environment.
environmentDescription_solutionStackName :: Lens' EnvironmentDescription (Maybe Text)

-- | The ARN of the platform version.
environmentDescription_platformArn :: Lens' EnvironmentDescription (Maybe Text)

-- | The name of this environment.
environmentDescription_environmentName :: Lens' EnvironmentDescription (Maybe Text)

-- | Describes the health status of the environment. AWS Elastic Beanstalk
--   indicates the failure levels for a running environment:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li><tt>Red</tt>: Indicates the environment is not responsive. Occurs
--   when three or more consecutive failures occur for an environment.</li>
--   <li><tt>Yellow</tt>: Indicates that something is wrong. Occurs when
--   two consecutive failures occur for an environment.</li>
--   <li><tt>Green</tt>: Indicates the environment is healthy and fully
--   functional.</li>
--   <li><tt>Grey</tt>: Default health for a new environment. The
--   environment is not fully launched and health checks have not started
--   or health checks are suspended during an <tt>UpdateEnvironment</tt> or
--   <tt>RestartEnvironment</tt> request.</li>
--   </ul>
--   
--   Default: <tt>Grey</tt>
environmentDescription_health :: Lens' EnvironmentDescription (Maybe EnvironmentHealth)

-- | The application version deployed in this environment.
environmentDescription_versionLabel :: Lens' EnvironmentDescription (Maybe Text)

-- | The URL to the CNAME for this environment.
environmentDescription_cname :: Lens' EnvironmentDescription (Maybe Text)

-- | The last modified date for this environment.
environmentDescription_dateUpdated :: Lens' EnvironmentDescription (Maybe UTCTime)

-- | The description of the AWS resources used by this environment.
environmentDescription_resources :: Lens' EnvironmentDescription (Maybe EnvironmentResourcesDescription)

-- | Describes this environment.
environmentDescription_description :: Lens' EnvironmentDescription (Maybe Text)

-- | For load-balanced, autoscaling environments, the URL to the
--   LoadBalancer. For single-instance environments, the IP address of the
--   instance.
environmentDescription_endpointURL :: Lens' EnvironmentDescription (Maybe Text)

-- | Returns the health status of the application running in your
--   environment. For more information, see <a>Health Colors and
--   Statuses</a>.
environmentDescription_healthStatus :: Lens' EnvironmentDescription (Maybe EnvironmentHealthStatus)

-- | The environment's Amazon Resource Name (ARN), which can be used in
--   other API requests that require an ARN.
environmentDescription_environmentArn :: Lens' EnvironmentDescription (Maybe Text)

-- | The name of the application associated with this environment.
environmentDescription_applicationName :: Lens' EnvironmentDescription (Maybe Text)

-- | Describes the current tier of this environment.
environmentDescription_tier :: Lens' EnvironmentDescription (Maybe EnvironmentTier)

-- | The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the environment's operations role.
--   For more information, see <a>Operations roles</a> in the <i>AWS
--   Elastic Beanstalk Developer Guide</i>.
environmentDescription_operationsRole :: Lens' EnvironmentDescription (Maybe Text)

instance GHC.Show.Show Network.AWS.ElasticBeanstalk.UpdateEnvironment.UpdateEnvironment

-- | Update the list of tags applied to an AWS Elastic Beanstalk resource.
--   Two lists can be passed: <tt>TagsToAdd</tt> for tags to add or update,
--   and <tt>TagsToRemove</tt>.
--   
--   Elastic Beanstalk supports tagging of all of its resources. For
--   details about resource tagging, see <a>Tagging Application
--   Resources</a>.
--   
--   If you create a custom IAM user policy to control permission to this
--   operation, specify one of the following two virtual actions (or both)
--   instead of the API operation name:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li><i>elasticbeanstalk:AddTags</i> Controls permission to call
--   <tt>UpdateTagsForResource</tt> and pass a list of tags to add in the
--   <tt>TagsToAdd</tt> parameter.</li>
--   <li><i>elasticbeanstalk:RemoveTags</i> Controls permission to call
--   <tt>UpdateTagsForResource</tt> and pass a list of tag keys to remove
--   in the <tt>TagsToRemove</tt> parameter.</li>
--   </ul>
--   
--   For details about creating a custom user policy, see <a>Creating a
--   Custom User Policy</a>.
module Network.AWS.ElasticBeanstalk.UpdateTagsForResource

-- | <i>See:</i> <a>newUpdateTagsForResource</a> smart constructor.
data UpdateTagsForResource
UpdateTagsForResource' :: Maybe [Text] -> Maybe [Tag] -> Text -> UpdateTagsForResource

-- | A list of tag keys to remove. If a tag key doesn't exist, it is
--   silently ignored.
--   
--   Specify at least one of these parameters: <tt>TagsToAdd</tt>,
--   <tt>TagsToRemove</tt>.
[$sel:tagsToRemove:UpdateTagsForResource'] :: UpdateTagsForResource -> Maybe [Text]

-- | A list of tags to add or update. If a key of an existing tag is added,
--   the tag's value is updated.
--   
--   Specify at least one of these parameters: <tt>TagsToAdd</tt>,
--   <tt>TagsToRemove</tt>.
[$sel:tagsToAdd:UpdateTagsForResource'] :: UpdateTagsForResource -> Maybe [Tag]

-- | The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the resouce to be updated.
--   
--   Must be the ARN of an Elastic Beanstalk resource.
[$sel:resourceArn:UpdateTagsForResource'] :: UpdateTagsForResource -> Text

-- | Create a value of <a>UpdateTagsForResource</a> with all optional
--   fields omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:tagsToRemove:UpdateTagsForResource'</a>,
--   <a>updateTagsForResource_tagsToRemove</a> - A list of tag keys to
--   remove. If a tag key doesn't exist, it is silently ignored.
--   
--   Specify at least one of these parameters: <tt>TagsToAdd</tt>,
--   <tt>TagsToRemove</tt>.
--   
--   <a>$sel:tagsToAdd:UpdateTagsForResource'</a>,
--   <a>updateTagsForResource_tagsToAdd</a> - A list of tags to add or
--   update. If a key of an existing tag is added, the tag's value is
--   updated.
--   
--   Specify at least one of these parameters: <tt>TagsToAdd</tt>,
--   <tt>TagsToRemove</tt>.
--   
--   <a>$sel:resourceArn:UpdateTagsForResource'</a>,
--   <a>updateTagsForResource_resourceArn</a> - The Amazon Resource Name
--   (ARN) of the resouce to be updated.
--   
--   Must be the ARN of an Elastic Beanstalk resource.
newUpdateTagsForResource :: Text -> UpdateTagsForResource

-- | A list of tag keys to remove. If a tag key doesn't exist, it is
--   silently ignored.
--   
--   Specify at least one of these parameters: <tt>TagsToAdd</tt>,
--   <tt>TagsToRemove</tt>.
updateTagsForResource_tagsToRemove :: Lens' UpdateTagsForResource (Maybe [Text])

-- | A list of tags to add or update. If a key of an existing tag is added,
--   the tag's value is updated.
--   
--   Specify at least one of these parameters: <tt>TagsToAdd</tt>,
--   <tt>TagsToRemove</tt>.
updateTagsForResource_tagsToAdd :: Lens' UpdateTagsForResource (Maybe [Tag])

-- | The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the resouce to be updated.
--   
--   Must be the ARN of an Elastic Beanstalk resource.
updateTagsForResource_resourceArn :: Lens' UpdateTagsForResource Text

-- | Takes a set of configuration settings and either a configuration
--   template or environment, and determines whether those values are
--   valid.
--   
--   This action returns a list of messages indicating any errors or
--   warnings associated with the selection of option values.
module Network.AWS.ElasticBeanstalk.ValidateConfigurationSettings

-- | A list of validation messages for a specified configuration template.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newValidateConfigurationSettings</a> smart constructor.
data ValidateConfigurationSettings
ValidateConfigurationSettings' :: Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Text -> [ConfigurationOptionSetting] -> ValidateConfigurationSettings

-- | The name of the configuration template to validate the settings
--   against.
--   
--   Condition: You cannot specify both this and an environment name.
[$sel:templateName:ValidateConfigurationSettings'] :: ValidateConfigurationSettings -> Maybe Text

-- | The name of the environment to validate the settings against.
--   
--   Condition: You cannot specify both this and a configuration template
--   name.
[$sel:environmentName:ValidateConfigurationSettings'] :: ValidateConfigurationSettings -> Maybe Text

-- | The name of the application that the configuration template or
--   environment belongs to.
[$sel:applicationName:ValidateConfigurationSettings'] :: ValidateConfigurationSettings -> Text

-- | A list of the options and desired values to evaluate.
[$sel:optionSettings:ValidateConfigurationSettings'] :: ValidateConfigurationSettings -> [ConfigurationOptionSetting]

-- | Create a value of <a>ValidateConfigurationSettings</a> with all
--   optional fields omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:templateName:ValidateConfigurationSettings'</a>,
--   <a>validateConfigurationSettings_templateName</a> - The name of the
--   configuration template to validate the settings against.
--   
--   Condition: You cannot specify both this and an environment name.
--   
--   <a>$sel:environmentName:ValidateConfigurationSettings'</a>,
--   <a>validateConfigurationSettings_environmentName</a> - The name of the
--   environment to validate the settings against.
--   
--   Condition: You cannot specify both this and a configuration template
--   name.
--   
--   <a>$sel:applicationName:ValidateConfigurationSettings'</a>,
--   <a>validateConfigurationSettings_applicationName</a> - The name of the
--   application that the configuration template or environment belongs to.
--   
--   <a>$sel:optionSettings:ValidateConfigurationSettings'</a>,
--   <a>validateConfigurationSettings_optionSettings</a> - A list of the
--   options and desired values to evaluate.
newValidateConfigurationSettings :: Text -> ValidateConfigurationSettings

-- | The name of the configuration template to validate the settings
--   against.
--   
--   Condition: You cannot specify both this and an environment name.
validateConfigurationSettings_templateName :: Lens' ValidateConfigurationSettings (Maybe Text)

--   
--   Condition: You cannot specify both this and a configuration template
--   name.
validateConfigurationSettings_environmentName :: Lens' ValidateConfigurationSettings (Maybe Text)

-- | The name of the application that the configuration template or
--   environment belongs to.
validateConfigurationSettings_applicationName :: Lens' ValidateConfigurationSettings Text

-- | A list of the options and desired values to evaluate.
validateConfigurationSettings_optionSettings :: Lens' ValidateConfigurationSettings [ConfigurationOptionSetting]

data ValidateConfigurationSettingsResponse

module Network.AWS.ElasticBeanstalk.Lens

-- | For a paginated request. Specify a token from a previous response page
--   to retrieve the next response page. All other parameter values must be
--   identical to the ones specified in the initial request.
--   
--   If no <tt>NextToken</tt> is specified, the first page is retrieved.
listPlatformBranches_nextToken :: Lens' ListPlatformBranches (Maybe Text)

-- | Criteria for restricting the resulting list of platform branches. The
--   filter is evaluated as a logical conjunction (AND) of the separate
--   <tt>SearchFilter</tt> terms.
--   
--   The following list shows valid attribute values for each of the
--   <tt>SearchFilter</tt> terms. Most operators take a single value. The
--   <tt>in</tt> and <tt>not_in</tt> operators can take multiple values.
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li><tt>Attribute = BranchName</tt>:<ul><li><tt>Operator</tt>:
--   <tt>=</tt> | <tt>!=</tt> | <tt>begins_with</tt> | <tt>ends_with</tt> |
--   <tt>contains</tt> | <tt>in</tt> | <tt>not_in</tt></li></ul></li>
--   <li><tt>Attribute = LifecycleState</tt>:<ul><li><tt>Operator</tt>:
--   <tt>=</tt> | <tt>!=</tt> | <tt>in</tt> |
--   <tt>not_in</tt></li><li><tt>Values</tt>: <tt>beta</tt> |
--   <tt>supported</tt> | <tt>deprecated</tt> |
--   <tt>retired</tt></li></ul></li>
--   <li><tt>Attribute = PlatformName</tt>:<ul><li><tt>Operator</tt>:
--   <tt>=</tt> | <tt>!=</tt> | <tt>begins_with</tt> | <tt>ends_with</tt> |
--   <tt>contains</tt> | <tt>in</tt> | <tt>not_in</tt></li></ul></li>
--   <li><tt>Attribute = TierType</tt>:<ul><li><tt>Operator</tt>:
--   <tt>=</tt> | <tt>!=</tt></li><li><tt>Values</tt>:
--   <tt>WebServer/Standard</tt> | <tt>Worker/SQS/HTTP</tt></li></ul></li>
--   </ul>
--   
--   Array size: limited to 10 <tt>SearchFilter</tt> objects.
--   
--   Within each <tt>SearchFilter</tt> item, the <tt>Values</tt> array is
--   limited to 10 items.
listPlatformBranches_filters :: Lens' ListPlatformBranches (Maybe [SearchFilter])

-- | The maximum number of platform branch values returned in one call.
listPlatformBranches_maxRecords :: Lens' ListPlatformBranches (Maybe Natural)

-- | In a paginated request, if this value isn't <tt>null</tt>, it's the
--   token that you can pass in a subsequent request to get the next
--   response page.
listPlatformBranchesResponse_nextToken :: Lens' ListPlatformBranchesResponse (Maybe Text)

-- | Summary information about the platform branches.
listPlatformBranchesResponse_platformBranchSummaryList :: Lens' ListPlatformBranchesResponse (Maybe [PlatformBranchSummary])

-- | The response's http status code.
listPlatformBranchesResponse_httpStatus :: Lens' ListPlatformBranchesResponse Int

--   or the <tt>SourceEnvironmentName</tt>. You may also specify both. If
--   you specify the <tt>SourceEnvironmentName</tt>, you must specify the
--   <tt>DestinationEnvironmentName</tt>.

--   must specify the <tt>SourceEnvironmentId</tt> with the

swapEnvironmentCNAMEs_destinationEnvironmentName :: Lens' SwapEnvironmentCNAMEs (Maybe Text)

-- | The Amazon S3 bucket and key that identify the location of the source
--   bundle for this version.
--   
--   The Amazon S3 bucket must be in the same region as the environment.
--   
--   Specify a source bundle in S3 or a commit in an AWS CodeCommit
--   repository (with <tt>SourceBuildInformation</tt>), but not both. If
--   neither <tt>SourceBundle</tt> nor <tt>SourceBuildInformation</tt> are
--   provided, Elastic Beanstalk uses a sample application.

--   
--   Elastic Beanstalk applies these tags only to the application version.
--   Environments that use the application version don't inherit the tags.
createApplicationVersion_tags :: Lens' CreateApplicationVersion (Maybe [Tag])

--   if it doesn't already exist.
createApplicationVersion_autoCreateApplication :: Lens' CreateApplicationVersion (Maybe Bool)

-- | A description of this application version.
createApplicationVersion_description :: Lens' CreateApplicationVersion (Maybe Text)

-- | Pre-processes and validates the environment manifest
--   (<tt>env.yaml</tt>) and configuration files (<tt>*.config</tt> files
--   in the <tt>.ebextensions</tt> folder) in the source bundle. Validating
--   configuration files can identify issues prior to deploying the
--   application version to an environment.
--   
--   You must turn processing on for application versions that you create
--   using AWS CodeBuild or AWS CodeCommit. For application versions built
--   from a source bundle in Amazon S3, processing is optional.
--   
--   The <tt>Process</tt> option validates Elastic Beanstalk configuration
--   files. It doesn't validate your application's configuration files,
--   like proxy server or Docker configuration.
createApplicationVersion_process :: Lens' CreateApplicationVersion (Maybe Bool)

-- | The name of the application. If no application is found with this
--   name, and <tt>AutoCreateApplication</tt> is <tt>false</tt>, returns an
--   <tt>InvalidParameterValue</tt> error.
createApplicationVersion_applicationName :: Lens' CreateApplicationVersion Text

-- | A label identifying this version.
--   
--   Constraint: Must be unique per application. If an application version
--   already exists with this label for the specified application, AWS
--   Elastic Beanstalk returns an <tt>InvalidParameterValue</tt> error.
createApplicationVersion_versionLabel :: Lens' CreateApplicationVersion Text

-- | The ApplicationVersionDescription of the application version.
applicationVersionDescriptionMessage_applicationVersion :: Lens' ApplicationVersionDescriptionMessage (Maybe ApplicationVersionDescription)

-- | The ID of an environment whose settings you want to use to create the
--   configuration template. You must specify <tt>EnvironmentId</tt> if you
--   don't specify <tt>PlatformArn</tt>, <tt>SolutionStackName</tt>, or
--   <tt>SourceConfiguration</tt>.
createConfigurationTemplate_environmentId :: Lens' CreateConfigurationTemplate (Maybe Text)

-- | The name of an Elastic Beanstalk solution stack (platform version)
--   that this configuration uses. For example, <tt>64bit Amazon Linux
--   2013.09 running Tomcat 7 Java 7</tt>. A solution stack specifies the
--   operating system, runtime, and application server for a configuration
--   template. It also determines the set of configuration options as well
--   as the possible and default values. For more information, see
--   <a>Supported Platforms</a> in the <i>AWS Elastic Beanstalk Developer
--   Guide</i>.
--   
--   You must specify <tt>SolutionStackName</tt> if you don't specify
--   <tt>PlatformArn</tt>, <tt>EnvironmentId</tt>, or
--   <tt>SourceConfiguration</tt>.
--   
--   Use the <a>ListAvailableSolutionStacks</a> API to obtain a list of
--   available solution stacks.
createConfigurationTemplate_solutionStackName :: Lens' CreateConfigurationTemplate (Maybe Text)

-- | The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the custom platform. For more
--   information, see <a>Custom Platforms</a> in the <i>AWS Elastic
--   Beanstalk Developer Guide</i>.
--   
--   If you specify <tt>PlatformArn</tt>, then don't specify
--   <tt>SolutionStackName</tt>.
createConfigurationTemplate_platformArn :: Lens' CreateConfigurationTemplate (Maybe Text)

-- | Specifies the tags applied to the configuration template.
createConfigurationTemplate_tags :: Lens' CreateConfigurationTemplate (Maybe [Tag])

-- | Option values for the Elastic Beanstalk configuration, such as the
--   instance type. If specified, these values override the values obtained
--   from the solution stack or the source configuration template. For a
--   complete list of Elastic Beanstalk configuration options, see
--   <a>Option Values</a> in the <i>AWS Elastic Beanstalk Developer
--   Guide</i>.
createConfigurationTemplate_optionSettings :: Lens' CreateConfigurationTemplate (Maybe [ConfigurationOptionSetting])

-- | An optional description for this configuration.
createConfigurationTemplate_description :: Lens' CreateConfigurationTemplate (Maybe Text)

-- | An Elastic Beanstalk configuration template to base this one on. If
--   specified, Elastic Beanstalk uses the configuration values from the
--   specified configuration template to create a new configuration.
--   
--   Values specified in <tt>OptionSettings</tt> override any values
--   obtained from the <tt>SourceConfiguration</tt>.
--   
--   You must specify <tt>SourceConfiguration</tt> if you don't specify
--   <tt>PlatformArn</tt>, <tt>EnvironmentId</tt>, or
--   <tt>SolutionStackName</tt>.
--   
--   Constraint: If both solution stack name and source configuration are
--   specified, the solution stack of the source configuration template
--   must match the specified solution stack name.
createConfigurationTemplate_sourceConfiguration :: Lens' CreateConfigurationTemplate (Maybe SourceConfiguration)

-- | The name of the Elastic Beanstalk application to associate with this
--   configuration template.
createConfigurationTemplate_applicationName :: Lens' CreateConfigurationTemplate Text

-- | The name of the configuration template.
--   
--   Constraint: This name must be unique per application.
createConfigurationTemplate_templateName :: Lens' CreateConfigurationTemplate Text

-- | If not <tt>null</tt>, the name of the configuration template for this
--   configuration set.
configurationSettingsDescription_templateName :: Lens' ConfigurationSettingsDescription (Maybe Text)

-- | The date (in UTC time) when this configuration set was created.
configurationSettingsDescription_dateCreated :: Lens' ConfigurationSettingsDescription (Maybe UTCTime)

-- | The name of the solution stack this configuration set uses.
configurationSettingsDescription_solutionStackName :: Lens' ConfigurationSettingsDescription (Maybe Text)

-- | If this configuration set is associated with an environment, the
--   <tt>DeploymentStatus</tt> parameter indicates the deployment status of
--   this configuration set:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li><tt>null</tt>: This configuration is not associated with a running
--   environment.</li>
--   <li><tt>pending</tt>: This is a draft configuration that is not
--   deployed to the associated environment but is in the process of
--   deploying.</li>
--   <li><tt>deployed</tt>: This is the configuration that is currently
--   deployed to the associated running environment.</li>
--   <li><tt>failed</tt>: This is a draft configuration that failed to
--   successfully deploy.</li>
--   </ul>
configurationSettingsDescription_deploymentStatus :: Lens' ConfigurationSettingsDescription (Maybe ConfigurationDeploymentStatus)

-- | The ARN of the platform version.
configurationSettingsDescription_platformArn :: Lens' ConfigurationSettingsDescription (Maybe Text)

-- | If not <tt>null</tt>, the name of the environment for this
--   configuration set.
configurationSettingsDescription_environmentName :: Lens' ConfigurationSettingsDescription (Maybe Text)

-- | The date (in UTC time) when this configuration set was last modified.
configurationSettingsDescription_dateUpdated :: Lens' ConfigurationSettingsDescription (Maybe UTCTime)

-- | A list of the configuration options and their values in this
--   configuration set.
configurationSettingsDescription_optionSettings :: Lens' ConfigurationSettingsDescription (Maybe [ConfigurationOptionSetting])

-- | Describes this configuration set.
configurationSettingsDescription_description :: Lens' ConfigurationSettingsDescription (Maybe Text)

-- | The name of the application associated with this configuration set.
configurationSettingsDescription_applicationName :: Lens' ConfigurationSettingsDescription (Maybe Text)

-- | Terminates the target environment even if another environment in the
--   same group is dependent on it.
terminateEnvironment_forceTerminate :: Lens' TerminateEnvironment (Maybe Bool)

-- | The ID of the environment to terminate.
--   
--   Condition: You must specify either this or an EnvironmentName, or
--   both. If you do not specify either, AWS Elastic Beanstalk returns
--   <tt>MissingRequiredParameter</tt> error.
terminateEnvironment_environmentId :: Lens' TerminateEnvironment (Maybe Text)

-- | Indicates whether the associated AWS resources should shut down when
--   the environment is terminated:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li><tt>true</tt>: The specified environment as well as the associated
--   AWS resources, such as Auto Scaling group and LoadBalancer, are
--   terminated.</li>
--   <li><tt>false</tt>: AWS Elastic Beanstalk resource management is
--   removed from the environment, but the AWS resources continue to
--   operate.</li>
--   </ul>
--   
--   For more information, see the <a>AWS Elastic Beanstalk User Guide.</a>
--   
--   Default: <tt>true</tt>
--   
--   Valid Values: <tt>true</tt> | <tt>false</tt>
terminateEnvironment_terminateResources :: Lens' TerminateEnvironment (Maybe Bool)

-- | The name of the environment to terminate.
--   
--   Condition: You must specify either this or an EnvironmentId, or both.
--   If you do not specify either, AWS Elastic Beanstalk returns
--   <tt>MissingRequiredParameter</tt> error.
terminateEnvironment_environmentName :: Lens' TerminateEnvironment (Maybe Text)

--   or application version deployment that you can cancel.

--   
--   <tt>false:</tt> There are no updates currently in progress.
environmentDescription_abortableOperationInProgress :: Lens' EnvironmentDescription (Maybe Bool)

-- | The name of the configuration template used to originally launch this
--   environment.
environmentDescription_templateName :: Lens' EnvironmentDescription (Maybe Text)

-- | The current operational status of the environment:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li><tt>Launching</tt>: Environment is in the process of initial
--   deployment.</li>
--   <li><tt>Updating</tt>: Environment is in the process of updating its
--   configuration settings or application version.</li>
--   <li><tt>Ready</tt>: Environment is available to have an action
--   performed on it, such as update or terminate.</li>
--   <li><tt>Terminating</tt>: Environment is in the shut-down
--   process.</li>
--   <li><tt>Terminated</tt>: Environment is not running.</li>
--   </ul>
environmentDescription_status :: Lens' EnvironmentDescription (Maybe EnvironmentStatus)

-- | The ARN of the platform version.
environmentDescription_platformArn :: Lens' EnvironmentDescription (Maybe Text)

-- | The name of this environment.
environmentDescription_environmentName :: Lens' EnvironmentDescription (Maybe Text)

-- | Describes the health status of the environment. AWS Elastic Beanstalk
--   indicates the failure levels for a running environment:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li><tt>Red</tt>: Indicates the environment is not responsive. Occurs
--   when three or more consecutive failures occur for an environment.</li>
--   <li><tt>Yellow</tt>: Indicates that something is wrong. Occurs when
--   two consecutive failures occur for an environment.</li>
--   <li><tt>Green</tt>: Indicates the environment is healthy and fully
--   functional.</li>
--   <li><tt>Grey</tt>: Default health for a new environment. The
--   environment is not fully launched and health checks have not started
--   or health checks are suspended during an <tt>UpdateEnvironment</tt> or
--   <tt>RestartEnvironment</tt> request.</li>
--   </ul>
--   
--   Default: <tt>Grey</tt>
environmentDescription_health :: Lens' EnvironmentDescription (Maybe EnvironmentHealth)

environmentDescription_versionLabel :: Lens' EnvironmentDescription (Maybe Text)

environmentDescription_dateUpdated :: Lens' EnvironmentDescription (Maybe UTCTime)

-- | Describes this environment.
environmentDescription_description :: Lens' EnvironmentDescription (Maybe Text)

--   Constraint: Must be from 4 to 40 characters in length. The name can
--   contain only letters, numbers, and hyphens. It can't start or end with
--   a hyphen. This name must be unique within a region in your account. If
--   the specified name already exists in the region, Elastic Beanstalk
--   returns an <tt>InvalidParameterValue</tt> error.

-- | Describes the health status of the environment. AWS Elastic Beanstalk
--   indicates the failure levels for a running environment:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li><tt>Red</tt>: Indicates the environment is not responsive. Occurs
--   when three or more consecutive failures occur for an environment.</li>
--   <li><tt>Yellow</tt>: Indicates that something is wrong. Occurs when
--   two consecutive failures occur for an environment.</li>
--   <li><tt>Green</tt>: Indicates the environment is healthy and fully
--   functional.</li>
--   <li><tt>Grey</tt>: Default health for a new environment. The
--   environment is not fully launched and health checks have not started
--   or health checks are suspended during an <tt>UpdateEnvironment</tt> or
--   <tt>RestartEnvironment</tt> request.</li>
--   </ul>
--   
--   Default: <tt>Grey</tt>
environmentDescription_health :: Lens' EnvironmentDescription (Maybe EnvironmentHealth)

--   to assume.
--   
--   The <tt>ServiceRole</tt> property is required the first time that you
--   provide a <tt>VersionLifecycleConfig</tt> for the application in one
--   of the supporting calls (<tt>CreateApplication</tt> or
--   <tt>UpdateApplicationResourceLifecycle</tt>). After you provide it
--   once, in either one of the calls, Elastic Beanstalk persists the
--   Service Role with the application, and you don't need to specify it
--   again in subsequent <tt>UpdateApplicationResourceLifecycle</tt> calls.
--   You can, however, specify it in subsequent calls to change the Service
--   Role to another value.

-- | The processing status of the application version. Reflects the state
--   of the application version during its creation. Many of the values are
--   only applicable if you specified <tt>True</tt> for the
--   <tt>Process</tt> parameter of the <tt>CreateApplicationVersion</tt>
--   action. The following list describes the possible values.
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li><tt>Unprocessed</tt> – Application version wasn't pre-processed or
--   validated. Elastic Beanstalk will validate configuration files during
--   deployment of the application version to an environment.</li>
--   <li><tt>Processing</tt> – Elastic Beanstalk is currently processing
--   the application version.</li>
--   <li><tt>Building</tt> – Application version is currently undergoing an
--   AWS CodeBuild build.</li>
--   <li><tt>Processed</tt> – Elastic Beanstalk was successfully
--   pre-processed and validated.</li>
--   <li><tt>Failed</tt> – Either the AWS CodeBuild build failed or
--   configuration files didn't pass validation. This application version
--   isn't usable.</li>
--   </ul>
applicationVersionDescription_status :: Lens' ApplicationVersionDescription (Maybe ApplicationVersionStatus)

-- | An indication of which type of values this option has and whether it
--   is allowable to select one or more than one of the possible values:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li><tt>Scalar</tt> : Values for this option are a single selection
--   from the possible values, or an unformatted string, or numeric value
--   governed by the <tt>MIN/MAX/Regex</tt> constraints.</li>
--   <li><tt>List</tt> : Values for this option are multiple selections
--   from the possible values.</li>
--   <li><tt>Boolean</tt> : Values for this option are either <tt>true</tt>
--   or <tt>false</tt> .</li>
--   <li><tt>Json</tt> : Values for this option are a JSON representation
--   of a <tt>ConfigDocument</tt>.</li>
--   </ul>

-- | An indication of which action is required if the value for this
--   configuration option changes:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li><tt>NoInterruption</tt> : There is no interruption to the
--   environment or application availability.</li>
--   <li><tt>RestartEnvironment</tt> : The environment is entirely
--   restarted, all AWS resources are deleted and recreated, and the
--   environment is unavailable during the process.</li>
--   <li><tt>RestartApplicationServer</tt> : The environment is available
--   the entire time. However, a short application outage occurs when the
--   application servers on the running Amazon EC2 instances are
--   restarted.</li>
--   </ul>
configurationOptionDescription_changeSeverity :: Lens' ConfigurationOptionDescription (Maybe Text)

-- | Describes the health status of the environment. AWS Elastic Beanstalk
--   indicates the failure levels for a running environment:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li><tt>Red</tt>: Indicates the environment is not responsive. Occurs
--   when three or more consecutive failures occur for an environment.</li>
--   <li><tt>Yellow</tt>: Indicates that something is wrong. Occurs when
--   two consecutive failures occur for an environment.</li>
--   <li><tt>Green</tt>: Indicates the environment is healthy and fully
--   functional.</li>
--   <li><tt>Grey</tt>: Default health for a new environment. The
--   environment is not fully launched and health checks have not started
--   or health checks are suspended during an <tt>UpdateEnvironment</tt> or
--   <tt>RestartEnvironment</tt> request.</li>
--   </ul>
--   
--   Default: <tt>Grey</tt>

--   state is reached. An error is returned after 20 failed checks.

-- | API version <tt>2010-12-01</tt> of the Amazon Elastic Beanstalk SDK
--   configuration.
defaultService :: Service

-- | You have exceeded the maximum number of allowed platforms associated
--   with the account.
_TooManyPlatformsException :: AsError a => Getting (First ServiceError) a ServiceError

-- | The number of tags in the resource would exceed the number of tags
--   that each resource can have.
--   
--   To calculate this, the operation considers both the number of tags the
--   resource already has and the tags this operation would add if it
--   succeeded.
_TooManyTagsException :: AsError a => Getting (First ServiceError) a ServiceError

-- | The specified account has reached its limit of applications.
_TooManyApplicationsException :: AsError a => Getting (First ServiceError) a ServiceError

-- | The specified account has reached its limit of environments.
_TooManyEnvironmentsException :: AsError a => Getting (First ServiceError) a ServiceError

-- | The specified account does not have sufficient privileges for one or
--   more AWS services.
_InsufficientPrivilegesException :: AsError a => Getting (First ServiceError) a ServiceError

-- | The type of the specified Amazon Resource Name (ARN) isn't supported
--   for this operation.
_ResourceTypeNotSupportedException :: AsError a => Getting (First ServiceError) a ServiceError

-- | The specified account has reached its limit of configuration
--   templates.
_TooManyConfigurationTemplatesException :: AsError a => Getting (First ServiceError) a ServiceError

-- | Unable to perform the specified operation because another operation
--   that effects an element in this activity is already in progress.
_OperationInProgressException :: AsError a => Getting (First ServiceError) a ServiceError

-- | The specified account has reached its limit of Amazon S3 buckets.
_TooManyBucketsException :: AsError a => Getting (First ServiceError) a ServiceError

-- | The specified account does not have a subscription to Amazon S3.
_S3SubscriptionRequiredException :: AsError a => Getting (First ServiceError) a ServiceError

-- | Unable to delete the Amazon S3 source bundle associated with the
--   application version. The application version was deleted successfully.
_SourceBundleDeletionException :: AsError a => Getting (First ServiceError) a ServiceError

-- | One or more input parameters is not valid. Please correct the input
--   parameters and try the operation again.
_InvalidRequestException :: AsError a => Getting (First ServiceError) a ServiceError

-- | A generic service exception has occurred.
_ElasticBeanstalkServiceException :: AsError a => Getting (First ServiceError) a ServiceError

-- | A resource doesn't exist for the specified Amazon Resource Name (ARN).
_ResourceNotFoundException :: AsError a => Getting (First ServiceError) a ServiceError

-- | The specified account has reached its limit of application versions.
_TooManyApplicationVersionsException :: AsError a => Getting (First ServiceError) a ServiceError

-- | AWS CodeBuild is not available in the specified region.
_CodeBuildNotInServiceRegionException :: AsError a => Getting (First ServiceError) a ServiceError

-- | You cannot delete the platform version because there are still
--   environments running on it.
_PlatformVersionStillReferencedException :: AsError a => Getting (First ServiceError) a ServiceError

-- | The specified S3 bucket does not belong to the S3 region in which the
--   service is running. The following regions are supported:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li>IAD/us-east-1</li>
--   <li>PDX/us-west-2</li>
--   <li>DUB/eu-west-1</li>
--   </ul>
_S3LocationNotInServiceRegionException :: AsError a => Getting (First ServiceError) a ServiceError

-- | Cannot modify the managed action in its current state.
_ManagedActionInvalidStateException :: AsError a => Getting (First ServiceError) a ServiceError

-- | <i>See:</i> <a>newListPlatformBranches</a> smart constructor.
data ListPlatformBranches
ListPlatformBranches' :: Maybe Text -> Maybe [SearchFilter] -> Maybe Natural -> ListPlatformBranches

-- | Create a value of <a>ListPlatformBranches</a> with all optional fields
--   omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:nextToken:ListPlatformBranches'</a>,
--   <a>listPlatformBranches_nextToken</a> - For a paginated request.
--   Specify a token from a previous response page to retrieve the next
--   response page. All other parameter values must be identical to the
--   ones specified in the initial request.
--   
--   If no <tt>NextToken</tt> is specified, the first page is retrieved.
--   
--   <a>$sel:filters:ListPlatformBranches'</a>,
--   <a>listPlatformBranches_filters</a> - Criteria for restricting the
--   resulting list of platform branches. The filter is evaluated as a
--   logical conjunction (AND) of the separate <tt>SearchFilter</tt> terms.
--   
--   The following list shows valid attribute values for each of the
--   <tt>SearchFilter</tt> terms. Most operators take a single value. The
--   <tt>in</tt> and <tt>not_in</tt> operators can take multiple values.
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li><tt>Attribute = BranchName</tt>:<ul><li><tt>Operator</tt>:
--   <tt>=</tt> | <tt>!=</tt> | <tt>begins_with</tt> | <tt>ends_with</tt> |
--   <tt>contains</tt> | <tt>in</tt> | <tt>not_in</tt></li></ul></li>
--   <li><tt>Attribute = LifecycleState</tt>:<ul><li><tt>Operator</tt>:
--   <tt>=</tt> | <tt>!=</tt> | <tt>in</tt> |
--   <tt>not_in</tt></li><li><tt>Values</tt>: <tt>beta</tt> |
--   <tt>supported</tt> | <tt>deprecated</tt> |
--   <tt>retired</tt></li></ul></li>
--   <li><tt>Attribute = PlatformName</tt>:<ul><li><tt>Operator</tt>:
--   <tt>=</tt> | <tt>!=</tt> | <tt>begins_with</tt> | <tt>ends_with</tt> |
--   <tt>contains</tt> | <tt>in</tt> | <tt>not_in</tt></li></ul></li>
--   <li><tt>Attribute = TierType</tt>:<ul><li><tt>Operator</tt>:
--   <tt>=</tt> | <tt>!=</tt></li><li><tt>Values</tt>:
--   <tt>WebServer/Standard</tt> | <tt>Worker/SQS/HTTP</tt></li></ul></li>
--   </ul>
--   
--   Array size: limited to 10 <tt>SearchFilter</tt> objects.
--   
--   Within each <tt>SearchFilter</tt> item, the <tt>Values</tt> array is
--   limited to 10 items.
--

-- | Create a value of <a>CreateApplicationVersion</a> with all optional

--   source bundle. Validating configuration files can identify issues
--   prior to deploying the application version to an environment.
--   
--   You must turn processing on for application versions that you create
--   using AWS CodeBuild or AWS CodeCommit. For application versions built
--   from a source bundle in Amazon S3, processing is optional.
--

--   files. It doesn't validate your application's configuration files,
--   like proxy server or Docker configuration.

--   this version.
--
