--   template. You must specify <tt>EnvironmentId</tt> if you don't specify
--   <tt>PlatformArn</tt>, <tt>SolutionStackName</tt>, or
--   <tt>SourceConfiguration</tt>.
--   
--   <a>$sel:solutionStackName:CreateConfigurationTemplate'</a>,
--   <a>createConfigurationTemplate_solutionStackName</a> - The name of an
--   Elastic Beanstalk solution stack (platform version) that this
--   configuration uses. For example, <tt>64bit Amazon Linux 2013.09
--   running Tomcat 7 Java 7</tt>. A solution stack specifies the operating
--   system, runtime, and application server for a configuration template.
--   It also determines the set of configuration options as well as the
--   possible and default values. For more information, see <a>Supported
--   Platforms</a> in the <i>AWS Elastic Beanstalk Developer Guide</i>.
--   
--   You must specify <tt>SolutionStackName</tt> if you don't specify
--   <tt>PlatformArn</tt>, <tt>EnvironmentId</tt>, or
--   <tt>SourceConfiguration</tt>.
--   
--   Use the <a>ListAvailableSolutionStacks</a> API to obtain a list of
--   available solution stacks.
--   
--   <a>$sel:platformArn:CreateConfigurationTemplate'</a>,
--   <a>createConfigurationTemplate_platformArn</a> - The Amazon Resource
--   Name (ARN) of the custom platform. For more information, see <a>Custom
--   Platforms</a> in the <i>AWS Elastic Beanstalk Developer Guide</i>.
--   
--   If you specify <tt>PlatformArn</tt>, then don't specify
--   <tt>SolutionStackName</tt>.
--   
--   <a>$sel:tags:CreateConfigurationTemplate'</a>,
--   <a>createConfigurationTemplate_tags</a> - Specifies the tags applied
--   to the configuration template.
--   
--   <a>$sel:optionSettings:CreateConfigurationTemplate'</a>,
--   <a>createConfigurationTemplate_optionSettings</a> - Option values for
--   the Elastic Beanstalk configuration, such as the instance type. If
--   specified, these values override the values obtained from the solution
--   stack or the source configuration template. For a complete list of
--   Elastic Beanstalk configuration options, see <a>Option Values</a> in
--   the <i>AWS Elastic Beanstalk Developer Guide</i>.
--   
--   <a>$sel:description:CreateConfigurationTemplate'</a>,
--   <a>createConfigurationTemplate_description</a> - An optional
--   description for this configuration.
--   
--   <a>$sel:sourceConfiguration:CreateConfigurationTemplate'</a>,
--   <a>createConfigurationTemplate_sourceConfiguration</a> - An Elastic
--   Beanstalk configuration template to base this one on. If specified,
--   Elastic Beanstalk uses the configuration values from the specified
--   configuration template to create a new configuration.
--   
--   Values specified in <tt>OptionSettings</tt> override any values
--   obtained from the <tt>SourceConfiguration</tt>.
--   
--   You must specify <tt>SourceConfiguration</tt> if you don't specify
--   <tt>PlatformArn</tt>, <tt>EnvironmentId</tt>, or
--   <tt>SolutionStackName</tt>.
--   
--   Constraint: If both solution stack name and source configuration are
--   specified, the solution stack of the source configuration template
--   must match the specified solution stack name.
--   
--   <a>$sel:applicationName:CreateConfigurationTemplate'</a>,

--   template.
--   
--   <a>$sel:templateName:CreateConfigurationTemplate'</a>,
--   <a>createConfigurationTemplate_templateName</a> - The name of the
--   configuration template.
--   
--   Constraint: This name must be unique per application.

--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:forceTerminate:TerminateEnvironment'</a>,
--   <a>terminateEnvironment_forceTerminate</a> - Terminates the target
--   environment even if another environment in the same group is dependent
--   on it.
--   
--   <a>$sel:environmentId:TerminateEnvironment'</a>,
--   <a>terminateEnvironment_environmentId</a> - The ID of the environment
--   to terminate.
--   
--   Condition: You must specify either this or an EnvironmentName, or
--   both. If you do not specify either, AWS Elastic Beanstalk returns
--   <tt>MissingRequiredParameter</tt> error.
--   
--   <a>$sel:terminateResources:TerminateEnvironment'</a>,
--   <a>terminateEnvironment_terminateResources</a> - Indicates whether the
--   associated AWS resources should shut down when the environment is
--   terminated:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li><tt>true</tt>: The specified environment as well as the associated
--   AWS resources, such as Auto Scaling group and LoadBalancer, are
--   terminated.</li>
--   <li><tt>false</tt>: AWS Elastic Beanstalk resource management is
--   removed from the environment, but the AWS resources continue to
--   operate.</li>
--   </ul>
--   
--   For more information, see the <a>AWS Elastic Beanstalk User Guide.</a>
--   
--   Default: <tt>true</tt>
--   
--   Valid Values: <tt>true</tt> | <tt>false</tt>
--   
--   <a>$sel:environmentName:TerminateEnvironment'</a>,
--   <a>terminateEnvironment_environmentName</a> - The name of the
--   environment to terminate.
--   
--   Condition: You must specify either this or an EnvironmentId, or both.
--   If you do not specify either, AWS Elastic Beanstalk returns
--   <tt>MissingRequiredParameter</tt> error.
newTerminateEnvironment :: TerminateEnvironment

-- | Describes the properties of an environment.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newEnvironmentDescription</a> smart constructor.
data EnvironmentDescription
EnvironmentDescription' :: Maybe Bool -> Maybe Text -> Maybe EnvironmentStatus -> Maybe ISO8601 -> Maybe [EnvironmentLink] -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe EnvironmentHealth -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe ISO8601 -> Maybe EnvironmentResourcesDescription -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe EnvironmentHealthStatus -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe EnvironmentTier -> Maybe Text -> EnvironmentDescription

-- | Create a value of <a>EnvironmentDescription</a> with all optional
--   fields omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:abortableOperationInProgress:EnvironmentDescription'</a>,
--   <a>environmentDescription_abortableOperationInProgress</a> - Indicates
--   if there is an in-progress environment configuration update or
--   application version deployment that you can cancel.
--   
--   <tt>true:</tt> There is an update in progress.
--   
--   <tt>false:</tt> There are no updates currently in progress.
--   
--   <a>$sel:templateName:EnvironmentDescription'</a>,
--   <a>environmentDescription_templateName</a> - The name of the
--   configuration template used to originally launch this environment.
--   
--   <a>$sel:status:EnvironmentDescription'</a>,
--   <a>environmentDescription_status</a> - The current operational status
--   of the environment:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li><tt>Launching</tt>: Environment is in the process of initial
--   deployment.</li>
--   <li><tt>Updating</tt>: Environment is in the process of updating its
--   configuration settings or application version.</li>
--   <li><tt>Ready</tt>: Environment is available to have an action
--   performed on it, such as update or terminate.</li>
--   <li><tt>Terminating</tt>: Environment is in the shut-down
--   process.</li>
--   <li><tt>Terminated</tt>: Environment is not running.</li>
--   </ul>
--   
--   <a>$sel:dateCreated:EnvironmentDescription'</a>,
--   <a>environmentDescription_dateCreated</a> - The creation date for this
--   environment.
--   
--   <a>$sel:environmentLinks:EnvironmentDescription'</a>,
--   <a>environmentDescription_environmentLinks</a> - A list of links to
--   other environments in the same group.
--   
--   <a>$sel:environmentId:EnvironmentDescription'</a>,
--   <a>environmentDescription_environmentId</a> - The ID of this
--   environment.
--   
--   <a>$sel:solutionStackName:EnvironmentDescription'</a>,
--   <a>environmentDescription_solutionStackName</a> - The name of the
--   <tt>SolutionStack</tt> deployed with this environment.
--   
--   <a>$sel:platformArn:EnvironmentDescription'</a>,
--   <a>environmentDescription_platformArn</a> - The ARN of the platform
--   version.
--   
--   <a>$sel:environmentName:EnvironmentDescription'</a>,
--   <a>environmentDescription_environmentName</a> - The name of this
--   environment.
--   
--   <a>$sel:health:EnvironmentDescription'</a>,
--   <a>environmentDescription_health</a> - Describes the health status of
--   the environment. AWS Elastic Beanstalk indicates the failure levels
--   for a running environment:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li><tt>Red</tt>: Indicates the environment is not responsive. Occurs
--   when three or more consecutive failures occur for an environment.</li>
--   <li><tt>Yellow</tt>: Indicates that something is wrong. Occurs when
--   two consecutive failures occur for an environment.</li>
--   <li><tt>Green</tt>: Indicates the environment is healthy and fully
--   functional.</li>
--   <li><tt>Grey</tt>: Default health for a new environment. The
--   environment is not fully launched and health checks have not started
--   or health checks are suspended during an <tt>UpdateEnvironment</tt> or
--   <tt>RestartEnvironment</tt> request.</li>
--   </ul>
--   
--   Default: <tt>Grey</tt>
--   
--   <a>$sel:versionLabel:EnvironmentDescription'</a>,
--   <a>environmentDescription_versionLabel</a> - The application version
--   deployed in this environment.
--   
--   <a>$sel:cname:EnvironmentDescription'</a>,
--   <a>environmentDescription_cname</a> - The URL to the CNAME for this
--   environment.
--   
--   <a>$sel:dateUpdated:EnvironmentDescription'</a>,
--   <a>environmentDescription_dateUpdated</a> - The last modified date for
--   this environment.
--   
--   <a>$sel:resources:EnvironmentDescription'</a>,
--   <a>environmentDescription_resources</a> - The description of the AWS
--   resources used by this environment.
--   
--   <a>$sel:description:EnvironmentDescription'</a>,
--   <a>environmentDescription_description</a> - Describes this
--   environment.
--   
--   <a>$sel:endpointURL:EnvironmentDescription'</a>,
--   <a>environmentDescription_endpointURL</a> - For load-balanced,
--   autoscaling environments, the URL to the LoadBalancer. For
--   single-instance environments, the IP address of the instance.
--   
--   <a>$sel:healthStatus:EnvironmentDescription'</a>,
--   <a>environmentDescription_healthStatus</a> - Returns the health status
--   of the application running in your environment. For more information,
--   see <a>Health Colors and Statuses</a>.
--   
--   <a>$sel:environmentArn:EnvironmentDescription'</a>,
--   <a>environmentDescription_environmentArn</a> - The environment's
--   Amazon Resource Name (ARN), which can be used in other API requests
--   that require an ARN.
--   
--   <a>$sel:applicationName:EnvironmentDescription'</a>,
--   <a>environmentDescription_applicationName</a> - The name of the
--   application associated with this environment.
--   
--   <a>$sel:tier:EnvironmentDescription'</a>,
--   <a>environmentDescription_tier</a> - Describes the current tier of
--   this environment.
--   
--   <a>$sel:operationsRole:EnvironmentDescription'</a>,
--   <a>environmentDescription_operationsRole</a> - The Amazon Resource
--   Name (ARN) of the environment's operations role. For more information,
--   see <a>Operations roles</a> in the <i>AWS Elastic Beanstalk Developer
--   Guide</i>.
newEnvironmentDescription :: EnvironmentDescription

-- | <i>See:</i> <a>newCreateEnvironment</a> smart constructor.
data CreateEnvironment
CreateEnvironment' :: Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe [OptionSpecification] -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe [Tag] -> Maybe [ConfigurationOptionSetting] -> Maybe Text -> Maybe EnvironmentTier -> Maybe Text -> Text -> CreateEnvironment

-- | Create a value of <a>CreateEnvironment</a> with all optional fields
--   omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:templateName:CreateEnvironment'</a>,
--   <a>createEnvironment_templateName</a> - The name of the Elastic
--   Beanstalk configuration template to use with the environment.
--   
--   If you specify <tt>TemplateName</tt>, then don't specify
--   <tt>SolutionStackName</tt>.
--   
--   <a>$sel:solutionStackName:CreateEnvironment'</a>,
--   <a>createEnvironment_solutionStackName</a> - The name of an Elastic
--   Beanstalk solution stack (platform version) to use with the
--   environment. If specified, Elastic Beanstalk sets the configuration
--   values to the default values associated with the specified solution
--   stack. For a list of current solution stacks, see <a>Elastic Beanstalk
--   Supported Platforms</a> in the <i>AWS Elastic Beanstalk Platforms</i>
--   guide.
--   
--   If you specify <tt>SolutionStackName</tt>, don't specify
--   <tt>PlatformArn</tt> or <tt>TemplateName</tt>.
--   
--   <a>$sel:groupName:CreateEnvironment'</a>,
--   <a>createEnvironment_groupName</a> - The name of the group to which
--   the target environment belongs. Specify a group name only if the
--   environment's name is specified in an environment manifest and not
--   with the environment name parameter. See <a>Environment Manifest
--   (env.yaml)</a> for details.
--   
--   <a>$sel:optionsToRemove:CreateEnvironment'</a>,
--   <a>createEnvironment_optionsToRemove</a> - A list of custom
--   user-defined configuration options to remove from the configuration
--   set for this new environment.
--   
--   <a>$sel:platformArn:CreateEnvironment'</a>,
--   <a>createEnvironment_platformArn</a> - The Amazon Resource Name (ARN)
--   of the custom platform to use with the environment. For more
--   information, see <a>Custom Platforms</a> in the <i>AWS Elastic
--   Beanstalk Developer Guide</i>.
--   
--   If you specify <tt>PlatformArn</tt>, don't specify
--   <tt>SolutionStackName</tt>.
--   
--   <a>$sel:environmentName:CreateEnvironment'</a>,
--   <a>createEnvironment_environmentName</a> - A unique name for the
--   environment.
--   
--   Constraint: Must be from 4 to 40 characters in length. The name can
--   contain only letters, numbers, and hyphens. It can't start or end with
--   a hyphen. This name must be unique within a region in your account. If
--   the specified name already exists in the region, Elastic Beanstalk
--   returns an <tt>InvalidParameterValue</tt> error.
--   
--   If you don't specify the <tt>CNAMEPrefix</tt> parameter, the
--   environment name becomes part of the CNAME, and therefore part of the
--   visible URL for your application.
--   
--   <a>$sel:cNAMEPrefix:CreateEnvironment'</a>,
--   <a>createEnvironment_cNAMEPrefix</a> - If specified, the environment
--   attempts to use this value as the prefix for the CNAME in your Elastic
--   Beanstalk environment URL. If not specified, the CNAME is generated
--   automatically by appending a random alphanumeric string to the
--   environment name.
--   
--   <a>$sel:versionLabel:CreateEnvironment'</a>,
--   <a>createEnvironment_versionLabel</a> - The name of the application
--   version to deploy.
--   
--   Default: If not specified, Elastic Beanstalk attempts to deploy the
--   sample application.
--   
--   <a>$sel:tags:CreateEnvironment'</a>, <a>createEnvironment_tags</a> -
--   Specifies the tags applied to resources in the environment.
--   
--   <a>$sel:optionSettings:CreateEnvironment'</a>,
--   <a>createEnvironment_optionSettings</a> - If specified, AWS Elastic
--   Beanstalk sets the specified configuration options to the requested
--   value in the configuration set for the new environment. These override
--   the values obtained from the solution stack or the configuration
--   template.
--   
--   <a>$sel:description:CreateEnvironment'</a>,
--   <a>createEnvironment_description</a> - Your description for this
--   environment.
--   
--   <a>$sel:tier:CreateEnvironment'</a>, <a>createEnvironment_tier</a> -
--   Specifies the tier to use in creating this environment. The
--   environment tier that you choose determines whether Elastic Beanstalk
--   provisions resources to support a web application that handles HTTP(S)
--   requests or a web application that handles background-processing
--   tasks.
--   
--   <a>$sel:operationsRole:CreateEnvironment'</a>,
--   <a>createEnvironment_operationsRole</a> - The Amazon Resource Name
--   (ARN) of an existing IAM role to be used as the environment's
--   operations role. If specified, Elastic Beanstalk uses the operations
--   role for permissions to downstream services during this call and
--   during subsequent calls acting on this environment. To specify an
--   operations role, you must have the <tt>iam:PassRole</tt> permission
--   for the role. For more information, see <a>Operations roles</a> in the
--   <i>AWS Elastic Beanstalk Developer Guide</i>.
--   
--   <a>$sel:applicationName:CreateEnvironment'</a>,
--   <a>createEnvironment_applicationName</a> - The name of the application
--   that is associated with this environment.
newCreateEnvironment :: Text -> CreateEnvironment

--   results.

--   <a>$sel:severity:DescribeEvents'</a>, <a>describeEvents_severity</a> -
--   If specified, limits the events returned from this call to include
--   only those with the specified severity or higher.
--   
--   <a>$sel:environmentId:DescribeEvents'</a>,
--   <a>describeEvents_environmentId</a> - If specified, AWS Elastic
--   Beanstalk restricts the returned descriptions to those associated with
--   this environment.

--   <a>$sel:startTime:DescribeEvents'</a>, <a>describeEvents_startTime</a>
--   - If specified, AWS Elastic Beanstalk restricts the returned
--   descriptions to those that occur on or after this time.
--   
--   <a>$sel:platformArn:DescribeEvents'</a>,

--   version. If specified, AWS Elastic Beanstalk restricts the returned
--   descriptions to those associated with this custom platform version.
--   
--   <a>$sel:endTime:DescribeEvents'</a>, <a>describeEvents_endTime</a> -
--   If specified, AWS Elastic Beanstalk restricts the returned
--   descriptions to those that occur up to, but not including, the
--   <tt>EndTime</tt>.
--   
--   <a>$sel:environmentName:DescribeEvents'</a>,
--   <a>describeEvents_environmentName</a> - If specified, AWS Elastic
--   Beanstalk restricts the returned descriptions to those associated with
--   this environment.
--   
--   <a>$sel:versionLabel:DescribeEvents'</a>,
--   <a>describeEvents_versionLabel</a> - If specified, AWS Elastic
--   Beanstalk restricts the returned descriptions to those associated with
--   this application version.
--   
--   <a>$sel:requestId:DescribeEvents'</a>, <a>describeEvents_requestId</a>
--   - If specified, AWS Elastic Beanstalk restricts the described events
--   to include only those associated with this request ID.
--   
--   <a>$sel:applicationName:DescribeEvents'</a>,
--   <a>describeEvents_applicationName</a> - If specified, AWS Elastic
--   Beanstalk restricts the returned descriptions to include only those
--   associated with this application.
--   
--   <a>$sel:maxRecords:DescribeEvents'</a>,
--   <a>describeEvents_maxRecords</a> - Specifies the maximum number of
--   events that can be returned, beginning with the most recent event.
newDescribeEvents :: DescribeEvents

-- | Describes the properties of an environment.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newEnvironmentDescription</a> smart constructor.
data EnvironmentDescription
EnvironmentDescription' :: Maybe Bool -> Maybe Text -> Maybe EnvironmentStatus -> Maybe ISO8601 -> Maybe [EnvironmentLink] -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe EnvironmentHealth -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe ISO8601 -> Maybe EnvironmentResourcesDescription -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe EnvironmentHealthStatus -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe EnvironmentTier -> Maybe Text -> EnvironmentDescription

-- | Create a value of <a>EnvironmentDescription</a> with all optional
--   fields omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:abortableOperationInProgress:EnvironmentDescription'</a>,
--   <a>environmentDescription_abortableOperationInProgress</a> - Indicates
--   if there is an in-progress environment configuration update or
--   application version deployment that you can cancel.
--   
--   <tt>true:</tt> There is an update in progress.
--   
--   <tt>false:</tt> There are no updates currently in progress.
--   
--   <a>$sel:templateName:EnvironmentDescription'</a>,
--   <a>environmentDescription_templateName</a> - The name of the
--   configuration template used to originally launch this environment.
--   
--   <a>$sel:status:EnvironmentDescription'</a>,
--   <a>environmentDescription_status</a> - The current operational status
--   of the environment:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li><tt>Launching</tt>: Environment is in the process of initial
--   deployment.</li>
--   <li><tt>Updating</tt>: Environment is in the process of updating its
--   configuration settings or application version.</li>
--   <li><tt>Ready</tt>: Environment is available to have an action
--   performed on it, such as update or terminate.</li>
--   <li><tt>Terminating</tt>: Environment is in the shut-down
--   process.</li>
--   <li><tt>Terminated</tt>: Environment is not running.</li>
--   </ul>
--   
--   <a>$sel:dateCreated:EnvironmentDescription'</a>,
--   <a>environmentDescription_dateCreated</a> - The creation date for this
--   environment.
--   
--   <a>$sel:environmentLinks:EnvironmentDescription'</a>,
--   <a>environmentDescription_environmentLinks</a> - A list of links to
--   other environments in the same group.
--   
--   <a>$sel:environmentId:EnvironmentDescription'</a>,
--   <a>environmentDescription_environmentId</a> - The ID of this
--   environment.
--   
--   <a>$sel:solutionStackName:EnvironmentDescription'</a>,
--   <a>environmentDescription_solutionStackName</a> - The name of the
--   <tt>SolutionStack</tt> deployed with this environment.
--   
--   <a>$sel:platformArn:EnvironmentDescription'</a>,
--   <a>environmentDescription_platformArn</a> - The ARN of the platform
--   version.
--   
--   <a>$sel:environmentName:EnvironmentDescription'</a>,
--   <a>environmentDescription_environmentName</a> - The name of this
--   environment.
--   
--   <a>$sel:health:EnvironmentDescription'</a>,
--   <a>environmentDescription_health</a> - Describes the health status of
--   the environment. AWS Elastic Beanstalk indicates the failure levels
--   for a running environment:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li><tt>Red</tt>: Indicates the environment is not responsive. Occurs
--   when three or more consecutive failures occur for an environment.</li>
--   <li><tt>Yellow</tt>: Indicates that something is wrong. Occurs when
--   two consecutive failures occur for an environment.</li>
--   <li><tt>Green</tt>: Indicates the environment is healthy and fully
--   functional.</li>
--   <li><tt>Grey</tt>: Default health for a new environment. The
--   environment is not fully launched and health checks have not started
--   or health checks are suspended during an <tt>UpdateEnvironment</tt> or
--   <tt>RestartEnvironment</tt> request.</li>
--   </ul>
--   
--   Default: <tt>Grey</tt>
--   
--   <a>$sel:versionLabel:EnvironmentDescription'</a>,
--   <a>environmentDescription_versionLabel</a> - The application version
--   deployed in this environment.
--   
--   <a>$sel:cname:EnvironmentDescription'</a>,
--   <a>environmentDescription_cname</a> - The URL to the CNAME for this
--   environment.
--   
--   <a>$sel:dateUpdated:EnvironmentDescription'</a>,
--   <a>environmentDescription_dateUpdated</a> - The last modified date for
--   this environment.
--   
--   <a>$sel:resources:EnvironmentDescription'</a>,
--   <a>environmentDescription_resources</a> - The description of the AWS
--   resources used by this environment.
--   
--   <a>$sel:description:EnvironmentDescription'</a>,
--   <a>environmentDescription_description</a> - Describes this
--   environment.
--   
--   <a>$sel:endpointURL:EnvironmentDescription'</a>,
--   <a>environmentDescription_endpointURL</a> - For load-balanced,
--   autoscaling environments, the URL to the LoadBalancer. For
--   single-instance environments, the IP address of the instance.
--   
--   <a>$sel:healthStatus:EnvironmentDescription'</a>,
--   <a>environmentDescription_healthStatus</a> - Returns the health status
--   of the application running in your environment. For more information,
--   see <a>Health Colors and Statuses</a>.
--   
--   <a>$sel:environmentArn:EnvironmentDescription'</a>,
--   <a>environmentDescription_environmentArn</a> - The environment's
--   Amazon Resource Name (ARN), which can be used in other API requests
--   that require an ARN.
--   
--   <a>$sel:applicationName:EnvironmentDescription'</a>,
--   <a>environmentDescription_applicationName</a> - The name of the
--   application associated with this environment.
--   
--   <a>$sel:tier:EnvironmentDescription'</a>,
--   <a>environmentDescription_tier</a> - Describes the current tier of
--   this environment.
--   
--   <a>$sel:operationsRole:EnvironmentDescription'</a>,
--   <a>environmentDescription_operationsRole</a> - The Amazon Resource
--   Name (ARN) of the environment's operations role. For more information,
--   see <a>Operations roles</a> in the <i>AWS Elastic Beanstalk Developer
--   Guide</i>.
newEnvironmentDescription :: EnvironmentDescription

--   the configuration.

--   application associated with the configuration template to update.
--   
--   If no application is found with this name,
--   <tt>UpdateConfigurationTemplate</tt> returns an
--   <tt>InvalidParameterValue</tt> error.
--   
--   <a>$sel:templateName:UpdateConfigurationTemplate'</a>,

--   configuration template to update.

--   <tt>UpdateConfigurationTemplate</tt> returns an

--   configuration set is associated with an environment, the
--   <tt>DeploymentStatus</tt> parameter indicates the deployment status of
--   this configuration set:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li><tt>null</tt>: This configuration is not associated with a running
--   environment.</li>
--   <li><tt>pending</tt>: This is a draft configuration that is not
--   deployed to the associated environment but is in the process of
--   deploying.</li>
--   <li><tt>deployed</tt>: This is the configuration that is currently
--   deployed to the associated running environment.</li>
--   <li><tt>failed</tt>: This is a draft configuration that failed to
--   successfully deploy.</li>
--   </ul>
--   
--   <a>$sel:platformArn:ConfigurationSettingsDescription'</a>,
--   <a>configurationSettingsDescription_platformArn</a> - The ARN of the
--   platform version.
--   
--   <a>$sel:environmentName:ConfigurationSettingsDescription'</a>,
--   <a>configurationSettingsDescription_environmentName</a> - If not
--   <tt>null</tt>, the name of the environment for this configuration set.
--   
--   <a>$sel:dateUpdated:ConfigurationSettingsDescription'</a>,
--   <a>configurationSettingsDescription_dateUpdated</a> - The date (in UTC
--   time) when this configuration set was last modified.
--   
--   <a>$sel:optionSettings:ConfigurationSettingsDescription'</a>,
--   <a>configurationSettingsDescription_optionSettings</a> - A list of the
--   configuration options and their values in this configuration set.
--   
--   <a>$sel:description:ConfigurationSettingsDescription'</a>,
--   <a>configurationSettingsDescription_description</a> - Describes this
--   configuration set.
--   
--   <a>$sel:applicationName:ConfigurationSettingsDescription'</a>,
--   <a>configurationSettingsDescription_applicationName</a> - The name of
--   the application associated with this configuration set.

-- | The resource lifecycle configuration for an application. Defines
--   lifecycle settings for resources that belong to the application, and
--   the service role that AWS Elastic Beanstalk assumes in order to apply
--   lifecycle settings. The version lifecycle configuration defines
--   lifecycle settings for application versions.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newApplicationResourceLifecycleConfig</a> smart
--   constructor.
data ApplicationResourceLifecycleConfig
ApplicationResourceLifecycleConfig' :: Maybe Text -> Maybe ApplicationVersionLifecycleConfig -> ApplicationResourceLifecycleConfig

-- | Create a value of <a>ApplicationResourceLifecycleConfig</a> with all
--   optional fields omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:serviceRole:ApplicationResourceLifecycleConfig'</a>,
--   <a>applicationResourceLifecycleConfig_serviceRole</a> - The ARN of an
--   IAM service role that Elastic Beanstalk has permission to assume.
--   
--   The <tt>ServiceRole</tt> property is required the first time that you
--   provide a <tt>VersionLifecycleConfig</tt> for the application in one
--   of the supporting calls (<tt>CreateApplication</tt> or
--   <tt>UpdateApplicationResourceLifecycle</tt>). After you provide it
--   once, in either one of the calls, Elastic Beanstalk persists the
--   Service Role with the application, and you don't need to specify it
--   again in subsequent <tt>UpdateApplicationResourceLifecycle</tt> calls.
--   You can, however, specify it in subsequent calls to change the Service
--   Role to another value.
--   
--   
--   <a>$sel:versionLifecycleConfig:ApplicationResourceLifecycleConfig'</a>,
--   <a>applicationResourceLifecycleConfig_versionLifecycleConfig</a> -
--   Defines lifecycle settings for application versions.
newApplicationResourceLifecycleConfig :: ApplicationResourceLifecycleConfig

-- | Describes the properties of an application version.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newApplicationVersionDescription</a> smart constructor.
data ApplicationVersionDescription
ApplicationVersionDescription' :: Maybe ApplicationVersionStatus -> Maybe ISO8601 -> Maybe S3Location -> Maybe SourceBuildInformation -> Maybe Text -> Maybe ISO8601 -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> ApplicationVersionDescription

-- | Create a value of <a>ApplicationVersionDescription</a> with all
--   optional fields omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:status:ApplicationVersionDescription'</a>,
--   <a>applicationVersionDescription_status</a> - The processing status of
--   the application version. Reflects the state of the application version
--   during its creation. Many of the values are only applicable if you
--   specified <tt>True</tt> for the <tt>Process</tt> parameter of the
--   <tt>CreateApplicationVersion</tt> action. The following list describes
--   the possible values.
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li><tt>Unprocessed</tt> – Application version wasn't pre-processed or
--   validated. Elastic Beanstalk will validate configuration files during
--   deployment of the application version to an environment.</li>
--   <li><tt>Processing</tt> – Elastic Beanstalk is currently processing
--   the application version.</li>
--   <li><tt>Building</tt> – Application version is currently undergoing an
--   AWS CodeBuild build.</li>
--   <li><tt>Processed</tt> – Elastic Beanstalk was successfully
--   pre-processed and validated.</li>
--   <li><tt>Failed</tt> – Either the AWS CodeBuild build failed or
--   configuration files didn't pass validation. This application version
--   isn't usable.</li>
--   </ul>
--   
--   <a>$sel:dateCreated:ApplicationVersionDescription'</a>,
--   <a>applicationVersionDescription_dateCreated</a> - The creation date
--   of the application version.
--   
--   <a>$sel:sourceBundle:ApplicationVersionDescription'</a>,
--   <a>applicationVersionDescription_sourceBundle</a> - The storage
--   location of the application version's source bundle in Amazon S3.
--   
--   <a>$sel:sourceBuildInformation:ApplicationVersionDescription'</a>,
--   <a>applicationVersionDescription_sourceBuildInformation</a> - If the
--   version's source code was retrieved from AWS CodeCommit, the location
--   of the source code for the application version.
--   
--   <a>$sel:versionLabel:ApplicationVersionDescription'</a>,
--   <a>applicationVersionDescription_versionLabel</a> - A unique
--   identifier for the application version.
--   
--   <a>$sel:dateUpdated:ApplicationVersionDescription'</a>,
--   <a>applicationVersionDescription_dateUpdated</a> - The last modified
--   date of the application version.
--   
--   <a>$sel:description:ApplicationVersionDescription'</a>,
--   <a>applicationVersionDescription_description</a> - The description of
--   the application version.
--   
--   <a>$sel:buildArn:ApplicationVersionDescription'</a>,
--   <a>applicationVersionDescription_buildArn</a> - Reference to the
--   artifact from the AWS CodeBuild build.
--   
--   <a>$sel:applicationName:ApplicationVersionDescription'</a>,
--   <a>applicationVersionDescription_applicationName</a> - The name of the
--   application to which the application version belongs.
--   
--   <a>$sel:applicationVersionArn:ApplicationVersionDescription'</a>,
--   <a>applicationVersionDescription_applicationVersionArn</a> - The
--   Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the application version.

-- | The application version lifecycle settings for an application. Defines
--   the rules that Elastic Beanstalk applies to an application's versions
--   in order to avoid hitting the per-region limit for application
--   versions.
--   
--   When Elastic Beanstalk deletes an application version from its
--   database, you can no longer deploy that version to an environment. The
--   source bundle remains in S3 unless you configure the rule to delete
--   it.

--   <i>See:</i> <a>newApplicationVersionLifecycleConfig</a> smart
--   constructor.

--   count rule to restrict the number of application versions that are
--   retained for an application.
--   
--   <a>$sel:maxAgeRule:ApplicationVersionLifecycleConfig'</a>,

data BuildConfiguration
BuildConfiguration' :: Maybe Text -> Maybe Int -> Maybe ComputeType -> Text -> Text -> BuildConfiguration

-- | Create a value of <a>BuildConfiguration</a> with all optional fields
--   omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:artifactName:BuildConfiguration'</a>,
--   <a>buildConfiguration_artifactName</a> - The name of the artifact of
--   the CodeBuild build. If provided, Elastic Beanstalk stores the build
--   artifact in the S3 location
--   <i>S3-bucket</i>/resources/<i>application-name</i>/codebuild/codebuild-<i>version-label</i>-<i>artifact-name</i>.zip.
--   If not provided, Elastic Beanstalk stores the build artifact in the S3
--   location
--   <i>S3-bucket</i>/resources/<i>application-name</i>/codebuild/codebuild-<i>version-label</i>.zip.
--   
--   <a>$sel:timeoutInMinutes:BuildConfiguration'</a>,
--   <a>buildConfiguration_timeoutInMinutes</a> - How long in minutes, from
--   5 to 480 (8 hours), for AWS CodeBuild to wait until timing out any
--   related build that does not get marked as completed. The default is 60
--   minutes.
--   
--   <a>$sel:computeType:BuildConfiguration'</a>,
--   <a>buildConfiguration_computeType</a> - Information about the compute
--   resources the build project will use.
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li><pre>BUILD_GENERAL1_SMALL: Use up to 3 GB memory and 2 vCPUs for
--   builds</pre></li>
--   <li><pre>BUILD_GENERAL1_MEDIUM: Use up to 7 GB memory and 4 vCPUs for
--   builds</pre></li>
--   <li><pre>BUILD_GENERAL1_LARGE: Use up to 15 GB memory and 8 vCPUs for
--   builds</pre></li>
--   </ul>
--   
--   <a>$sel:codeBuildServiceRole:BuildConfiguration'</a>,
--   <a>buildConfiguration_codeBuildServiceRole</a> - The Amazon Resource
--   Name (ARN) of the AWS Identity and Access Management (IAM) role that
--   enables AWS CodeBuild to interact with dependent AWS services on
--   behalf of the AWS account.
--   
--   <a>$sel:image:BuildConfiguration'</a>, <a>buildConfiguration_image</a>
--   - The ID of the Docker image to use for this build project.
newBuildConfiguration :: Text -> Text -> BuildConfiguration

--   
--   <a>$sel:idle:CPUUtilization'</a>, <a>cPUUtilization_idle</a> -
--   Percentage of time that the CPU has spent in the <tt>Idle</tt> state
--   over the last 10 seconds.
--   
--   <a>$sel:user:CPUUtilization'</a>, <a>cPUUtilization_user</a> -
--   Percentage of time that the CPU has spent in the <tt>User</tt> state
--   over the last 10 seconds.
--   
--   <a>$sel:privileged:CPUUtilization'</a>,
--   <a>cPUUtilization_privileged</a> - Available on Windows environments
--   only.
--   
--   Percentage of time that the CPU has spent in the <tt>Privileged</tt>
--   state over the last 10 seconds.
--   
--   <a>$sel:iOWait:CPUUtilization'</a>, <a>cPUUtilization_iOWait</a> -
--   Available on Linux environments only.
--   
--   Percentage of time that the CPU has spent in the <tt>I/O Wait</tt>
--   state over the last 10 seconds.
--   
--   <a>$sel:softIRQ:CPUUtilization'</a>, <a>cPUUtilization_softIRQ</a> -
--   Available on Linux environments only.
--   
--   Percentage of time that the CPU has spent in the <tt>SoftIRQ</tt>
--   state over the last 10 seconds.
--   
--   <a>$sel:nice:CPUUtilization'</a>, <a>cPUUtilization_nice</a> -
--   Available on Linux environments only.
--   
--   Percentage of time that the CPU has spent in the <tt>Nice</tt> state
--   over the last 10 seconds.
--   
--   <a>$sel:system:CPUUtilization'</a>, <a>cPUUtilization_system</a> -
--   Available on Linux environments only.
--   
--   Percentage of time that the CPU has spent in the <tt>System</tt> state
--   over the last 10 seconds.
--   
--   <a>$sel:irq:CPUUtilization'</a>, <a>cPUUtilization_irq</a> - Available
--   on Linux environments only.
--   
--   Percentage of time that the CPU has spent in the <tt>IRQ</tt> state
--   over the last 10 seconds.
newCPUUtilization :: CPUUtilization

-- | Describes the possible values for a configuration option.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newConfigurationOptionDescription</a> smart
--   constructor.
data ConfigurationOptionDescription
ConfigurationOptionDescription' :: Maybe Int -> Maybe [Text] -> Maybe ConfigurationOptionValueType -> Maybe Text -> Maybe OptionRestrictionRegex -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Int -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Int -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Bool -> ConfigurationOptionDescription

-- | Create a value of <a>ConfigurationOptionDescription</a> with all
--   optional fields omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:maxValue:ConfigurationOptionDescription'</a>,
--   <a>configurationOptionDescription_maxValue</a> - If specified, the
--   configuration option must be a numeric value less than this value.
--   
--   <a>$sel:valueOptions:ConfigurationOptionDescription'</a>,
--   <a>configurationOptionDescription_valueOptions</a> - If specified,
--   values for the configuration option are selected from this list.
--   
--   <a>$sel:valueType:ConfigurationOptionDescription'</a>,
--   <a>configurationOptionDescription_valueType</a> - An indication of
--   which type of values this option has and whether it is allowable to
--   select one or more than one of the possible values:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li><tt>Scalar</tt> : Values for this option are a single selection
--   from the possible values, or an unformatted string, or numeric value
--   governed by the <tt>MIN/MAX/Regex</tt> constraints.</li>
--   <li><tt>List</tt> : Values for this option are multiple selections
--   from the possible values.</li>
--   <li><tt>Boolean</tt> : Values for this option are either <tt>true</tt>
--   or <tt>false</tt> .</li>
--   <li><tt>Json</tt> : Values for this option are a JSON representation
--   of a <tt>ConfigDocument</tt>.</li>
--   </ul>
--   
--   <a>$sel:changeSeverity:ConfigurationOptionDescription'</a>,
--   <a>configurationOptionDescription_changeSeverity</a> - An indication
--   of which action is required if the value for this configuration option
--   changes:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li><tt>NoInterruption</tt> : There is no interruption to the
--   environment or application availability.</li>
--   <li><tt>RestartEnvironment</tt> : The environment is entirely
--   restarted, all AWS resources are deleted and recreated, and the
--   environment is unavailable during the process.</li>
--   <li><tt>RestartApplicationServer</tt> : The environment is available
--   the entire time. However, a short application outage occurs when the
--   application servers on the running Amazon EC2 instances are
--   restarted.</li>
--   </ul>
--   
--   <a>$sel:regex:ConfigurationOptionDescription'</a>,
--   <a>configurationOptionDescription_regex</a> - If specified, the
--   configuration option must be a string value that satisfies this
--   regular expression.
--   
--   <a>$sel:name:ConfigurationOptionDescription'</a>,
--   <a>configurationOptionDescription_name</a> - The name of the
--   configuration option.
--   
--   <a>$sel:minValue:ConfigurationOptionDescription'</a>,
--   <a>configurationOptionDescription_minValue</a> - If specified, the
--   configuration option must be a numeric value greater than this value.
--   
--   <a>$sel:namespace:ConfigurationOptionDescription'</a>,
--   <a>configurationOptionDescription_namespace</a> - A unique namespace
--   identifying the option's associated AWS resource.
--   
--   <a>$sel:maxLength:ConfigurationOptionDescription'</a>,
--   <a>configurationOptionDescription_maxLength</a> - If specified, the
--   configuration option must be a string value no longer than this value.
--   
--   <a>$sel:defaultValue:ConfigurationOptionDescription'</a>,
--   <a>configurationOptionDescription_defaultValue</a> - The default value
--   for this configuration option.
--   
--   <a>$sel:userDefined:ConfigurationOptionDescription'</a>,
--   <a>configurationOptionDescription_userDefined</a> - An indication of
--   whether the user defined this configuration option:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li><tt>true</tt> : This configuration option was defined by the user.
--   It is a valid choice for specifying if this as an <tt>Option to
--   Remove</tt> when updating configuration settings.</li>
--   <li><tt>false</tt> : This configuration was not defined by the
--   user.</li>
--   </ul>
--   
--   Constraint: You can remove only <tt>UserDefined</tt> options from a
--   configuration.
--   
--   Valid Values: <tt>true</tt> | <tt>false</tt>
newConfigurationOptionDescription :: ConfigurationOptionDescription

-- | A specification identifying an individual configuration option along
--   with its current value. For a list of possible namespaces and option
--   values, see <a>Option Values</a> in the <i>AWS Elastic Beanstalk
--   Developer Guide</i>.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newConfigurationOptionSetting</a> smart constructor.

--   <a>configurationOptionSetting_value</a> - The current value for the
--   configuration option.
--   
--   <a>$sel:namespace:ConfigurationOptionSetting'</a>,
--   <a>configurationOptionSetting_namespace</a> - A unique namespace that
--   identifies the option's associated AWS resource.

--   configuration set.

--   time) when this configuration set was created.

--   of the solution stack this configuration set uses.
--

--   <a>configurationSettingsDescription_deploymentStatus</a> - If this
--   configuration set is associated with an environment, the
--   <tt>DeploymentStatus</tt> parameter indicates the deployment status of
--   this configuration set:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li><tt>null</tt>: This configuration is not associated with a running
--   environment.</li>
--   <li><tt>pending</tt>: This is a draft configuration that is not
--   deployed to the associated environment but is in the process of
--   deploying.</li>
--   <li><tt>deployed</tt>: This is the configuration that is currently
--   deployed to the associated running environment.</li>
--   <li><tt>failed</tt>: This is a draft configuration that failed to
--   successfully deploy.</li>
--   </ul>
--

--   platform version.
--   
--   <a>$sel:environmentName:ConfigurationSettingsDescription'</a>,
--   <a>configurationSettingsDescription_environmentName</a> - If not
--   <tt>null</tt>, the name of the environment for this configuration set.
--   
--   <a>$sel:dateUpdated:ConfigurationSettingsDescription'</a>,
--   <a>configurationSettingsDescription_dateUpdated</a> - The date (in UTC
--   time) when this configuration set was last modified.
--   
--   <a>$sel:optionSettings:ConfigurationSettingsDescription'</a>,
--   <a>configurationSettingsDescription_optionSettings</a> - A list of the
--   configuration options and their values in this configuration set.
--   
--   <a>$sel:description:ConfigurationSettingsDescription'</a>,
--   <a>configurationSettingsDescription_description</a> - Describes this
--   configuration set.
--   
--   <a>$sel:applicationName:ConfigurationSettingsDescription'</a>,
--   <a>configurationSettingsDescription_applicationName</a> - The name of
--   the application associated with this configuration set.
newConfigurationSettingsDescription :: ConfigurationSettingsDescription

-- | Describes the properties of an environment.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newEnvironmentDescription</a> smart constructor.
data EnvironmentDescription
EnvironmentDescription' :: Maybe Bool -> Maybe Text -> Maybe EnvironmentStatus -> Maybe ISO8601 -> Maybe [EnvironmentLink] -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe EnvironmentHealth -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe ISO8601 -> Maybe EnvironmentResourcesDescription -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe EnvironmentHealthStatus -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe EnvironmentTier -> Maybe Text -> EnvironmentDescription

-- | Create a value of <a>EnvironmentDescription</a> with all optional
--   fields omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:abortableOperationInProgress:EnvironmentDescription'</a>,
--   <a>environmentDescription_abortableOperationInProgress</a> - Indicates
--   if there is an in-progress environment configuration update or
--   application version deployment that you can cancel.
--   
--   <tt>true:</tt> There is an update in progress.
--   
--   <tt>false:</tt> There are no updates currently in progress.
--   
--   <a>$sel:templateName:EnvironmentDescription'</a>,
--   <a>environmentDescription_templateName</a> - The name of the
--   configuration template used to originally launch this environment.
--   
--   <a>$sel:status:EnvironmentDescription'</a>,
--   <a>environmentDescription_status</a> - The current operational status
--   of the environment:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li><tt>Launching</tt>: Environment is in the process of initial
--   deployment.</li>
--   <li><tt>Updating</tt>: Environment is in the process of updating its
--   configuration settings or application version.</li>
--   <li><tt>Ready</tt>: Environment is available to have an action
--   performed on it, such as update or terminate.</li>
--   <li><tt>Terminating</tt>: Environment is in the shut-down
--   process.</li>
--   <li><tt>Terminated</tt>: Environment is not running.</li>
--   </ul>
--   
--   <a>$sel:dateCreated:EnvironmentDescription'</a>,
--   <a>environmentDescription_dateCreated</a> - The creation date for this
--   environment.
--   
--   <a>$sel:environmentLinks:EnvironmentDescription'</a>,
--   <a>environmentDescription_environmentLinks</a> - A list of links to
--   other environments in the same group.
--   
--   <a>$sel:environmentId:EnvironmentDescription'</a>,
--   <a>environmentDescription_environmentId</a> - The ID of this
--   environment.
--   
--   <a>$sel:solutionStackName:EnvironmentDescription'</a>,
--   <a>environmentDescription_solutionStackName</a> - The name of the
--   <tt>SolutionStack</tt> deployed with this environment.
--   
--   <a>$sel:platformArn:EnvironmentDescription'</a>,
--   <a>environmentDescription_platformArn</a> - The ARN of the platform
--   version.
--   
--   <a>$sel:environmentName:EnvironmentDescription'</a>,
--   <a>environmentDescription_environmentName</a> - The name of this
--   environment.
--   
--   <a>$sel:health:EnvironmentDescription'</a>,
--   <a>environmentDescription_health</a> - Describes the health status of
--   the environment. AWS Elastic Beanstalk indicates the failure levels
--   for a running environment:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li><tt>Red</tt>: Indicates the environment is not responsive. Occurs
--   when three or more consecutive failures occur for an environment.</li>
--   <li><tt>Yellow</tt>: Indicates that something is wrong. Occurs when
--   two consecutive failures occur for an environment.</li>
--   <li><tt>Green</tt>: Indicates the environment is healthy and fully
--   functional.</li>
--   <li><tt>Grey</tt>: Default health for a new environment. The
--   environment is not fully launched and health checks have not started
--   or health checks are suspended during an <tt>UpdateEnvironment</tt> or
--   <tt>RestartEnvironment</tt> request.</li>
--   </ul>
--   
--   Default: <tt>Grey</tt>
--   
--   <a>$sel:versionLabel:EnvironmentDescription'</a>,
--   <a>environmentDescription_versionLabel</a> - The application version
--   deployed in this environment.
--   
--   <a>$sel:cname:EnvironmentDescription'</a>,
--   <a>environmentDescription_cname</a> - The URL to the CNAME for this
--   environment.
--   
--   <a>$sel:dateUpdated:EnvironmentDescription'</a>,
--   <a>environmentDescription_dateUpdated</a> - The last modified date for
--   this environment.
--   
--   <a>$sel:resources:EnvironmentDescription'</a>,
--   <a>environmentDescription_resources</a> - The description of the AWS
--   resources used by this environment.
--   
--   <a>$sel:description:EnvironmentDescription'</a>,
--   <a>environmentDescription_description</a> - Describes this
--   environment.
--   
--   <a>$sel:endpointURL:EnvironmentDescription'</a>,
--   <a>environmentDescription_endpointURL</a> - For load-balanced,
--   autoscaling environments, the URL to the LoadBalancer. For
--   single-instance environments, the IP address of the instance.
--   
--   <a>$sel:healthStatus:EnvironmentDescription'</a>,
--   <a>environmentDescription_healthStatus</a> - Returns the health status
--   of the application running in your environment. For more information,
--   see <a>Health Colors and Statuses</a>.
--   
--   <a>$sel:environmentArn:EnvironmentDescription'</a>,
--   <a>environmentDescription_environmentArn</a> - The environment's
--   Amazon Resource Name (ARN), which can be used in other API requests
--   that require an ARN.
--   
--   <a>$sel:applicationName:EnvironmentDescription'</a>,
--   <a>environmentDescription_applicationName</a> - The name of the
--   application associated with this environment.
--   
--   <a>$sel:tier:EnvironmentDescription'</a>,
--   <a>environmentDescription_tier</a> - Describes the current tier of
--   this environment.
--   
--   <a>$sel:operationsRole:EnvironmentDescription'</a>,
--   <a>environmentDescription_operationsRole</a> - The Amazon Resource
--   Name (ARN) of the environment's operations role. For more information,
--   see <a>Operations roles</a> in the <i>AWS Elastic Beanstalk Developer
--   Guide</i>.
newEnvironmentDescription :: EnvironmentDescription

--   fields.
--

--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:version:EnvironmentTier'</a>, <a>environmentTier_version</a> -
--   The version of this environment tier. When you don't set a value to
--   it, Elastic Beanstalk uses the latest compatible worker tier version.
--   
--   This member is deprecated. Any specific version that you set may
--   become out of date. We recommend leaving it unspecified.

--   <a>$sel:name:EnvironmentTier'</a>, <a>environmentTier_name</a> - The
--   name of this environment tier.
--   
--   Valid values:
--

--   <li>For <i>Web server tier</i> – <tt>WebServer</tt></li>
--   <li>For <i>Worker tier</i> – <tt>Worker</tt></li>
--   </ul>

--   type of this environment tier.
--   
--   Valid values:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li>For <i>Web server tier</i> – <tt>Standard</tt></li>
--   <li>For <i>Worker tier</i> – <tt>SQS/HTTP</tt></li>
--   </ul>
newEnvironmentTier :: EnvironmentTier

-- | Represents summary information about the health of an instance. For
--   more information, see <a>Health Colors and Statuses</a>.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newInstanceHealthSummary</a> smart constructor.
data InstanceHealthSummary
InstanceHealthSummary' :: Maybe Int -> Maybe Int -> Maybe Int -> Maybe Int -> Maybe Int -> Maybe Int -> Maybe Int -> Maybe Int -> InstanceHealthSummary

-- | Create a value of <a>InstanceHealthSummary</a> with all optional
--   fields omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:ok:InstanceHealthSummary'</a>, <a>instanceHealthSummary_ok</a>
--   - <b>Green.</b> An instance is passing health checks and the health
--   agent is not reporting any problems.
--   
--   <a>$sel:noData:InstanceHealthSummary'</a>,
--   <a>instanceHealthSummary_noData</a> - <b>Grey.</b> AWS Elastic
--   Beanstalk and the health agent are reporting no data on an instance.
--   
--   <a>$sel:info:InstanceHealthSummary'</a>,
--   <a>instanceHealthSummary_info</a> - <b>Green.</b> An operation is in
--   progress on an instance.
--   
--   <a>$sel:severe:InstanceHealthSummary'</a>,
--   <a>instanceHealthSummary_severe</a> - <b>Red.</b> The health agent is
--   reporting a very high number of request failures or other issues for
--   an instance or environment.
--   
--   <a>$sel:warning:InstanceHealthSummary'</a>,
--   <a>instanceHealthSummary_warning</a> - <b>Yellow.</b> The health agent
--   is reporting a moderate number of request failures or other issues for
--   an instance or environment.
--   
--   <a>$sel:pending:InstanceHealthSummary'</a>,
--   <a>instanceHealthSummary_pending</a> - <b>Grey.</b> An operation is in
--   progress on an instance within the command timeout.
--   
--   <a>$sel:unknown:InstanceHealthSummary'</a>,
--   <a>instanceHealthSummary_unknown</a> - <b>Grey.</b> AWS Elastic
--   Beanstalk and the health agent are reporting an insufficient amount of
--   data on an instance.
--   
--   <a>$sel:degraded:InstanceHealthSummary'</a>,
--   <a>instanceHealthSummary_degraded</a> - <b>Red.</b> The health agent
--   is reporting a high number of request failures or other issues for an
--   instance or environment.
newInstanceHealthSummary :: InstanceHealthSummary

--   number of days.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newMaxAgeRule</a> smart constructor.
data MaxAgeRule

-- | Create a value of <a>MaxAgeRule</a> with all optional fields omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--

--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:deleteSourceFromS3:MaxAgeRule'</a>,
--   <a>maxAgeRule_deleteSourceFromS3</a> - Set to <tt>true</tt> to delete
--   a version's source bundle from Amazon S3 when Elastic Beanstalk
--   deletes the application version.
--   
--   <a>$sel:maxAgeInDays:MaxAgeRule'</a>, <a>maxAgeRule_maxAgeInDays</a> -
--   Specify the number of days to retain an application versions.
--   
--   <a>$sel:enabled:MaxAgeRule'</a>, <a>maxAgeRule_enabled</a> - Specify
--   <tt>true</tt> to apply the rule, or <tt>false</tt> to disable it.
newMaxAgeRule :: Bool -> MaxAgeRule

--   <a>platformBranchSummary_branchOrder</a> - An ordinal number that

--   platform. This can be helpful, for example, if your code calls the
--   <tt>ListPlatformBranches</tt> action and then displays a list of
--   platform branches.

--   A larger <tt>BranchOrder</tt> value designates a newer platform branch

--   <tt>Worker/SQS/HTTP</tt>

--   <a>platformBranchSummary_platformName</a> - The name of the platform

--   
--   <a>$sel:dateUpdated:PlatformDescription'</a>,
--   <a>platformDescription_dateUpdated</a> - The date when the platform
--   version was last updated.
--   
--   <a>$sel:supportedTierList:PlatformDescription'</a>,
--   <a>platformDescription_supportedTierList</a> - The tiers supported by
--   the platform version.
--   
--   <a>$sel:maintainer:PlatformDescription'</a>,
--   <a>platformDescription_maintainer</a> - Information about the
--   maintainer of the platform version.
--   
--   <a>$sel:description:PlatformDescription'</a>,
--   <a>platformDescription_description</a> - The description of the
--   platform version.
--   
--   <a>$sel:platformLifecycleState:PlatformDescription'</a>,
--   <a>platformDescription_platformLifecycleState</a> - The state of the
--   platform version in its lifecycle.
--   
--   Possible values: <tt>Recommended</tt> | <tt>null</tt>
--   
--   If a null value is returned, the platform version isn't the
--   recommended one for its branch. Each platform branch has a single
--   recommended platform version, typically the most recent one.
--   
--   <a>$sel:platformName:PlatformDescription'</a>,
--   <a>platformDescription_platformName</a> - The name of the platform
--   version.
--   
--   <a>$sel:programmingLanguages:PlatformDescription'</a>,
--   <a>platformDescription_programmingLanguages</a> - The programming
--   languages supported by the platform version.
--   
--   <a>$sel:operatingSystemVersion:PlatformDescription'</a>,
--   <a>platformDescription_operatingSystemVersion</a> - The version of the
--   operating system used by the platform version.
newPlatformDescription :: PlatformDescription

-- | Describes criteria to restrict the results when listing platform
--   versions.
--   
--   The filter is evaluated as follows: <tt>Type Operator Values[1]</tt>
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newPlatformFilter</a> smart constructor.
data PlatformFilter
PlatformFilter' :: Maybe [Text] -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> PlatformFilter

-- | Create a value of <a>PlatformFilter</a> with all optional fields
--   omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:values:PlatformFilter'</a>, <a>platformFilter_values</a> - The
--   list of values applied to the filtering platform version attribute.
--   Only one value is supported for all current operators.
--   
--   The following list shows valid filter values for some filter
--   attributes.
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li><tt>PlatformStatus</tt>: <tt>Creating</tt> | <tt>Failed</tt> |
--   <tt>Ready</tt> | <tt>Deleting</tt> | <tt>Deleted</tt></li>
--   <li><tt>PlatformLifecycleState</tt>: <tt>recommended</tt></li>
--   <li><tt>SupportedTier</tt>: <tt>WebServer/Standard</tt> |
--   <tt>Worker/SQS/HTTP</tt></li>
--   <li><tt>SupportedAddon</tt>: <tt>Log/S3</tt> |
--   <tt>Monitoring/Healthd</tt> | <tt>WorkerDaemon/SQSD</tt></li>
--   </ul>
--   
--   <a>$sel:operator:PlatformFilter'</a>, <a>platformFilter_operator</a> -
--   The operator to apply to the <tt>Type</tt> with each of the
--   <tt>Values</tt>.
--   
--   Valid values: <tt>=</tt> | <tt>!=</tt> | <tt>&lt;</tt> |
--   <tt>&lt;=</tt> | <tt>&gt;</tt> | <tt>&gt;=</tt> | <tt>contains</tt> |
--   <tt>begins_with</tt> | <tt>ends_with</tt>
--   
--   <a>$sel:type':PlatformFilter'</a>, <a>platformFilter_type</a> - The
--   platform version attribute to which the filter values are applied.
--   
--   Valid values: <tt>PlatformName</tt> | <tt>PlatformVersion</tt> |
--   <tt>PlatformStatus</tt> | <tt>PlatformBranchName</tt> |
--   <tt>PlatformLifecycleState</tt> | <tt>PlatformOwner</tt> |
--   <tt>SupportedTier</tt> | <tt>SupportedAddon</tt> |
--   <tt>ProgrammingLanguageName</tt> | <tt>OperatingSystemName</tt>
newPlatformFilter :: PlatformFilter

-- | Describes criteria to restrict a list of results.
--   
--   For operators that apply a single value to the attribute, the filter
--   is evaluated as follows: <tt>Attribute Operator Values[1]</tt>
--   
--   Some operators, e.g. <tt>in</tt>, can apply multiple values. In this
--   case, the filter is evaluated as a logical union (OR) of applications
--   of the operator to the attribute with each one of the values:
--   <tt>(Attribute Operator Values[1]) OR (Attribute Operator Values[2])
--   OR ...</tt>
--   
--   The valid values for attributes of <tt>SearchFilter</tt> depend on the
--   API action. For valid values, see the reference page for the API
--   action you're calling that takes a <tt>SearchFilter</tt> parameter.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newSearchFilter</a> smart constructor.
data SearchFilter
SearchFilter' :: Maybe [Text] -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> SearchFilter

-- | Create a value of <a>SearchFilter</a> with all optional fields
--   omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:values:SearchFilter'</a>, <a>searchFilter_values</a> - The
--   list of values applied to the <tt>Attribute</tt> and <tt>Operator</tt>
--   attributes. Number of values and valid values vary by
--   <tt>Attribute</tt>.
--   
--   <a>$sel:operator:SearchFilter'</a>, <a>searchFilter_operator</a> - The
--   operator to apply to the <tt>Attribute</tt> with each of the
--   <tt>Values</tt>. Valid values vary by <tt>Attribute</tt>.
--   
--   <a>$sel:attribute:SearchFilter'</a>, <a>searchFilter_attribute</a> -
--   The result attribute to which the filter values are applied. Valid
--   values vary by API action.
newSearchFilter :: SearchFilter
